'''Harry Edward Styles''' (born 1 February 1994) is an English singer.<!--Keep most notable occupation in lead per [[MOS:ROLEBIO]].--> Known for [[Cultural impact of Harry Styles|his influence in popular culture]], showmanship, artistry, and philanthropy, he is a subject of widespread public interest with a vast fanbase. Styles is considered to be among the most successful solo artists who have emerged from a boy band.

Styles' musical career began in 2010 as part of [[One Direction]], a boy band formed on the British music competition series ''[[The X Factor (British TV series)|The X Factor]]'' after each member of the band had been eliminated from the solo contest. They became one of the [[List of best-selling boy groups|best-selling boy bands]] of all time before going on an indefinite hiatus in 2016. Styles released his [[Harry Styles (album)|self-titled debut solo album]] through [[Erskine Records|Erskine]] and [[Columbia Records]] in 2017. It debuted at number one in the UK and the US and was one of the world's top-ten best-selling albums of the year, while its lead single, "[[Sign of the Times (Harry Styles song)|Sign of the Times]]," topped the [[UK Singles Chart]].

His second album, ''[[Fine Line (Harry Styles album)|Fine Line]]'' (2019), debuted atop the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with the biggest ever first-week sales by an English male artist, with ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' including it in their 2020 revision of the [[Rolling Stone's 500 Greatest Albums of All Time|500 Greatest Albums of All Time]]. Its fourth single, "[[Watermelon Sugar]]," topped the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. Styles' widely acclaimed third album, ''[[Harry's House]]'' (2022), broke several records, receiving the [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year]] in [[65th Annual Grammy Awards|2023]]. It was included in the 2023 revision of ''Rolling Stone''{{'}}s 500 Greatest Albums of All Time. Its lead single, "[[As It Was]]," became the [[List of Billboard Global 200 number ones of 2022|number-one song of 2022 globally]], according to ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.

Styles [[List of awards and nominations received by Harry Styles|has received various accolades]], including six [[Brit Award]]s, three [[Grammy Award]]s, two [[Ivor Novello Award]]s, three [[American Music Awards]], and four [[MTV Video Music Awards]]. His film roles include ''[[Dunkirk (2017 film)|Dunkirk]]'' (2017), ''[[Don't Worry Darling]]'' (2022), and ''[[My Policeman (film)|My Policeman]]'' (2022). Aside from music and acting, Styles is known for his flamboyant fashion. He is the first man to appear solo on the cover of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]].''
{{TOC limit|limit=3}}

==Early life==
Harry Edward Styles was born on 1 February 1994 in [[Redditch, Worcestershire]], England,{{efn|His father clarified that he was not born in the neighboring town [[Bromsgrove]], where his birth was registered.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bromsgroveadvertiser.co.uk/news/10913305.harry-styles-dad-tweets-about-birthplace-rumours/|title=Harry Styles' dad tweets about birthplace rumours|work=Bromsgrove Advertiser|date=3 January 2014|publisher=Newsquest Media Group Ltd|access-date=5 July 2021|archive-date=9 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709183355/https://www.bromsgroveadvertiser.co.uk/news/10913305.harry-styles-dad-tweets-about-birthplace-rumours/|url-status=live}}</ref>}}<ref>{{cite news|last=Rogers|first=Jude| author-link = Jude Rogers |title=Harry Styles: teen star turned serious player?|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/may/13/harry-styles-debut-solo-album-one-direction-observer-profile|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|access-date=24 October 2017|date=14 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024095518/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/may/13/harry-styles-debut-solo-album-one-direction-observer-profile|archive-date=24 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> the son of pub owner<ref>{{cite news|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709182625/https://www.warringtonguardian.co.uk/news/5248288.cheers-to-the-future/|url=https://www.warringtonguardian.co.uk/news/5248288.cheers-to-the-future/|title=Cheers to the Future|work=Washington Guardian|date=9 April 2003|archive-date=9 July 2021}}</ref> Anne Twist (''née'' Selley) and finance worker Desmond "Des" Styles.<ref name=EPOMJepson/><ref name="rolling stone">{{Cite magazine |last=Crowe |first=Cameron |date=18 April 2017 |title=Harry Styles' New Direction |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/feature/harry-styles-new-direction-119432/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713193059/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-new-direction-119432/ |archive-date=13 July 2018 |access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bagwell|first=Matt|title=Harry Styles Is All Smiles As Best Man At His Mum Anne Cox's Wedding|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/06/03/harry-styles-one-direction-mum-anne-cox-wedding-pictures_n_3376751.html|website=[[HuffPost]]|access-date=24 October 2017|date=3 June 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024100257/http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/06/03/harry-styles-one-direction-mum-anne-cox-wedding-pictures_n_3376751.html|archive-date=24 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> When he was a child, he moved with his parents and older sister, Gemma, to the village of [[Holmes Chapel]] in [[Cheshire]].<ref name=EPOMJepson>{{cite book|last=Jepson|first=Louisa|title=Harry Styles – Every Piece of Me|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4XzgWkBeNUoC&q=harry%20styles%20birth&pg=PR1|access-date=8 April 2018|year=2013|publisher=[[Simon & Schuster]]|isbn=9781471128479|archive-date=1 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101050617/https://books.google.com/books?id=4XzgWkBeNUoC&q=harry+styles+birth&pg=PR1|url-status=live}}</ref> His parents divorced when he was seven years old. His mother later married business partner John Cox,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.warringtonguardian.co.uk/news/5248288.cheers-to-the-future/|title=Cheers to the future|work=Warrington Guardian|date=9 April 2003|publisher=Newsquest|access-date=5 July 2021|archive-date=9 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709182625/https://www.warringtonguardian.co.uk/news/5248288.cheers-to-the-future/|url-status=live}}</ref> although they divorced years later. Through her subsequent marriage in 2013 to Robin Twist, who died of cancer in 2017, Styles gained an older stepbrother Mike, and a stepsister, Amy.<ref name="Robin Twist">{{cite web |author1=Newsbeat |date=22 June 2017 |title=Harry Styles' stepfather Robin Twist dies aged 57 after 'long cancer battle' |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/40368012/harry-styles-stepfather-robin-twist-dies-aged-57-after-long-cancer-battle |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180114144227/http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/40368012/harry-styles-stepfather-robin-twist-dies-aged-57-after-long-cancer-battle |archive-date=14 January 2018 |access-date=24 October 2017 |website=[[Newsbeat]] |publisher=BBC}}</ref>

Styles said he experienced a "great childhood" and always felt supported by his parents.<ref name="rolling stone" /> As a child, he sang covers on a [[karaoke machine]] he was given by his grandfather, and the first song he recorded was [[Elvis Presley]]'s "[[The Girl of My Best Friend]]."<ref>{{cite news|last=Finn|first=Natalie|url=https://www.eonline.com/uk/news/1010613/25-essential-things-you-should-know-about-harry-styles|title=25 Essential Things You Should Know About Harry Styles|publisher=[[E!]]|date=1 February 2019|access-date=23 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223192621/https://www.eonline.com/uk/news/1010613/25-essential-things-you-should-know-about-harry-styles|archive-date=23 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles attended the [[Holmes Chapel Comprehensive School]],<ref name="Crewe Chronicle">{{cite news|first=Belinda|last=Ryan|date=29 September 2010|url=http://www.crewechronicle.co.uk/news/local-news/holmes-chapel-x-factor-star-5613573|title=Holmes Chapel X Factor star Harry Styles can win show say school bandmates|work=[[Crewe Chronicle]]|publisher=[[Reach plc]]|access-date=10 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921041745/http://www.crewechronicle.co.uk/news/local-news/holmes-chapel-x-factor-star-5613573|archive-date=21 September 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> where he was the lead singer for the band White Eskimo, which won a local Battle of the Bands competition.<ref name="Crewe Chronicle" /><ref name="BBC" /> At the age of 16, he worked part-time at the W. Mandeville Bakery in Holmes Chapel.<ref name="BBC">{{cite news|first=Kate|last=Simms|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/local/stoke/hi/people_and_places/music/newsid_9195000/9195671.stm|title=Harry Styles has got the X Factor in Holmes Chapel|publisher=[[BBC News]]|date=17 November 2010|access-date=10 September 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921061453/http://news.bbc.co.uk/local/stoke/hi/people_and_places/music/newsid_9195000/9195671.stm|archive-date=21 September 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles also worked a paper round in the local village<ref>{{Cite web |last=AnotherMan |date=1 February 2018 |title=Gemma Styles on Growing Up With Her Brother |url=https://www.anothermanmag.com/life-culture/10171/gemma-styles-on-growing-up-with-her-brother |access-date=13 May 2024 |website=AnotherMan}}</ref> and at a stable mucking out horses during his adolescence.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lcKRMkIi2bE |title=What Did Harry Styles Do Before He Was Famous? |date=26 November 2014 |access-date=13 May 2024 |via=YouTube}}</ref>

==Career==
{{see also|List of awards and nominations received by Harry Styles|List of awards and nominations received by One Direction}}

===2010–2015: ''The X Factor'' and One Direction===
{{Main|One Direction}}

[[File:One Direction X Factor Live Glasgow.jpg|thumb|left|Styles (left) with One Direction on ''The X Factor'' Live Tour in 2011]]
Following a suggestion from his mother, on 11 April 2010, Styles auditioned as a solo contestant for the [[The X Factor (UK series 7)|seventh series]] of the British televised singing competition ''[[The X Factor (UK)|The X Factor]]'', singing a rendition of [[Train (band)|Train]]'s "[[Hey, Soul Sister]]." After [[Simon Cowell]] suggested that the track was not right for him, he instead sang a rendition of [[Stevie Wonder]]'s "[[Isn't She Lovely]]."<ref name="rolling stone" /><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Blistein|first=Jon|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-x-factor-audition-extended-cut-1391140/|title=Harry Styles' Full 'X Factor' Audition Included a Train Song, Bakery Banter With Simon Cowell|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=1 August 2022|access-date=13 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220813102947/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-x-factor-audition-extended-cut-1391140/|archive-date=13 August 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> He advanced to bootcamp but failed to progress further. Four others in his age group who were also eliminated were put together to form a boy band in July 2010 to compete in the "Groups" category, mentored by Cowell.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Bootcamp 2|series=[[The X Factor (UK TV series)|The X Factor]]|network=[[ITV plc]]|station=[[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]|air-date=26 September 2010|series-no=7|number=8 }}</ref> The group consisting of Styles, [[Niall Horan]], [[Liam Payne]], [[Louis Tomlinson]], and [[Zayn Malik]] practised for two weeks;<ref>{{cite news|first1=Stan|last1=Walker|first2=Short|last2=Stack|first3=Michael|last3=Paynter|first4=Amy|last4=Meredith|url=http://www.thehothits.com/artists/6069/one-direction/bio|title=One Direction Biography|work=[[The Hot Hits Live from LA]]|publisher=MCM Media|access-date=27 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327221234/http://www.thehothits.com/artists/6069/one-direction/bio|archive-date=27 March 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=South Wales Echo|website=WalesOnline|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/showbiz-and-lifestyle/showbiz/2012/01/13/one-direction-prepare-for-cardiff-sell-out-shows-91466-30112196/|title=One Direction prepare for Cardiff sell-out shows|publisher=[[Media Wales]]|date=13 January 2012|access-date=6 June 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126001640/http://www.walesonline.co.uk/showbiz-and-lifestyle/showbiz/2012/01/13/one-direction-prepare-for-cardiff-sell-out-shows-91466-30112196/|archive-date=26 January 2012}}</ref> Styles suggested the name One Direction to his colleagues which they agreed to.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/harry-styles-reveals-came-name-one-direction-2150976|title=Harry Styles reveals he came up with the name for One Direction|work=[[NME]]|publisher=[[TI Media]]|first=Lisa|last=Bowman|date=17 October 2017|access-date=5 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107021253/http://www.nme.com/news/music/harry-styles-reveals-came-name-one-direction-2150976|archive-date=7 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> They began to gain considerable popularity in the UK,<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Andy|last=Greene|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/exclusive-qa-simon-cowell-on-one-directions-rise-to-stardom-77999/|title=Exclusive Q&A: Simon Cowell on One Direction's Rise to Stardom|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=9 April 2012|access-date=11 May 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180723212519/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/exclusive-qa-simon-cowell-on-one-directions-rise-to-stardom-77999/|archive-date=23 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and within the first four weeks of the live shows, were Cowell's last act in the competition.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.cnn.com/2012/04/09/showbiz/music/simon-cowell-one-direction-rs/index.html|title=Simon Cowell on One Direction's rise to stardom|first=Andy|last=Greene|magazine=Rolling Stone|via=CNN|date=9 April 2012|access-date=20 April 2020|archive-date=18 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018182518/http://www.cnn.com/2012/04/09/showbiz/music/simon-cowell-one-direction-rs/index.html|url-status=live}}</ref> The group eventually reached the final of ''The X Factor'' and finished in third place.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/dec/10/xfactor-final-results-liveblog|title=The X Factor 2010 final results show|work=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|date=12 December 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|first=Stuart|last=Heritage|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922202708/http://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2010/dec/10/xfactor-final-results-liveblog|archive-date=22 September 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:HarryStyles2013-corte2.png|thumb|right|upright=0.7|Styles during the [[Take Me Home Tour (One Direction)|Take Me Home Tour]] in 2013]]
In January 2011, One Direction signed a recording contract with Cowell's label [[Syco Music|Syco Records]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Nicholson|first=Rebecca|title=Also-rans to world's biggest boy band: the rise of One Direction|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/17/one-direction-biggest-band-world|website=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|access-date=16 October 2017|date=17 November 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017043302/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/nov/17/one-direction-biggest-band-world|archive-date=17 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Mayer|last=Nissim|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/the-x-factor/news/a300729/one-direction-get-2m-syco-investment/|title=One Direction 'get £2m Syco investment'|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Communications]]|date=28 January 2011|access-date=23 October 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224001454/http://www.digitalspy.com/music/the-x-factor/news/a300729/one-direction-get-2m-syco-investment/|archive-date=24 December 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Their [[List of UK Singles Chart number ones of the 2010s|UK number one]] debut single, "[[What Makes You Beautiful]]," and their debut studio album, ''[[Up All Night (One Direction album)|Up All Night]]'', were released later that year.<ref>{{cite news|first=Alan|last=Jones|url=http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=22&storycode=1046622|title=What Makes You Beautiful becomes fastest seller of the year|work=[[Music Week]]|publisher=Intent Media|date=19 September 2011|access-date=5 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120116085928/http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?sectioncode=22&storycode=1046622|archive-date=16 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Daniels|first=Colin|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/music/a345784/one-direction-name-debut-album-up-all-night-reveal-cover/|title=One Direction name debut album 'Up All Night', reveal cover|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=16 October 2011|access-date=9 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309141751/https://www.digitalspy.com/music/a345784/one-direction-name-debut-album-up-all-night-reveal-cover/|archive-date=9 March 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> The album, which contained three songs co-written by Styles, debuted at number one in the United States.<ref name=notes>{{cite AV media notes |title=Up All Night |date=2011 |type=liner notes |publisher=[[Syco Music]], [[Sony Music Entertainment]]}} One Direction</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|first=Keith|last= Caulfield|title=One Direction Makes History With No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/499420/one-direction-makes-history-with-no-1-debut-on-billboard-200|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=20 March 2012|access-date=29 June 2024|archive-date=14 February 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130214140936/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/499420/one-direction-makes-history-with-no-1-debut-on-billboard-200|url-status=live}}</ref> Their four succeeding studio albums—''[[Take Me Home (One Direction album)|Take Me Home]]'' (2012), ''[[Midnight Memories]]'' (2013), ''[[Four (One Direction album)|Four]]'' (2014) and ''[[Made in the A.M.]]'' (2015)—all debuted at number one in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|author=Dan Lane|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-number-1-single-and-album-__2564/ |title=One Direction score number 1 single and album!|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=18 November 2012|access-date=9 March 2021|location=United Kingdom|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309011817/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-number-1-single-and-album-__2564/|archive-date=9 March 2021|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-fastest-selling-album-of-their-career-with-midnigh__3580/|title=One Direction score fastest selling album of their career with Midnight Memories|last=Lane|first=Daniel|date=1 December 2013|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=9 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309012044/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-score-fastest-selling-album-of-their-career-with-midnigh__3580/|archive-date=9 March 2021|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|last=Myers|first=Justin|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/four-scores-one-direction-a-third-consecutive-official-albums-chart-number-1__7285/|title=Four scores One Direction a third consecutive Number 1 album|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=23 November 2014|access-date=9 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309012455/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/four-scores-one-direction-a-third-consecutive-official-albums-chart-number-1__7285/|archive-date=9 March 2021|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-vs-justin-bieber-how-this-weeks-album-chart-race-was-won__12061/|title=One Direction vs Justin Bieber: How this week's album chart race was won|last=Talbot|first=Martin|date=20 November 2015|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=20 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309012624/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-vs-justin-bieber-how-this-weeks-album-chart-race-was-won__12061/|archive-date=9 March 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Midnight Memories'' was the world's best-selling album of 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bpi.co.uk/home/one-direction-claim-the-worlds-biggest-selling-album-of-2013.aspx|title=One Direction claim the world's biggest selling album of 2013|publisher=The British Recorded Music Industry|access-date=30 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140518073935/https://www.bpi.co.uk/home/one-direction-claim-the-worlds-biggest-selling-album-of-2013.aspx|archive-date=18 May 2014}}</ref> and its accompanying [[Where We Are Tour (One Direction)|Where We Are Tour]] was the highest-grossing tour of 2014.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2015/03/24/these-were-the-10-highest-grossing-tours-of-2014/#673c117c3643 | title=These Were the 10 Highest-Grossing Tours of 2014 | website=[[Forbes]] | access-date=20 July 2019 | archive-date=18 July 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718234838/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2015/03/24/these-were-the-10-highest-grossing-tours-of-2014/#673c117c3643 | url-status=live }}</ref> After the release of ''Four'', One Direction became the only group in the 58-year history of the [[Billboard Hot 200|''Billboard'' 200]] albums chart to have their first four albums debut at number one.<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Caufield|first1=Keith|title=One Direction's 'Four' Makes Historic No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6327789/one-direction-four-no-1-debut-billboard-200|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=20 October 2015|archive-date=27 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141127143625/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6327789/one-direction-four-no-1-debut-billboard-200|url-status=live}}</ref> The albums spawned a string of successful singles, including "[[Live While We're Young]]," "[[Little Things (One Direction song)|Little Things]]," "[[Best Song Ever]]," "[[Story of My Life (One Direction song)|Story of My Life]]," "[[Drag Me Down]]" and "[[History (One Direction song)|History]]."<ref>{{cite web|title=One Direction's Official Top 10 Biggest Selling Singles Revealed!|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-s-official-top-10-biggest-selling-singles-revealed-__7226/|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=15 September 2018|date=25 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150829090736/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/one-direction-s-official-top-10-biggest-selling-singles-revealed-__7226/|archive-date=29 August 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="1D sales">{{cite magazine|last=Trust|first=Gary|title=Ask Billboard: One Direction's Career Sales|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7408939/ask-billboard-one-directions-career-sales|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=15 September 2018|date=19 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627151555/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7408939/ask-billboard-one-directions-career-sales|archive-date=27 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Copsey|first=Rob|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/ten-years-of-one-direction-10-chart-facts-you-probably-didnt-know-about-one-of-the-uks-most-loved-boybands__30301/|title=Ten years of One Direction: 10 chart facts you probably didn't know about one of the UK's most loved boybands|publisher=Official Charts Company|date=23 July 2020|access-date=9 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116044942/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/ten-years-of-one-direction-10-chart-facts-you-probably-didnt-know-about-one-of-the-uks-most-loved-boybands__30301/|archive-date=16 January 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles also co-wrote the song "Just a Little Bit of Your Heart" for [[Ariana Grande]]'s 2014 album ''[[My Everything (Ariana Grande album)|My Everything]]''.<ref>{{cite AV media notes |title=My Everything |date=2014 |type=liner notes |publisher=[[Republic Records]] ([[Universal Music Group]])}} Ariana Grande</ref>

Not wanting to "exhaust" the fan base, upon Styles' suggestion, One Direction went on an indefinite hiatus in 2016, after completing promotional activities related to ''Made in the A.M''.<ref name="rolling stone" /><ref>{{cite web|first1=Melanie|last1=Bromley|first2=Mike|last2=Vulpo|title=One Direction Taking Extended Hiatus to Focus on Individual Projects—Are They Breaking Up for Good?|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/689033/one-direction-taking-extended-hiatus-to-focus-on-individual-projects-are-they-breaking-up-for-good|website=[[E!]]|access-date=17 September 2018|date=23 August 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180917105347/https://www.eonline.com/news/689033/one-direction-taking-extended-hiatus-to-focus-on-individual-projects-are-they-breaking-up-for-good|archive-date=17 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Savage|first=Mark|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-52283104|title=One Direction are speaking about anniversary reunion, Liam Payne says|publisher=BBC News|date=14 April 2020|access-date=9 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309141113/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-52283104|archive-date=9 March 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> Since their debut, One Direction have sold 70 million records worldwide, including 7.6 million albums and 26 million singles in the US, becoming one of the [[List of best-selling boy groups|best-selling boy bands of all time]].<ref name="1D sales" /><ref>{{cite magazine|first1=Jason|last1=Lipshutz|first2=Keith|last2=Caulfield|title=23 Million Songs, 6 Million Albums & More: One Direction With Zayn Malik, By The Numbers|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6509669/one-direction-zayn-malik-by-the-numbers|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=15 September 2018|date=25 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919224216/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6509669/one-direction-zayn-malik-by-the-numbers|archive-date=19 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/53447792|title=One Direction: Ten years of 1D, but is a reunion on the way?|work=[[BBC]]|date=21 July 2020|access-date=1 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001160423/https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/53447792|archive-date=1 October 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The group amassed [[List of awards and nominations received by One Direction|numerous accolades]], including seven [[Brit Awards]],<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7701365/one-direction-zayn-malik-video-of-the-year-2017-brit-awards|title=One Direction Beats Out Zayn Malik for Video of the Year at 2017 Brit Awards|last=Weatherby|first=Taylor|date=22 February 2017|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=24 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180825022717/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7701365/one-direction-zayn-malik-video-of-the-year-2017-brit-awards|archive-date=25 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> seven [[American Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theamas.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|title=Winners Database|website=[[American Music Awards]]|publisher=[[Dick Clark Productions]]|access-date=24 August 2018|archive-date=6 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106023032/https://www.theamas.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|url-status=live}}</ref> six [[Billboard Music Award|''Billboard'' Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboardmusicawards.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|title=Winners Database|website=[[Billboard Music Award]]s|publisher=[[Dick Clark Productions]]|access-date=24 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180913075843/https://www.billboardmusicawards.com/winners-database/?winnerKeyword=one+direction&winnerYear=&winnerCategory=|archive-date=13 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and four [[MTV Video Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1713022/one-direction-vma-2013-song-of-the-summer/|title=One Direction: Eight Million Votes Prove The Boys Own 'Song Of The Summer'|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|date=25 August 2013|website=[[MTV News]]|access-date=24 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180825002551/http://www.mtv.com/news/1713022/one-direction-vma-2013-song-of-the-summer/|archive-date=25 August 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> While Styles has been generally positive about his time in One Direction, he has revealed that the hyper-visibility he experienced while being in the band was not always easy to deal with.<ref name="ls" /> Styles attributed his avoidance of social media to past pressure that he should be constantly accessible online.<ref name="ls" /><ref>{{cite web |last=Magazine |first=i-D. |date=27 December 2019 |title=timothée chalamet in conversation with harry styles: the hottest actor on the planet interviewed by music's most charismatic popstar |url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/evwwma/timothee-chalamet-in-conversation-with-harry-styles-the-hottest-actor-on-the-planet-interviewed-by-musics-most-charismatic-popstar |access-date=1 July 2022 |website=i-D |language=en |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701131140/https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/evwwma/timothee-chalamet-in-conversation-with-harry-styles-the-hottest-actor-on-the-planet-interviewed-by-musics-most-charismatic-popstar |url-status=live }}</ref> He has spoken about being scared of saying the wrong things in interviews and of fear that not answering questions such as the number of people he slept with would cause journalists to leave the interview annoyed with him.<ref name="ls" /> His contracts with One Direction contained "cleanliness clauses" which stated that the group would be "null and void" if he did not obey them[...].<ref name="ls" /> He expressed that he "burst into tears" when he signed a solo contract without these clauses because he felt "free."<ref name="ls" />

===2016–2018: ''Harry Styles'' and ''Dunkirk''===

As a solo artist, Styles joined Jeffrey Azoff's Full Stop Management and talent agency [[Creative Artists Agency|CAA]], signing a recording contract with [[Columbia Records]] in the first half of 2016.<ref name="Columbia">{{cite magazine|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|title=Harry Styles Signs Recording Contract With Columbia: Exclusive|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7416429/harry-styles-solo-record-deal-one-direction|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=23 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019111119/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7416429/harry-styles-solo-record-deal-one-direction|archive-date=19 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ingham|first=Tim|title=Harry Styles has launched his own independent label – Erskine Records|url=https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/harry-styles-launched-independent-label-erskine-records/|website=Music Business Worldwide|access-date=23 December 2017|date=9 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612162140/https://www.musicbusinessworldwide.com/harry-styles-launched-independent-label-erskine-records/|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Around this time, he also launched his own record label, [[Erskine Records]].<ref name="Columbia"/> Recording for Styles' debut album occurred throughout 2016 in Los Angeles, London and [[Port Antonio, Jamaica]], where Styles and his collaborators spent a two-month writing retreat in the autumn.<ref name="rolling stone" /> In March 2017, he announced that his first solo single, "[[Sign of the Times (Harry Styles song)|Sign of the Times]]," would be released on 7 April.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Tom|first=Lauren|title=Harry Styles Debuts Cover Art for First Solo Single, 'Sign of the Times'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7744377/harry-styles-solo-single-cover-art-sign-of-the-times|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=31 March 2017|access-date=3 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170403070610/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7744377/harry-styles-solo-single-cover-art-sign-of-the-times|archive-date=3 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The song peaked at number one on the UK Singles Chart and number four on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/official-charts-analysis-harry-styles-ends-ed-sheeran-s-reign-as-no-1-single/068162|title=Official Charts Analysis: Harry Styles ends Ed Sheeran's reign as No.1 single|first=Alan|last=Jones|work=[[Music Week]]|publisher=[[NewBay Media]]|date=14 April 2017|access-date=14 April 2017|url-access=subscription|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170416221824/http://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/official-charts-analysis-harry-styles-ends-ed-sheeran-s-reign-as-no-1-single/068162|archive-date=16 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7760569/ed-sheeran-harry-styles-sign-times-hot-100|title=Ed Sheeran Tops Hot 100 for 12th Week, as Harry Styles Starts at No. 4|last=Trust|first=Gary|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=17 April 2017|access-date=18 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170418050143/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7760569/ed-sheeran-harry-styles-sign-times-hot-100|archive-date=18 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> A [[glam rock]]-influenced [[soft rock]] [[Sentimental ballad|power ballad]],<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Smith|first=Da'Shan|title=Here Are The Lyrics To Harry Style's 'Sign Of The Times'|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7752459/harry-styles-sign-of-the-times-lyrics|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=17 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171023233435/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7752459/harry-styles-sign-of-the-times-lyrics|archive-date=23 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wass|first=Mike|title=Harry Styles Takes Flight With 'Sign Of The Times'|url=http://www.idolator.com/7660685/harry-styles-sign-of-the-times-full-song-review|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|publisher=Hive Media|access-date=16 October 2017|date=7 April 2017|archive-date=13 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170613195956/http://www.idolator.com/7660685/harry-styles-sign-of-the-times-full-song-review|url-status=live}}</ref> it drew comparisons to the work of [[David Bowie]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=Relaxnews|title=Harry Styles channels glam rock in post-One Direction debut|url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/harry-styles-channels-glam-rock-in-post-one-direction-debut-1.3358871|publisher=[[CTV News]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=7 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620102544/http://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/harry-styles-channels-glam-rock-in-post-one-direction-debut-1.3358871|archive-date=20 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' ranked "Sign of the Times" as the best song of 2017.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-songs-of-2017-116129/|title=50 Best Songs of 2017|last1=Weingarten|first1=Christopher R.|last2=Spanos|first2=Brittany|date=29 November 2017|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=30 November 2017|last3=Aaron|first3=Charles|last4=Vozick-Levinson|first4=Simon|last5=Sheffield|first5=Rob|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180915155223/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-songs-of-2017-116129/|archive-date=15 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Its music video featured Styles flying and walking on water<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tiffany|first1=Kaitlyn|last2=Plaugic|first2=Lizzie|last3=Jennings|first3=Rebecca|title=One Video: Sign of the Times by Harry Styles|url=https://www.theverge.com/tldr/2017/5/12/15629796/harry-styles-sign-of-the-times-video-watch|website=[[The Verge]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|access-date=7 November 2017|date=12 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107165151/https://www.theverge.com/tldr/2017/5/12/15629796/harry-styles-sign-of-the-times-video-watch|archive-date=7 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=McDermott|first=Maeve|title=Harry Styles drops Jesus-like music video for 'Sign of the Times'|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/05/08/sign-of-the-times-harry-styles-drops-jesus-like-music-video/101424804/|website=[[USA Today]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=8 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817100013/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2017/05/08/sign-of-the-times-harry-styles-drops-jesus-like-music-video/101424804/|archive-date=17 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> and won the [[Brit Award for British Video of the Year]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/feb/22/full-list-of-winners-at-the-2018-brit-awards|title=Full list of winners at the 2018 Brit awards|last=Beaumont-Thomas|first=Ben|date=22 February 2018|work=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|access-date=19 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180322112059/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/feb/22/full-list-of-winners-at-the-2018-brit-awards|archive-date=22 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In April, Styles was a musical guest on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' in the US and made his debut televised solo performance in the UK on ''[[The Graham Norton Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ungerman|first=Alex|title=Harry Styles Officially Goes Solo, Shares Single Art and Release Date Ahead of 'SNL' Performance|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/harry-styles-officially-goes-solo-231300860.html|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|date=1 April 2017|access-date=3 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612162848/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/harry-styles-officially-goes-solo-231300860.html|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Harp|first=Justin|title=Harry Styles is making his solo UK debut on The Graham Norton Show|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/graham-norton-show/news/a825204/harry-styles-making-uk-debut-on-graham-norton-show/|website=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Communications]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=5 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808000026/http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/graham-norton-show/news/a825204/harry-styles-making-uk-debut-on-graham-norton-show/|archive-date=8 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>
[[File:180612 Harry Styles Live On Tour in Nashville.png|thumb|left|upright|Styles performing in [[Nashville, Tennessee]] in 2018]]
His [[Harry Styles (album)|self-titled debut album]] was released in May 2017,<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Kaufman|first=Gil|title=Harry Styles Self-Titled Debut Due May 12, Check Out Tracklist|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7760233/harry-styles-self-titled-debut-may-12-tracklist|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=13 April 2017|access-date=13 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623084612/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7760233/harry-styles-self-titled-debut-may-12-tracklist|archive-date=23 June 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> whereupon it debuted at number one in several countries, including Australia, the UK and the US.<ref>{{cite web|last=White|first=Jack|title=How Harry Styles' debut album has performed in the charts across the world|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/how-harry-styles-debut-album-has-performed-in-the-charts-across-the-world__19250/|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=24 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017043437/http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/how-harry-styles-debut-album-has-performed-in-the-charts-across-the-world__19250/|archive-date=17 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The record was influenced by 1970s soft rock and was described by ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' as a "classic cocktail of psychedelia, Britpop, and balladry."<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-39883061|title=Is Harry Styles' album worth the wait?|last=Savage|first=Mark|work=[[BBC News]]|date=12 May 2017|access-date=21 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517072220/http://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-39883061|archive-date=17 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Britpop">{{cite web|last=Barlow|first=Eve|title=Harry Styles' Solo Album: A Track-by-Track Breakdown|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/harry-styles-solo-album-track-breakdown-1202424544/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=17 October 2017|date=12 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016230818/http://variety.com/2017/music/news/harry-styles-solo-album-track-breakdown-1202424544/|archive-date=16 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> It received generally favourable reviews from critics<ref>{{cite web|title=Harry Styles by Harry Styles Reviews and Tracks|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/harry-styles/harry-styles|website=[[Metacritic]]|access-date=20 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170724024059/http://www.metacritic.com/music/harry-styles/harry-styles|archive-date=24 July 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/grammy-nominations-seven-surprises-jay-z-taylor-swift-harry-styles-1202624281/|title=Grammy Nominations: 7 Biggest Snubs and Surprises|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Jem|last=Aswad|date=28 November 2017|access-date=13 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180114183911/http://variety.com/2017/music/news/grammy-nominations-seven-surprises-jay-z-taylor-swift-harry-styles-1202624281/|archive-date=14 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and was included in several publications' lists of the best albums of 2017.<ref>{{cite magazine|first1=Christopher R. |last1=Weingarten |first2=Jon |last2=Dolan |first3=Hank |last3=Shteamer |first4=Brittany |last4=Spanos |first5=Suzy |last5=Exposito |first6=Joseph |last6=Hudak |first7=Simon |last7=Vozick-Levinson |first8=Keith |last8=Harris |first9=Maura |last9=Johnston |author9-link=Maura Johnston |first10=Joe |last10=Levy |first11=Will |last11=Hermes |first12=Rob |last12=Sheffield |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-albums-of-2017-123296/harry-styles-harry-styles-124121/|title=50 Best Albums of 2017|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=27 November 2017|access-date=13 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824135142/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/50-best-albums-of-2017-123296/harry-styles-harry-styles-124121/|archive-date=24 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8062834/billboard-50-best-albums-of-2017-critics-picks|title=Billboard's 50 Best Albums of 2017: Critics' Picks|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=12 December 2017|access-date=12 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171213032834/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8062834/billboard-50-best-albums-of-2017-critics-picks|archive-date=13 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://time.com/5034987/best-albums-2017/|first=Raisa|last=Bruner|title=The Top 10 Albums of 2017|date=4 December 2017|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|access-date=6 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171204200739/http://time.com/5034987/best-albums-2017/|archive-date=4 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Harry Styles'' yielded two more singles, "[[Two Ghosts]]" and "[[Kiwi (song)|Kiwi]]."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|date=11 July 2017|access-date=12 July 2017|publisher=All Access Music Group|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170807093548/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archive-date=7 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Prance|first=Sam|title=Harry Styles Releases Brilliant 'Kiwi' Video|url=https://www.mtv.co.uk/news/2naacs/harry-styles-releases-brilliant-kiwi-music-video|publisher=[[MTV (UK and Ireland)|MTV]]|access-date=8 November 2017|date=8 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108205519/http://www.mtv.co.uk/harry-styles/news/harry-styles-releases-brilliant-kiwi-music-video|archive-date=8 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The film ''Harry Styles: Behind the Album'', which documented the writing and recording process for the album, was released in May exclusively on [[Apple Music]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Harry Styles Drops Unplugged Video for 'Two Ghosts'|url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/harry-styles-drops-unplugged-video-for-two-ghosts-1202543885/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=6 November 2017|date=31 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107010221/http://variety.com/2017/music/news/harry-styles-drops-unplugged-video-for-two-ghosts-1202543885/|archive-date=7 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles embarked on his first headlining concert tour, [[Harry Styles: Live on Tour]], from September 2017 through to July 2018, performing in North and South Americas, Europe, Asia, and Australia.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Blistein|first=Jon|title=Harry Styles Plots Extensive 2018 Tour|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-plots-extensive-2018-tour-194858/|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=8 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180912165655/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-plots-extensive-2018-tour-194858/|archive-date=12 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Brooks|first=Dave|title=Harry Styles Sells Out First World Tour in Seconds|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7784890/harry-styles-sells-out-first-world-tour-seconds|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=5 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907071616/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7784890/harry-styles-sells-out-first-world-tour-seconds|archive-date=7 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On tour he debuted two unreleased songs, "Anna" and "[[Medicine (Harry Styles song)|Medicine]]."<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |date=12 March 2018 |title=Harry Styles World Tour Kick Off Includes Debut of Two New Songs, 'Anna' & 'Medicine' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-world-tour-kick-off-new-songs-anna-medicine-8240704/ |access-date=3 July 2022 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |language=en-US |archive-date=18 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818045045/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-world-tour-kick-off-new-songs-anna-medicine-8240704/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Styles made his feature film debut in [[Christopher Nolan]]'s war film ''[[Dunkirk (2017 film)|Dunkirk]]'', in July 2017, playing a British soldier named Alex in the [[Dunkirk evacuation]] during [[World War II]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Jones|first=Nate|title=How Much Is Harry Styles in ''Dunkirk''?|url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/07/does-harry-styles-die-in-dunkirk.html|website=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]]|access-date=16 October 2017|date=20 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017043130/http://www.vulture.com/2017/07/does-harry-styles-die-in-dunkirk.html|archive-date=17 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> He appeared alongside an [[ensemble cast]] which included [[Fionn Whitehead]], [[Tom Glynn-Carney]], [[Jack Lowden]], [[Kenneth Branagh]], [[Cillian Murphy]], [[Mark Rylance]], and [[Tom Hardy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/harry-styles-one-direction-christopher-nolan-dunkirk-1201728153|title=Harry Styles, Fionn Whitehead to Star in Christopher Nolan WW2 Action-Thriller 'Dunkirk'|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=11 March 2016|access-date=7 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504152927/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/harry-styles-one-direction-christopher-nolan-dunkirk-1201728153/|archive-date=4 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles won the part over "thousands of young men;"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mitchell|first1=Bea|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a825628/harry-styles-beat-thousands-actors-christopher-nolan-dunkirk/|title=Harry Styles beat thousands of actors for his role in Christopher Nolan's Dunkirk|website=[[Digital Spy]]|date=10 April 2017|access-date=14 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914115748/https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a825628/harry-styles-beat-thousands-actors-christopher-nolan-dunkirk/|archive-date=14 September 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Nolan later admitted he was unaware of the extent of Styles' fame and that he was cast "because he fit the part wonderfully and truly earned a seat at the table."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Evatt|first1=Nicole|url=https://apnews.com/33ab89b8f73d49eda9a8557c00ba1ba4/Christopher-Nolan-didn't-know-how-famous-Harry-Styles-was|title=Christopher Nolan didn't know how famous Harry Styles was|work=[[Associated Press]]|date=9 July 2020|access-date=14 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914115806/https://apnews.com/33ab89b8f73d49eda9a8557c00ba1ba4/Christopher-Nolan-didn%27t-know-how-famous-Harry-Styles-was|archive-date=14 September 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=''Dunkirk''|first1=Matt|last1=Maytum|first2=Jane|last2=Crowther|magazine=[[Total Film]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|date=Summer 2017|issue=260|pages=56–65}}</ref> ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' film critic [[Robbie Collin]] praised Styles for his "bright, convicted, and unexpectedly not-at-all-jarring performance."<ref>{{cite news|last=Collin|first=Robbie|title=Dunkirk review: heart-hammering and heroically British, this is Christopher Nolan at the peak of his powers|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/0/dunkirk-review-heart-hammering-heroically-british-christopher/|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|location=London|access-date=16 October 2017|date=21 July 2017|archive-url=https://archive.today/20170718155926/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/0/dunkirk-review-heart-hammering-heroically-british-christopher/|archive-date=18 July 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

In November 2017, [[BBC One]] broadcast ''Harry Styles at the BBC'', a one-hour [[television special]] presented by [[Nick Grimshaw]].<ref>{{cite web|author1=BBC|title=Harry Styles At The BBC to hit BBC One this autumn|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2017/harry-styles-at-the-bbc|work=[[BBC Online]]|access-date=23 October 2017|date=21 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026025517/http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediacentre/latestnews/2017/harry-styles-at-the-bbc|archive-date=26 October 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that month, he performed at the [[Victoria's Secret Fashion Show]] held in [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-victorias-secret-fashion-show-shanghai-lingerie-runway | title=Harry Styles Stole the Show on the Victoria's Secret Runway | last=Ward |first=Maria |work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |date=20 November 2017 |access-date=20 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220326152716/https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-victorias-secret-fashion-show-shanghai-lingerie-runway|archive-date=26 March 2022 |url-status=live }}</ref> At [[ARIA Music Awards of 2017|2017 ARIA Music Awards]], Styles received the [[ARIA Award for Best International Artist|Best International Artist]] award.<ref>{{cite web |author1=[[ARIA]] |title=ARIA Awards |url=https://www.ariaawards.com.au/news/2017/and-the-aria-award-goes-to |publisher=[[ARIA Music Awards]] |access-date=19 August 2018 |date=28 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180819083051/https://www.ariaawards.com.au/news/2017/and-the-aria-award-goes-to |archive-date=19 August 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> He guest-hosted ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]'' in December.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hill|first=Libby|title=Harry Styles emergency hosts 'Late Late Show' when James Corden's wife gives birth|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-et-entertainment-news-updates-harry-styles-emergency-hosts-late-late-1513178935-htmlstory.html|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|access-date=3 March 2018|date=13 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180304172452/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-et-entertainment-news-updates-harry-styles-emergency-hosts-late-late-1513178935-htmlstory.html|archive-date=4 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Together with [[Jack Antonoff]] and [[Ilsey Juber]], Styles cowrote "Alfie's Song (Not So Typical Love Song)," performed by the band [[Bleachers (band)|Bleachers]], for the soundtrack of the film ''[[Love, Simon]]'' (2018).<ref>{{cite web|last=Hosken|first=Patrick|title=Khalid Calls Normani 'Unmatchable' Ahead Of Their Love, Simon Collab|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3061657/khalid-normani-love-simon-love-lies/|publisher=[[MTV News]]|access-date=24 March 2018|date=29 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180322142103/http://www.mtv.com/news/3061657/khalid-normani-love-simon-love-lies/|archive-date=22 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> He also served as an executive producer on the [[CBS]] [[sitcom]] ''[[Happy Together (U.S. TV series)|Happy Together]]'', which premiered in October 2018 and was inspired by his time living with television producer [[Ben Winston]] and his wife.<ref>{{cite news|last=Yahr|first=Emily|title=Yes, Harry Styles (that Harry Styles) will executive-produce a sitcom on CBS this fall|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2018/05/16/yes-harry-styles-that-harry-styles-will-executive-produce-a-sitcom-on-cbs-this-fall/|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|access-date=19 May 2018|date=16 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180806054845/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2018/05/16/yes-harry-styles-that-harry-styles-will-executive-produce-a-sitcom-on-cbs-this-fall/|archive-date=6 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2018, Styles began modelling for the Italian fashion house [[Gucci]], appearing in several campaigns for the brand.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/harry-styles-gucci-tailoring-2019 | title=A Pig, A Swan, A Statue, A Headscarf — Harry Styles's New Gucci Campaign Is Even More Extra Than The Last | last=Pike |first=Naomi |work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |date=21 May 2019 |access-date=21 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190528201121/https://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/harry-styles-gucci-tailoring-2019|archive-date=28 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/gucci-memoire-campaign | title=Alongside Harry Styles, Three Faces Of Gucci's New Campaign Discuss Its Hopeful Message | last=Pike |first=Naomi |work=[[British Vogue]] |date=1 August 2019 |access-date=1 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190806071253/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/gucci-memoire-campaign |archive-date=6 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===2019–2021: ''Fine Line''===
In July 2019, it was reported that Styles was in early talks to play [[List of The Little Mermaid characters#Prince Eric|Prince Eric]] in the live-action Disney film, ''[[The Little Mermaid (2023 film)|The Little Mermaid]]'' (2023).<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kit |first=Borys |date=16 July 2019 |title=Harry Styles in Talks to Play Prince Eric in Disney's Live-Action 'Little Mermaid' |work=The Hollywood Reporter |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/harry-styles-talks-play-prince-eric-disneys-little-mermaid-1224669 |url-status=live |access-date=16 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716200249/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/harry-styles-talks-play-prince-eric-disneys-little-mermaid-1224669 |archive-date=16 July 2019}}</ref> However, he ultimately turned the part down for various reasons which included touring and wanting to pursue darker, non-musical roles.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gonzales |first=Umberto |date=13 August 2019 |title=Harry Styles Turns Down Role of Prince Eric in 'Little Mermaid' (Exclusive) |work=[[TheWrap]] |url=https://www.thewrap.com/harry-styles-little-mermaid-prince-eric/ |url-status=live |access-date=14 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814031640/https://www.thewrap.com/harry-styles-little-mermaid-prince-eric/ |archive-date=14 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Harrison |first=Ellie |date=4 November 2019 |title=Harry Styles reveals why he turned down role of Prince Eric in Little Mermaid |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/harry-styles-little-mermaid-prince-eric-reject-role-a9183981.html |url-status=live |magazine=[[The Independent]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220820034829/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/harry-styles-little-mermaid-prince-eric-reject-role-a9183981.html |archive-date=20 August 2022 |access-date=27 May 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Romano |first=Nick |date=4 April 2023 |title=Making a splash: A deep dive into the live-action Little Mermaid with a new generation's Ariel |url=https://ew.com/movies/the-little-mermaid-halle-bailey-melissa-mccarthy-cover-story/ |url-status=live |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404180704/https://ew.com/movies/the-little-mermaid-halle-bailey-melissa-mccarthy-cover-story/ |archive-date=4 April 2023 |access-date=4 April 2023}}</ref> The part ultimately went to [[Jonah Hauer-King]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=12 November 2019 |title='Little Mermaid' Live-Action Remake Finds Its Prince Eric in Jonah Hauer-King |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/little-mermaid-live-action-remake-finds-prince-eric-jonah-hauer-king-1254375 |url-status=live |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113030958/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/little-mermaid-live-action-remake-finds-prince-eric-jonah-hauer-king-1254375 |archive-date=13 November 2019 |access-date=13 November 2019}}</ref> "[[Lights Up]]," the lead single from Styles' second album, ''[[Fine Line (Harry Styles album)|Fine Line]]'', was released in October 2019, debuting at number three in the UK.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Pace|first=Lilly|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8542507/harry-styles-announces-new-album-fine-line|title=Harry Styles Just Announced His Sophomore Album ''Fine Line'' and Nothing Else Matters|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=4 November 2019|access-date=10 November 2019|archive-date=6 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191106015047/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8542507/harry-styles-announces-new-album-fine-line|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 (18 October 2019 – 24 October 2019) |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20191018/7501/ |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |access-date=11 January 2020 |archive-date=18 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191018152354/https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20191018/7501/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The song featured a "soft-touch re-entry into the pop slipstream," according to music writer [[Jon Caramanica]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Caramanica |first1=Jon |title=The Playlist: Harry Styles's Lite Rock Return, and 10 More New Songs |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/11/arts/music/playlist-harry-styles-city-girls-liz-phair.html |website=[[The New York Times]] |url-access=limited |access-date=14 October 2019 |date=11 October 2019 |archive-date=13 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013185113/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/11/arts/music/playlist-harry-styles-city-girls-liz-phair.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Styles served as both host and musical guest on ''Saturday Night Live'' in November.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Spanos |first1=Brittany |title=Harry Styles Pulling 'Double Duty' for 'SNL' as Host, Musical Guest |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-saturday-night-live-host-musical-guest-snl-903207/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=24 October 2019 |access-date=26 November 2019 |archive-date=5 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105180211/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-saturday-night-live-host-musical-guest-snl-903207/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The second single preceding ''Fine Line'', "[[Adore You (Harry Styles song)|Adore You]]," was released in December, peaking at number seven in the UK and at number six in the US.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-adore-you-922817/|title=Harry Styles Will Walk Through Fire for Love in New Song 'Adore You'|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=6 December 2019|access-date=13 December 2019|archive-date=7 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207140137/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-adore-you-922817/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/51376/harry-styles/|title=Harry Styles {{!}} Full Official Chart History|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|access-date=12 January 2020|archive-date=15 April 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415011409/http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/51376/harry-styles/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9352114/the-weeknd-blinding-lights-number-one-second-week-hot-1000|title=The Weeknd's 'Blinding Lights' Shines at No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100 For Second Week|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=6 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200615003354/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9340653/roddy-ricch-the-box-harry-styles-adore-you-hot-100|archive-date=15 June 2020|url-status=live|access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref> That month, Styles again guest-hosted ''The Late Late Show with James Corden''.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/television/8545959/harry-styles-late-late-show-guest-host-recap|title=Harry Styles Epically Guest-Hosts 'Late Late Show': Interviews Himself, Performs 'Adore You,' Hits 'Carpool' Lane: Watch|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=20 December 2019|archive-date=19 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219115600/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/television/8545959/harry-styles-late-late-show-guest-host-recap|url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Harry Styles - 9 25 2021 - United Center (52560547868).jpg|thumb|right|upright=1.2|Styles performing at [[United Center]] in [[Chicago]] in 2021]]
''Fine Line'' was released on 13 December. The album was recorded at the [[Shangri-La (recording studio)|Shangri-La]] studio in [[Malibu, California]], with the same production team behind Styles' debut album, and features a similar sound to ''Harry Styles'' while also incorporating elements of funk and soul.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Haylock |first1=Zoe |title=Get Your Bell-Bottoms on, Harry Styles's New Album Is Out! |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/12/listen-harry-styless-new-album-fine-line-is-out-now.html |website=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |access-date=11 January 2020 |date=13 December 2019 |archive-date=13 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213175439/https://www.vulture.com/2019/12/listen-harry-styless-new-album-fine-line-is-out-now.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Mylrea |first1=Hannah |title=Harry Styles – ''Fine Line'' review: packed with personality and charm (and saucy lyrics) |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/harry-styles-fine-line-review-packed-with-personality-and-charm-and-saucy-lyrics-2584779 |website=[[NME]] |access-date=11 January 2020 |date=9 December 2019 |archive-date=9 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209215729/https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/harry-styles-fine-line-review-packed-with-personality-and-charm-and-saucy-lyrics-2584779 |url-status=live }}</ref> It received generally positive reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/fine-line/harry-styles|title=''Fine Line'' by Harry Styles reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|access-date=18 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218115658/https://www.metacritic.com/music/fine-line/harry-styles|archive-date=18 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The album peaked at number two in the UK<ref>{{cite news|last=Copsey|first=Rob|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/taylor-swifts-evermore-reclaims-number-1-on-the-official-albums-chart__32089/|title=Taylor Swift's Evermore reclaims Number 1 on the Official Albums Chart|work=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=8 January 2021|access-date=18 September 2021|archive-date=5 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205174120/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/taylor-swifts-evermore-reclaims-number-1-on-the-official-albums-chart__32089/|url-status=live}}</ref> and topped the US charts, breaking the record as the biggest sales debut from an English male artist in the US since [[Nielsen SoundScan]] began electronically tracking sales data in 1991.<ref name=":0">{{cite magazine |last1=Caulfield |first1=Keith |title=Harry Styles' ''Fine Line'' Album Earns Huge No. 1 Debut on Billboard 200 Chart |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8546971/harry-styles-fine-line-album-no-1-billboard-200-chart |access-date=23 December 2019 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=22 December 2019 |archive-date=19 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200119022457/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8546971/harry-styles-fine-line-album-no-1-billboard-200-chart |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Rolling Stone'' ranked it at number 491 in their 2020 list of the "[[Rolling Stone's 500 Greatest Albums of All Time|500 Greatest Albums of All Time]]."<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-albums-of-all-time-1062063/|title=The 500 Greatest Albums of All Time (2020)|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=22 September 2020|access-date=29 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922163403/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-albums-of-all-time-1062063/|archive-date=22 September 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Five other singles, "[[Falling (Harry Styles song)|Falling]]," "[[Watermelon Sugar]]," "[[Golden (Harry Styles song)|Golden]]," "[[Treat People with Kindness]]" and the title track, were released from the album.<ref>{{cite web|last=Haylock|first=Zoe|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/harry-styles-falling-music-video-watch.html|title=Flood Warning: Harry Styles's 'Falling' Video Will Make You Sob|website=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]]|url-access=limited|date=28 February 2020|access-date=28 June 2020|archive-date=12 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200712084832/https://www.vulture.com/2020/02/harry-styles-falling-music-video-watch.html|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite magazine|last=Angermiller|first=Michele Amabile|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-watermelon-sugar-visual-video-watch-1234609075/|title=Harry Styles Unveils 'Watermelon Sugar' Visual; Cavities Abound|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=18 May 2020|access-date=28 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200621005417/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-watermelon-sugar-visual-video-watch-1234609075/|archive-date=21 June 2020|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite magazine|last=Iasimone|first=Ashley|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9472593/harry-styles-golden-video|title=Harry Styles Is Absolutely 'Golden' in Scenic Music Video: Watch|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=26 October 2020|access-date=27 October 2020|archive-date=1 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101050619/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9472593/harry-styles-golden-video|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/harry-styles-and-phoebe-waller-bridge-dance-up-a-storm-in-treat-people-with-kindness-video-2847257|title=Harry Styles and Phoebe Waller-Bridge dance up a storm in 'Treat People With Kindness' video|date=1 January 2021|access-date=8 January 2021|website=[[NME]]|archive-date=9 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109181331/https://www.nme.com/news/music/harry-styles-and-phoebe-waller-bridge-dance-up-a-storm-in-treat-people-with-kindness-video-2847257|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite web|url=https://radiodate.it/radio-date/harry-styles-fine-line-232783-19-11-2021-radiodate/|title=Harry Styles ''Fine Line'' {{!}} (Radio Date: 19 November 2021)|publisher=[[Sony Music]]|last=Sisti|first=Sara|access-date=12 November 2021|via=Radio Airplay SRL|archive-date=4 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220404224910/https://radiodate.it/radio-date/harry-styles-fine-line-232783-19-11-2021-radiodate/|url-status=live}}</ref> "Watermelon Sugar" became Styles' fourth UK top-ten single, peaking at number four,<ref>{{cite web|last=Copsey|first=Rob|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/joel-corry-and-mneks-head-heart-keeps-number-1-as-billie-eilish-scores-highest-new-entry-on-official-singles-chart__30701/|title=Joel Corry and MNEK's Head & Heart keeps Number 1 as Billie Eilish scores highest new entry on Official Singles Chart|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=7 August 2020|access-date=7 August 2020|archive-date=1 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101050652/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/joel-corry-and-mneks-head-heart-keeps-number-1-as-billie-eilish-scores-highest-new-entry-on-official-singles-chart__30701/|url-status=live}}</ref> as well as his first number-one single in the US.<ref>{{Cite magazine|date=10 August 2020|title=Harry Styles' 'Watermelon Sugar' Surges to Top of Billboard Hot 100, Becoming His First No. 1|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9431815/harry-styles-watermelon-sugar-hot-100|access-date=10 August 2020|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archive-date=15 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815155715/https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9431815/harry-styles-watermelon-sugar-hot-100|url-status=live}}</ref> A tour to support ''Fine Line'', entitled [[Love On Tour]], which was originally set to take place throughout 2020,<ref>{{cite news |last=Melas |first=Chloe |title=Harry Styles announces 2020 tour |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/13/entertainment/harry-styles-2020-tour/index.html |work=[[CNN]] |access-date=13 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191113185412/https://www.cnn.com/2019/11/13/entertainment/harry-styles-2020-tour/index.html |archive-date=13 November 2019 |location=United States |date=13 November 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> was postponed until 2021 due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/05/events-cancelled-coronavirus.html|title=All the Live Events, Movie Releases, and Productions Affected by the Coronavirus|website=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]]|url-access=limited|date=4 May 2020|access-date=9 May 2020|archive-date=9 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200509093155/https://www.vulture.com/2020/05/events-cancelled-coronavirus.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|date=10 June 2020|title=Harry Styles Postpones North American Love On Tour Until Summer 2021|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9400069/harry-styles-north-american-tour-postponement|access-date=11 June 2020|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archive-date=11 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611074542/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9400069/harry-styles-north-american-tour-postponement|url-status=live}}</ref>

At the [[2020 Brit Awards]], Styles was nominated for [[Brit Award for British Male Solo Artist|British Male Solo Artist]] and [[Brit Award for British Album of the Year|British Album of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51535680|title=Brit Awards 2020: Full list of nominees|work=[[BBC News]]|date=17 February 2020|access-date=14 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217205532/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-51535680|archive-date=17 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2020, he performed an [[NPR]] [[Tiny Desk Concerts|Tiny Desk concert]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=McKenna|first1=Lyndsey|last2=Lorusso|first2=Marissa|url=https://www.npr.org/2020/03/16/815556266/harry-styles-tiny-desk-concert|title=Harry Styles: Tiny Desk Concert|work=[[NPR]]|date=16 March 2020|access-date=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317124147/https://www.npr.org/2020/03/16/815556266/harry-styles-tiny-desk-concert|archive-date=17 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and in July, he narrated a [[bedtime story]] titled ''Dream with Me'' for the [[Mindfulness|relaxation]] [[Mobile app|app]] [[Calm (company)|Calm]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Haylock|first1=Zoe|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/07/harry-styles-calm-app-review.html|title=The Joy of Sleeping With Harry Styles (on the Calm App)|website=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]]|url-access=limited|date=15 July 2020|access-date=14 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200716170634/https://www.vulture.com/2020/07/harry-styles-calm-app-review.html|archive-date=16 July 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles co-wrote the song 'Changes' for [[Cam (singer)|Cam]]'s album [[The Otherside (album)|The Otherside]]<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Brandle |first=Lars |date=30 October 2020 |title=Cam Drops 'The Otherside,' Featuring Songs With Harry Styles, Tim Bergling and More: Listen |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/cam-the-otherside-harry-styles-tim-bergling-stream-9475626/ |url-status=live |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220916120214/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/cam-the-otherside-harry-styles-tim-bergling-stream-9475626/ |archive-date=16 September 2022 |access-date=30 October 2020}}</ref> Later that year, Styles won the [[American Music Award for Favorite Pop/Rock Album|Favorite Pop/Rock Album]] award for ''Fine Line'' at the [[American Music Awards of 2020|48th American Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/9488111/amas-2020-winners-list-american-music-awards/|title=Here Are All the Winners From the 2020 AMAs|date=22 November 2020|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=23 November 2020|archive-date=23 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123010705/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/9488111/amas-2020-winners-list-american-music-awards/|url-status=live}}</ref> the Best International Artist award at the [[2020 ARIA Music Awards|34th ARIA Music Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Gwee|first=Karen|url=https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/music/aria-awards-2020-australia-winners-rolling-list-2824040|title=Here are all the winners from the ARIA Awards 2020|work=[[NME]]|date=25 November 2020|access-date=26 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125054747/https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/music/aria-awards-2020-australia-winners-rolling-list-2824040|archive-date=25 November 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and the [[Billboard Music Award for Chart Achievement|Chart Achievement Award]] at the [[2020 Billboard Music Awards|27th ''Billboard'' Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Atkinson|first=Katie|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbmas/9465082/2020-billboard-music-awards-winners/|title=2020 Billboard Music Awards Winners: Complete List|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=14 October 2020|access-date=27 November 2020|archive-date=26 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126175557/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/bbmas/9465082/2020-billboard-music-awards-winners/|url-status=live}}</ref> He was also named ''Variety''{{'}}s Hitmaker of the Year.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Oganesyan|first=Natalie|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-hitmaker-of-the-year-variety-1234827231/|title=Harry Styles Named Variety's Hitmaker of the Year|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=10 November 2020|access-date=27 November 2020|archive-date=27 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127131359/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-hitmaker-of-the-year-variety-1234827231/|url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[63rd Annual Grammy Awards]] in March 2021, he received three nominations for [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album|Best Pop Vocal Album]] (''Fine Line''), [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Solo Performance|Best Pop Solo Performance]] ("Watermelon Sugar") and [[Grammy Award for Best Music Video|Best Music Video]] ("Adore You"), winning for Best Pop Solo Performance.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fekadu|first1=Mesfin|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/grammys-announce-1st-batch-of-nominees-for-2021-show/2020/11/24/54ccf1fe-2e78-11eb-9dd6-2d0179981719_story.html|title=A Grammys 'Savage': Beyoncé leads with 9 nominations|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|url-access=limited|date=24 November 2020|access-date=24 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124181238/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/grammys-announce-1st-batch-of-nominees-for-2021-show/2020/11/24/54ccf1fe-2e78-11eb-9dd6-2d0179981719_story.html|archive-date=24 November 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Libbey|first=Peter|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/14/arts/music/grammys-winners-list.html|title=2021 Grammys Winners: The Full List|magazine=[[The New York Times]]|url-access=limited|date=14 March 2021|access-date=15 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315113314/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/14/arts/music/grammys-winners-list.html|archive-date=15 March 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> "Watermelon Sugar" also earned Styles his second Brit Award for [[Brit Award for Song of the Year|British Single of the Year]] during the [[2021 Brit Awards|2021 ceremony]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Skinner|first=Tom|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/brit-awards-2021-winners-list-2938278|title=Here are the winners from the BRIT Awards 2021 – rolling list|work=[[NME]]|date=11 May 2021|access-date=11 May 2021|archive-date=11 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210511211540/https://www.nme.com/news/music/brit-awards-2021-winners-list-2938278|url-status=live}}</ref> After previous postponement, [[Love On Tour]] kicked off on 4 September 2021 in Las Vegas.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-footage-of-harry-styles-kicking-off-his-love-on-tour-dates-in-las-vegas-3037199|title= Watch footage of Harry Styles kicking off his 'Love On Tour' dates in Las Vegas|website= [[NME]]|date= 5 September 2021|access-date= 5 September 2021|archive-date= 5 September 2021|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210905080440/https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-footage-of-harry-styles-kicking-off-his-love-on-tour-dates-in-las-vegas-3037199|url-status= live}}</ref> At the 2021 [[Ivor Novello Awards]], "Adore You" won the award for Most Performed Work.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Khomami|first1=Nadia|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2021/sep/21/harry-styles-lianne-la-havas-dave-and-fraser-t-smith-win-ivor-awards|title=Harry Styles, Lianne La Havas, Dave and Fraser T Smith win Ivor awards|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=21 September 2021|access-date=22 September 2021|archive-date=21 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210921201406/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2021/sep/21/harry-styles-lianne-la-havas-dave-and-fraser-t-smith-win-ivor-awards|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles made a [[cameo appearance]] as [[Eros (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Eros / Starfox]], brother of [[Thanos (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Thanos]], in the [[mid-credits scene]] of the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] superhero film ''[[Eternals (film)|Eternals]]'', which was released in November 2021.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Paul |first=Larisha |date=19 October 2021 |title=Harry Styles Will Apparently Arouse Everyone as Eros in MCU's 'Eternals' |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-eros-eternals-mcu-1244181/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211019234141/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-eros-eternals-mcu-1244181/ |archive-date=19 October 2021 |access-date=20 October 2021 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref> He launched his gender-neutral skin and nail care brand, [[Pleasing (brand)|Pleasing]], that month.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Maoui|first=Zak|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/grooming/article/harry-styles-pleasing|title=Introducing Pleasing, Harry Styles' first brand|magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]]|date=15 November 2021|access-date=15 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211115204542/https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/grooming/article/harry-styles-pleasing|archive-date=15 November 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

===2022–present: ''Harry's House'' and further acting roles===
[[File:Harry Styles Wembley June 2022 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|right|Styles performing at [[Wembley Stadium]] in 2022]]
[[File:Can I Offer You A Scotch, Officer- - My Policeman - Prime Video edited 0.webm|thumb|Scene from ''[[My Policeman (film)|My Policeman]]'' (2022) featuring Harry Styles as Tom Burgess and [[David Dawson (actor)|David Dawson]] as Patrick Hazlewood.]]

In 2022, Styles achieved critical and commercial success with his third album, ''[[Harry's House]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=''Harry's House'' by Harry Styles Reviews |url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/harrys-house/harry-styles/critic-reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |access-date=11 June 2024 |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226160114/https://www.metacritic.com/music/harrys-house/harry-styles/critic-reviews |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="DoubleChart">{{Cite magazine |last=Lars |first=Brandle |date=1 June 2022 |title=Harry Styles Floods Global Charts With ''Harry's House'' |url=https://themusicnetwork.com/harry-styles-global-charts-harrys-house/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221130081853/https://themusicnetwork.com/harry-styles-global-charts-harrys-house/ |archive-date=30 November 2022 |access-date=16 July 2024 |magazine=[[The Music Network]]}}</ref> Its lead single, "[[As It Was]]," debuted atop the UK and US charts, becoming his second solo number-one single in both countries.<ref>{{cite web|last=Griffiths|first=George|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/harry-styles-claims-career-best-debut-with-second-solo-number-1-single__35710/|title=Harry Styles claims career-best debut with second solo Number 1 single|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=8 April 2022|access-date=8 April 2022|archive-date=8 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220408164657/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/harry-styles-claims-career-best-debut-with-second-solo-number-1-single__35710/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/harry-styles-as-it-was-number-one-billboard-hot-100-debut-1235057698/|title=Harry Styles' 'As It Was' Launches at No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100|last=Trust|first=Gary|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=11 April 2022|access-date=11 April 2022|archive-date=11 April 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411171729/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/harry-styles-as-it-was-number-one-billboard-hot-100-debut-1235057698/|url-status=live}}</ref> In the US, it became the [[List of Billboard Hot 100 chart achievements and milestones#Songs milestones|fourth-longest-running number-one in the charts history]], at 15 weeks.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-63045287|title=Harry Styles' As It Was becomes longest-running US number one by a UK act|work=[[BBC]]|date=27 September 2022|access-date=27 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220927085014/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-63045287|archive-date=27 September 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> The album similarly debuted atop the UK and US charts.<ref>{{cite web|last=Smith|first=Carl|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/harry-styles-boasts-fastest-selling-album-of-the-year-to-date-with-harry-s-house__36460/|title=Harry Styles boasts fastest-selling album of the year to date with ''Harry's House''|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=27 May 2022|access-date=2 June 2022|archive-date=26 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226160850/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/harry-styles-boasts-fastest-selling-album-of-the-year-to-date-with-harry-s-house__36460/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/harry-styles-harrys-house-number-one-billboard-200-chart-1235078807/|title=Harry Styles' ''Harry's House'' Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 With Half-Million-Plus First Week in U.S.|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=29 May 2022|access-date=2 June 2022|archive-date=29 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220529200437/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/harry-styles-harrys-house-number-one-billboard-200-chart-1235078807/|url-status=live}}</ref> During its release week, Styles occupied the top spot of the album and singles charts in over fifteen countries, including the UK and US, with ''Harry's House'' and "As It Was," respectively.<ref name="DoubleChart" /> With four tracks from the album concurrently charting within the US top 10, he became the first British solo artist to achieve this feat.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Trust|first=Gary|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/harry-styles-as-it-was-harrys-house-hot-100-number-one-1235078922/|title=Harry Styles Returns to No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100 With 'As It Was,' Debuts 3 Songs in Top 10|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=31 May 2022|access-date=2 June 2022|archive-date=9 June 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220609101700/https://www.billboard.com/music/chart-beat/harry-styles-as-it-was-harrys-house-hot-100-number-one-1235078922/|url-status=live}}</ref> He headlined the [[Coachella|Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]] in April to a crowd of over 100,000 people.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last1=Aswad |first1=Jem |last2=Halperin |first2=Shirley |date=20 April 2022 |title=Harry Styles' Coachella Crowd Topped 100,000 During Opening-Night Performance |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/harry-styles-audience-size-coachella-1235237258/ |access-date=11 June 2024 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US |archive-date=27 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230427001602/https://variety.com/2022/music/news/harry-styles-audience-size-coachella-1235237258/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In June, Styles and his song "[[Music for a Sushi Restaurant]]" were featured in a new [[AirPods]] commercial for [[Apple Inc.|Apple]].<ref name="Harry Styles Helps Apple Bring Back Its Iconic ‘Silhouettes’ Ad">{{cite magazine |last1=Kreps |first1=Daniel |title=Harry Styles Helps Apple Bring Back Its Iconic 'Silhouettes' Ad |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-apple-silhouettes-ad-airpods-1361933/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=2 June 2022 |date=2 June 2022 |archive-date=2 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220602160653/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-apple-silhouettes-ad-airpods-1361933/ |url-status=live }}</ref> A music video for ''Harry's House''{{'}}s second single, "[[Late Night Talking]]," was released on 13 July.<ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Dailey|first=Hannah|title=Harry Styles Has Fun in Bed in 'Late Night Talking' Music Video: Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-late-night-talking-music-video-1235113797/|date=13 July 2022|access-date=13 July 2022|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|archive-date=13 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220713165903/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-late-night-talking-music-video-1235113797/|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that month, ''Harry's House'' was short-listed for the [[Mercury Prize]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Singh |first=Surej |title=Mercury Prize 2022 shortlist revealed |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/mercury-prize-2022-shortlist-nominations-3277014 |magazine=[[NME]] |date=26 July 2022 |access-date=23 October 2022 |archive-date=26 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220726101632/https://www.nme.com/news/music/mercury-prize-2022-shortlist-nominations-3277014 |url-status=live }}</ref> "As It Was" became the [[List of Billboard Global 200 number ones of 2022|number-one song of 2022 globally]], according to ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2022/billboard-global-200/|title=Year-End Charts, Billboard Global 200|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=19 July 2024}}</ref> At the [[2022 MTV Video Music Awards]], Styles received three accolades, including [[MTV Video Music Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]] for ''Harry's House''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Daly|first1=Rhian|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/mtv-vmas-2022-winners-list-3299368|title=Here are all the winners from the MTV VMAs 2022|website=[[NME]]|date=29 August 2022|access-date=29 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220829005540/https://www.nme.com/news/music/mtv-vmas-2022-winners-list-3299368|archive-date=29 August 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> The album won Album of the Year and Best Pop Vocal Album at the [[65th Annual Grammy Awards|65th Grammy Awards]] and British Album of the Year at the [[Brit Awards 2023|43rd Brit Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-64533539|author=Mark Savage|title=Grammys 2023: Beyoncé makes history and Harry Styles wins album of the year|work=[[BBC]]|date=6 February 2023|access-date=16 February 2023|archive-date=15 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230215141602/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-64533539|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-64612218|author=Helen Bushby|title=Brit Awards 2023: Harry Styles steals the show with four wins|work=[[BBC]]|date=12 February 2023|access-date=16 February 2023|archive-date=14 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230214115506/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-64612218|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Rolling Stone'' ranked ''Harry's House'' at number 491 on its 2023 revision of the "500 Greatest Albums of All Time" list.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-albums-of-all-time-1062063/harry-styles-harrys-house-3-1234935322/ |title=The 500 Greatest Albums of All Time (2023) |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=31 December 2023 |access-date=10 June 2024 |archive-date=1 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240101201856/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-albums-of-all-time-1062063/harry-styles-harrys-house-3-1234935322/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Styles auditioned for the role of Elvis Presley in [[Baz Luhrmann]]'s musical biopic ''[[Elvis (2022 film)|Elvis]]'' (2022). Luhrmann stated that while "Harry is a really talented actor ... the real issue with Harry is, he's Harry Styles. He's already an icon."<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.nme.com/news/film/baz-luhrmann-harry-styles-embodies-so-much-elvis-3245346|title= Baz Luhrmann says Harry Styles "embodies so much of Elvis"|website= [[NME]]|date= 12 June 2022|access-date= 15 June 2022|archive-date= 15 June 2022|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220615182701/https://www.nme.com/news/film/baz-luhrmann-harry-styles-embodies-so-much-elvis-3245346|url-status= live}}</ref> Styles starred alongside [[Florence Pugh]] in the 2022 psychological thriller film ''[[Don't Worry Darling]]'', directed by [[Olivia Wilde]].<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=Romano|first1=Nick|url=https://ew.com/movies/dont-worry-darling-first-look-florence-pugh-harry-styles/|title=Don't Worry Darling drops first look at Florence Pugh, Harry Styles film|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=4 March 2021|access-date=8 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304162139/https://ew.com/movies/dont-worry-darling-first-look-florence-pugh-harry-styles/|archive-date=4 March 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> Having premiered at the [[79th Venice International Film Festival]], the film, as well as his performance, received mixed reviews.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/dont-worry-darling|title=''Don't Worry Darling''|website=[[Metacritic]]|access-date=7 September 2022|archive-date=4 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220904170145/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/dont-worry-darling|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dont_worry_darling|title=Don't Worry Darling|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=7 September 2022|archive-date=6 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220906014059/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/dont_worry_darling|url-status=live}}</ref> Steph Green, writing for the [[BBC]], noted, "Harry Styles doesn't feel up to the material here, with leaden line delivery and a lack of light and shade making his scenes opposite Pugh fall flat,"<ref>{{Cite web |last=Green |first=Steph |title=Don't Worry Darling review: Full of 'half-baked ideas' |url=https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20220905-dont-worry-darling-is-full-of-half-baked-risk-free-ideas |access-date=10 September 2022 |work=[[BBC]] |language=en |archive-date=10 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220910021454/https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20220905-dont-worry-darling-is-full-of-half-baked-risk-free-ideas |url-status=live }}</ref> but some were more positive of his performance, with [[Owen Gleiberman]] writing, "With his popping eyes, floppy shock of hair, and saturnine suaveness, he recalls the young [[Frank Sinatra]] as an actor."<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gleiberman |first=Owen |date=5 September 2022 |title='Don't Worry Darling' Review: Florence Pugh and Harry Styles Sizzle in Olivia Wilde's Neo-'50s Nightmare Thriller, but the Movie Is More Showy Than Convincing |url=https://variety.com/2022/film/reviews/dont-worry-darling-review-florence-pugh-harry-styles-olivia-wilde-1235360429/ |access-date=5 September 2022 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US |archive-date=10 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220910090354/https://variety.com/2022/film/reviews/dont-worry-darling-review-florence-pugh-harry-styles-olivia-wilde-1235360429/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in 2022, Styles starred alongside [[Emma Corrin]] in ''[[My Policeman (film)|My Policeman]]'', a film adaptation of the [[My Policeman|2012 novel of the same name]] which premiered at the [[Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Brent|last=Lang|url=https://variety.com/2022/film/markets-festivals/harry-styles-gay-drama-my-policeman-world-premiere-toronto-film-festival-1235321892/|title=Harry Styles Drama 'My Policeman' to World Premiere at Toronto Film Festival|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=21 July 2022|access-date=11 June 2024|archive-date=19 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220819184358/https://variety.com/2022/film/markets-festivals/harry-styles-gay-drama-my-policeman-world-premiere-toronto-film-festival-1235321892/|url-status=live}}</ref> At the 2022 [[TIFF Tribute Awards]], the main cast of the film were awarded the TIFF Tribute Award for Performance.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Nolfi |first=Joey |date=8 August 2022 |title=Harry Styles, My Policeman cast win early acting award in the Oscars race |url=https://ew.com/awards/2022-tiff-peoples-choice-award-my-policeman-cast-harry-styles/ |access-date=8 August 2022 |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |language=en-US |archive-date=8 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220808180610/https://ew.com/awards/2022-tiff-peoples-choice-award-my-policeman-cast-harry-styles/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite this, reviews for the film and his performance were less positive, with Robert Daniels of ''[[RogerEbert.com]]'' writing, "Here, Styles' inexperience as a leading man in a weepy British queer period piece is glaring."<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/my-policeman-movie-review-2022|title= My Policeman|website= [[RogerEbert.com]]|access-date= 12 September 2022|archive-date= 12 September 2022|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20220912153147/https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/my-policeman-movie-review-2022|url-status= live}}</ref>

In August and September 2022, as part of his Love On Tour, Styles performed 15 sold-out shows at [[Madison Square Garden]]. To mark the achievement, a permanent banner was raised in his honor inside the venue. He became the third musical artist in history to have a banner raised at Madison Square Garden, following rock band [[Phish]] and artist [[Billy Joel]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-banner-raised-msg-rafters-15-show-run-1235142875/|title=Harry Styles Banner Raised to MSG Rafters After History-Making 15-Show Run: 'That's Insane'|date=22 September 2022|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=22 September 2022|archive-date=22 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922122723/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-banner-raised-msg-rafters-15-show-run-1235142875/}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-madison-square-garden-banner-raising-1234597708/|title=Harry Styles Celebrates Historic 15-Show Run at Madison Square Garden With Banner Raising|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=22 September 2022|access-date=22 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922081639/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-madison-square-garden-banner-raising-1234597708/|archive-date=22 September 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2022, Gucci released a collaborative collection between [[Alessandro Michele]] and Styles, titled "Gucci Ha Ha Ha."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Directo-Meston |first=Danielle |date=3 November 2022 |title=Harry Styles Wears His "Dream Wardrobe" in New Gucci Campaign |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lifestyle/shopping/harry-styles-gucci-ha-ha-ha-campaign-collection-1235255006/ |access-date=3 November 2022 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |language=en-US |archive-date=3 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221103234334/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lifestyle/shopping/harry-styles-gucci-ha-ha-ha-campaign-collection-1235255006/ |url-status=live }}</ref> At the [[American Music Awards of 2022|50th American Music Awards]], Styles won Favorite Male Pop Artist and Favorite Pop Song ("As It Was").<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Moreau |first=Jordan |date=20 November 2022 |title=American Music Awards 2022: Full Winners List |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/awards/american-music-awards-winners-1235432252/ |access-date=20 November 2022 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US |archive-date=20 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221120224709/https://variety.com/2022/music/awards/american-music-awards-winners-1235432252/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Love On Tour concluded in July 2023 as the then-[[List of highest-grossing concert tours|fifth-highest-grossing tour of all time]], earning $617.3 million.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/pro/harry-styles-love-on-tour-fourth-600-million-trek-ever/|title=Harry Styles' Love On Tour Ends As the Fourth $600 Million Trek Ever|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Eric|last=Frankenberg|date=7 August 2023|access-date=27 August 2023|archive-date=9 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230809180634/https://www.billboard.com/pro/harry-styles-love-on-tour-fourth-600-million-trek-ever/|url-status=live}}</ref> In September 2023, Styles gave background vocals on bandmate [[Mitch Rowland]]'s track "Here Comes the Comeback" for his debut album, ''Come June''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Reilly |first=Nick |date=2023-09-14 |title=Mitch Rowland shares 'Here Comes The Comeback' with backing vocals from Harry Styles |url=https://www.rollingstone.co.uk/music/news/mitch-rowland-shares-here-comes-the-comeback-with-backing-vocals-from-harry-styles-32722/ |access-date=2024-05-15 |website=[[Rolling Stone UK]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> In July 2024, Styles joined [[Stevie Nicks]] on stage at the [[British Summer Time (concerts)|British Summer Time]] festival in [[Hyde Park, London|Hyde Park]] in London to perform "[[Stop Draggin' My Heart Around]]" and "[[Landslide (Fleetwood Mac song)|Landslide]]" in tribute of [[Christine McVie]]'s birthday.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2024-07-12 |title=Harry Styles and Stevie Nicks Duet in Tribute to Christine McVie at BST Hyde Park Concert |url=https://variety.com/2024/music/news/harry-styles-stevie-nicks-christine-mcvie-tribute-bst-hyde-park-1236069396/ |access-date=2024-07-13 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US}}</ref>

