Styles' music has been described as [[Pop music|pop]], [[pop rock]], [[Rock music|rock]], [[soft rock]], [[Britpop]], [[New wave music|new wave]], [[synth-pop]] and [[disco]], with elements of [[Folk music|folk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/harry-styles-new-album-review-harrys-house-9h32qzbnf|title=Harry Styles: Harry's House review — a masterclass in how to be a charming pop star|website=[[The Times]]|url-access=subscription|last=Hodgkinson|first=Will|date=16 May 2022|access-date=20 May 2022|quote=a nice collection of pop-rock tunes|archive-date=23 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220523034419/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/harry-styles-new-album-review-harrys-house-9h32qzbnf|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="NME debut">{{cite web|last=Cooper|first=Leonie|title=Harry Styles – 'Harry Styles' Review|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/harry-styles-harry-styles-album-review-nme|website=[[NME]]|publisher=[[TI Media]]|access-date=12 May 2017|date=12 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512060619/http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/harry-styles-harry-styles-album-review-nme|archive-date=12 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="The Straits Times">{{Cite news|last=Raguraman|first=Anjali|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/soft-rock-with-an-edge|title=Soft rock with an edge|date=17 May 2017|work=[[The Straits Times]]|access-date=25 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170530173543/http://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/soft-rock-with-an-edge|archive-date=30 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="NPR HS">{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/therecord/2017/05/16/528617874/styles-of-the-times|title=Styles Of The Times|last1=Powers|first1=Ann|author-link1=Ann Powers|date=16 May 2017|work=[[NPR]]|access-date=7 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711211955/http://www.npr.org/sections/therecord/2017/05/16/528617874/styles-of-the-times|archive-date=11 July 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Britpop" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/harry-styles-harrys-house-album-review/|title="Harry Styles Harry's House Review: A Pop Trendsetter Tries on Different Styles"|website=[[Slant Magazine]]|date=16 May 2022|access-date=21 November 2022|archive-date=18 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220518011054/https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/harry-styles-harrys-house-album-review/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/qjddvb/harry-styles-fine-line-album-review-2019|title=The New Harry Styles Album Is Brilliant – But Only Occasionally|last=O'Neill|first=Lauren|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|date=12 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311025138/https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/qjddvb/harry-styles-fine-line-album-review-2019|archive-date=11 March 2020|url-status=live|access-date=16 June 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|last=Appleford|first=Steve|title=Harry Styles Emulates Folk-Rock Heroes at Intimate Los Angeles Gig|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-live-reviews/harry-styles-emulates-folk-rock-heroes-at-intimate-los-angeles-gig-194355/|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=5 December 2017|date=20 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180717150516/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-live-reviews/harry-styles-emulates-folk-rock-heroes-at-intimate-los-angeles-gig-194355/|archive-date=17 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The musical style on his debut solo album was called a "mish-mash of Los Angeles' style classic rock and ballads" by ''[[NME]]'',<ref name="NME debut" /> invoking an "intimately emotional Seventies soft-rock vibe" by ''Rolling Stone'', and "synthesis[ing] influences from the last half-century of rock" by ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine.<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://time.com/4775461/harry-styles-solo-album-review/|title=Harry Styles' Solo Album Is an Unexpected Tour of Rock History|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|last=Lansky|first=Sam|access-date=27 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171116231537/http://time.com/4775461/harry-styles-solo-album-review/|archive-date=16 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/review-harry-styles-is-a-true-rock-star-on-superb-solo-debut-119736/|title=Review: Harry Styles Is a True Rock Star on Superb Solo Debut|access-date=27 October 2018|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181027143144/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/review-harry-styles-is-a-true-rock-star-on-superb-solo-debut-119736/|archive-date=27 October 2018|url-status=live|date=12 May 2017}}</ref> It was influenced by the artists he grew up listening to, such as [[Pink Floyd]], [[the Rolling Stones]], [[the Beatles]] and [[Fleetwood Mac]], as well as the songwriting of [[Harry Nilsson]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Coscarelli|first=Joe|title=Harry Styles Opens Up, Slightly, About Going Solo With a Rock Edge|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/11/arts/music/harry-styles-solo-album-interview.html|website=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=8 December 2017|date=11 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208070738/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/11/arts/music/harry-styles-solo-album-interview.html|archive-date=8 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Nilsson">{{cite web|last=McDermott|first=Maeve|title=Harry Styles interview: Writing his new album was 'like therapy'|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2017/05/12/harry-styles-interview-new-album/101462222/|website=[[USA Today]]|access-date=8 December 2017|date=12 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208075110/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2017/05/12/harry-styles-interview-new-album/101462222/|archive-date=8 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles praised Nilsson's lyrics as being "honest, and so good, and I think it's because he's never trying to sound clever."<ref name="Nilsson" /> His second solo album, ''Fine Line'', was seen by ''NME'' to have taken, "this nostalgic sound [from his first record] and combined it with soaring pop sensibilities."<ref>{{cite magazine |date=9 December 2019 |title=Harry Styles – 'Fine Line' review: packed with personality and charm (and saucy lyrics) |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/harry-styles-fine-line-review-packed-with-personality-and-charm-and-saucy-lyrics-2584779 |access-date=4 July 2022 |magazine=[[NME]] |language=en-GB |archive-date=9 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209215729/https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/harry-styles-fine-line-review-packed-with-personality-and-charm-and-saucy-lyrics-2584779 |url-status=live }}</ref> Music critics have described Styles as having a [[baritone]] [[vocal range]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Amir |first=Maya |date=February 19, 2023 |title=Harry Styles and his evolution from One Direction to King of Pop |url=https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/23326706.harry-styles-evolution-one-direction-king-pop/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231201165404/https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/23326706.harry-styles-evolution-one-direction-king-pop/ |archive-date=December 1, 2023 |access-date=October 18, 2024 |work=[[The Herald (Glasgow)|The Herald]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Sherman |first=Maria |date=September 5, 2022 |title=The essential Harry Styles song book |url=https://www.rollingstone.co.uk/music/lists/harry-styles-essential-songs-solo-one-direction-22241/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240930174435/https://www.rollingstone.co.uk/music/lists/harry-styles-essential-songs-solo-one-direction-22241/ |archive-date=September 30, 2024 |access-date=October 18, 2024 |work=[[Rolling Stone UK]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Montes |first=Rebeca Partida |date=May 24, 2017 |title=Ex-boyband member releases soft rock album |url=https://www.mesapress.com/audio/2017/05/24/ex-boyband-member-releases-soft-rock-album/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221203123320/https://www.mesapress.com/audio/2017/05/24/ex-boyband-member-releases-soft-rock-album/ |archive-date=December 3, 2022 |access-date=October 18, 2024 |work=[[San Diego Mesa College|The Mesa Press]]}}</ref>

Styles said, "I think with music it's so important to evolve—and that extends to clothes and videos and all that stuff. That's why you look back at David Bowie with [[Ziggy Stardust (character)|Ziggy Stardust]] or the Beatles and their different eras—that fearlessness is super inspiring."<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://vogue.sg/harry-styles-american-vogue-december-issue-cover-story/|title=10 things you need to know about Harry Styles' internet-breaking American Vogue December issue cover story|date=14 November 2020|access-date=14 November 2020|archive-date=21 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210621164538/https://vogue.sg/harry-styles-american-vogue-december-issue-cover-story/|magazine=[[Vogue Singapore]]|url-status=live}}</ref> While making ''Fine Line'' he said he kept watching a vintage Bowie clip on his phone, which he used as an inspiring pep talk to push his art further.<ref name=EternalSunshineHarry>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-cover-interview-album-871568/|title=The Eternal Sunshine of Harry Styles|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|url-access=subscription|publisher=Penske Business Media|date=26 August 2019|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|access-date=23 December 2020|archive-date=2 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191102083823/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-cover-interview-album-871568/|url-status=live}}</ref> He has also cited [[Freddie Mercury]], Elvis Presley, and [[Paul McCartney]] (including his side project [[Paul McCartney and Wings|Wings]]) as influences, while mentioning [[Shania Twain]] as his main inspiration both musically and in fashion.<ref>{{cite web|last=Frank|first=Alex|title=Harry Styles Moves Like Jagger, But His Heart Belongs to Shania Twain|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-shania-twain-style|website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|publisher=[[Condé Nast]]|access-date=5 December 2017|date=30 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206135852/https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-shania-twain-style|archive-date=6 December 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="HarrysFavourite" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.howardstern.com/show/2020/3/1/harry-styles-walking-away-one-direction-befriending-stevie-nicks-and-being-robbed-knifepoint/|title=Harry Styles on Stern Show|work=Howard Stern|date=2 March 2020|access-date=13 September 2020|archive-date=1 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200501220753/https://www.howardstern.com/show/2020/3/1/harry-styles-walking-away-one-direction-befriending-stevie-nicks-and-being-robbed-knifepoint/|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles attributed the American twang in his music to Presley as he was the first artist Styles grew up listening to.<ref name="HarrysFavourite" /> When curating an "All-time top ten tracks" mixtape for ''[[Another Man]]'', Styles included tracks by [[Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young|Crosby, Stills & Nash]], [[Ray Charles]], [[Blaze Foley]], [[Patsy Cline]], and [[Travis (band)|Travis]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2016-09-29 |title=Listen to Harry Styles' Ultimate Mixtape for Another Man |url=https://www.anothermag.com/another-man/9113/listen-to-harry-styles-ultimate-mixtape-for-another-man |access-date=2024-06-11 |magazine=[[Another Magazine]] |language=en}}</ref> Upon listening to Pink Floyd's 1973 album ''[[The Dark Side of the Moon]]'' as a child, he said he "couldn't really get it, but I just remember being like—this is really fucking cool."<ref name="rolling stone" /> The first song Styles learned the words to was "[[Dreams (Fleetwood Mac song)|Dreams]]" (1977) by Fleetwood Mac, although as a child he believed the song "was about the weather."<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Bell |first=Keaton |date=25 November 2020 |title=Stevie Nicks Answers All Our Questions About Harry Styles |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/stevie-nicks-harry-styles-fleetwood-mac |access-date=12 June 2024 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |date=29 March 2019 |title=Read Harry Styles' Heartwarming Rock Hall Tribute to Stevie Nicks |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-stevie-nicks-rock-and-roll-hall-of-fame-2019-813901/ |access-date=12 June 2024 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]}}</ref>

Styles' favourite album is ''[[Astral Weeks]]'' (1968) by [[Van Morrison]], which he called "completely perfect;" he also considers [[Etta James]]'s album ''[[At Last!]]'' (1960) to be "perfect." His favourite album cover is [[Plastic Ono Band]]'s 1969 live album ''[[Live Peace in Toronto 1969]]''.<ref name="HarrysFavourite" /> Styles labelled [[Paul Simon]]'s "[[50 Ways to Leave Your Lover]]" (1975) as "the greatest verse melody ever written," [[Simon & Garfunkel]]'s "[[The Boxer]]" (1969) as "a perfect lyric, especially that first verse," and "[[Helplessly Hoping]]" (1969) by [[Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young|Crosby, Stills & Nash]] as the song he "would play if I had three minutes to live."<ref name="HarrysFavourite" /> He is also inspired by [[George Michael]], sampling "[[Faith (George Michael song)|Faith]]" (1987) for his unreleased track "Anna" and has lyrics from "[[Careless Whisper]]" (1984) tattooed on his ankles.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Butterworth |first=Benjamin |date=2018-03-15 |title=Harry Styles performs George Michael as he hints at being bisexual |url=https://www.thepinknews.com/2018/03/15/harry-styles-performs-george-michael-as-he-hints-at-being-bisexual/ |access-date=2024-06-12 |newspaper=[[PinkNews]] |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=13 June 2013 |title=Harry Styles Debuts New George Michael 'Careless Whisper' Tattoos On His Ankles (PICTURES) |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2013/06/13/harry-styles-tattoos-george-michael-careless-whisper_n_3435595.html |access-date=12 June 2024 |newspaper=[[HuffPost]]}}</ref> [[Joni Mitchell]]'s album ''[[Blue (Joni Mitchell album)|Blue]]'' (1971) inspired Styles to contact the album's dulcimer instrumentalist, with whom he worked on ''Fine Line''. He also chose to record ''Fine Line'' in [[Jim Henson Company Lot|Henson Studios]] after being inspired by [[Carole King]]'s album ''[[Tapestry (Carole King album)|Tapestry]]'' (1971) as it was recorded there.<ref name=HarrysFavourite>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-favorite-things-albums-tv-878041/|title=The Harry Styles Hit List: A Few of His Favorite Things|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=Penske Business Media, LLC|date=29 August 2019|last=Sheffield|first=Rob|url-access=subscription|access-date=10 December 2020|archive-date=8 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108010438/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-favorite-things-albums-tv-878041/|url-status=live}}</ref>

During the [[COVID-19 lockdowns|COVID-19 lockdown]], Styles highlighted [[Mac Miller]]'s 2020 single "[[Blue World (Mac Miller song)|Blue World]]" as his personal quarantine track of choice.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Rowley |first=Glenn |date=2020-03-19 |title=Harry Styles Reveals How He's Staying Busy During Self-Isolation in New Interview: Listen |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-self-isolation-interview-9338343/ |access-date=2024-06-11 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |language=en-US}}</ref> He also compiled a playlist for Apple Music during lockdown, inclusive of artists such as [[Otis Redding]], [[Sam Cooke]], [[Bill Withers]], [[Billie Holiday]], [[Bread (band)|Bread]], and [[Labi Siffre]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lindsay |first=Kathryn |title=Harry Styles Is Learning Italian & Sign Language During Quarantine |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2020/03/9585090/harry-styles-quarantine-learning-italian-sign-language |access-date=2024-06-11 |website=[[Refinery29]] |language=en}}</ref> While writing his third album, ''Harry's House'', in Tokyo, Styles was inspired by [[Haruomi Hosono]]'s 1973 debut album ''[[Hosono House]]'' and paid homage to the album's title.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Michel |first=Patrick St |date=2022-06-05 |title=Harry and the house that Hosono built |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2022/06/05/music/harrys-house-hosono/ |access-date=2024-06-11 |newspaper=[[The Japan Times]] |language=en}}</ref> Upon announcing ''Harry's House'', Joni Mitchell, whose 1975 album ''[[The Hissing of Summer Lawns]]'' featured a track of the same name, tweeted that she "love[d] the title."<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gallagher |first=Alex |date=2022-03-24 |title=Joni Mitchell approves of Harry Styles naming his new album 'Harry's House' |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/joni-mitchell-approves-of-harry-styles-naming-his-new-album-harrys-house-3189222 |access-date=2024-06-11 |magazine=[[NME]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> [[Gerry Rafferty]]'s 1978 single "[[Right Down the Line]]" was a specific reference point during the creation of ''Harry's House''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Willman |first=Chris |date=2022-12-01 |title=Harry Styles' 'House' Had Some Roommates: Kid Harpoon and Tyler Johnson on Making 2022's Most Ubiquitous Single, 'As It Was' |url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/songwriters-kid-harpoon-tyler-johnson-hitmakers-harry-styles-1235447248/ |access-date=2024-06-11 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US}}</ref>

Styles is also inspired by [[fine art]]. He has an extensive private art collection, owning original works from artists such as [[Jean-Michel Basquiat]], [[Damien Hirst]], [[Polly Morgan (taxidermist)|Polly Morgan]], [[Yunizar]], [[Ben Turnbull]], Jessica Zoob, and [[Hayden Kays]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 February 2014 |title=One Direction's Harry Styles Drops $4 Million on a Jean-Michel Basquiat Painting |url=https://www.complex.com/style/a/susan-cheng/one-direction-harry-styles-drops-4-million-on-a-painting-by-jean-michel-basquiat |access-date=12 June 2024 |website=Complex}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Tilley |first=Jade |date=2013-12-03 |title=Jessica Zoob - A British contemporary artist |url=https://interiordesignermagazine.co.uk/2013/12/03/jessica-zoob-a-british-contemporary-artist/ |access-date=2024-06-12 |website=Interior Designer Magazine |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2013-03-01 |title=Forget Socrates, it's stuffed foxes now for Harry Styles |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/londoners-diary/forget-socrates-it-s-stuffed-foxes-now-for-harry-styles-8516871.html |access-date=2024-06-12 |magazine=[[Evening Standard]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Stern |first=Joan |date=2023-06-03 |title=5 Crazy Expensive Things Harry Styles Has Bought |url=https://pursuitist.com/5-crazy-expensive-things-harry-styles-has-bought/ |access-date=2024-06-12 |website=Pursuitist |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Nessif |first=Bruna |date=5 February 2014 |title=Harry Styles Spends $33,000 on Sexually Provocative Art—Take a Peek! |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/507775/harry-styles-spends-33-000-on-provocative-sexual-art-take-a-peek |access-date=12 June 2024 |newspaper=[[E! News]]}}</ref> In the music video for his 2022 single "[[Late Night Talking]]," Styles referenced [[Tracey Emin]]'s 1998 seminal work ''[[My Bed]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gregory |first=Elizabeth |date=13 July 2022 |title=Late Night Talking: Harry Styles stays in bed in his new official video |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/culture/music/late-night-talking-harry-styles-releases-official-video-for-b1012186.html |access-date=12 June 2024 |magazine=[[Evening Standard]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Hunt |first=El |date=19 July 2022 |title=Why Everyone Is Talking About The Model In Harry Styles' "Late Night Talking" Video |url=https://www.bustle.com/entertainment/harry-styles-late-night-talking-music-video-girl-bed-model-thea |access-date=12 June 2024 |magazine=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]}}</ref> He is also inspired by English painter [[David Hockney]].<ref name=":4">{{Cite magazine |date=2020-11-13 |title=From College to a Vogue Cover Story, Harry Styles and Bode Celebrate Senior Cords |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-bode-senior-cord |access-date=2024-05-13 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |language=en-US}}</ref> In 2023, Hockney painted a portrait of Styles included in the exhibition called 'David Hockney: Drawing From Life' at [[National Portrait Gallery, London|The National Portrait Gallery]] in London. He called the experience a "complete privilege" and that "Hockney has been reinventing the way we look at the world for decades."<ref name=":3">{{Cite magazine |date=2023-08-02 |title=When Harry Styles Met David Hockney: An Exclusive First Look At A Special New Portrait |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/david-hockney-harry-styles-portrait |access-date=2024-05-13 |magazine=[[British Vogue]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> He has also cited writer [[Alain de Botton]] as influential, speaking to ''Vogue'', Styles stated "I love his writing, I just think he's brilliant." He also admitted that after reading de Botton's 2016 novel ''The Course of Love'', he fully appreciated the work required in cultivating and sustaining a romantic bond.<ref name=":15">{{Cite magazine |last=Ramzi |first=Lilah |date=2020-11-13 |title=Harry Styles Likes Alain de Botton—And He Has the Sweatshirt Prove It |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-alain-de-botton |access-date=2024-06-12 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |language=en-US}}</ref>

=== Stage performances ===
As a solo artist, Styles has chosen to tour as a rock artist with a backing band.<ref>{{cite news |last=Johnson |first=Kevin C. |title=Harry Styles lights up Enterprise Center with rock-star swagger, and it's worth the wait |url=https://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/music/reviews/harry-styles-lights-up-enterprise-center-with-rock-star-swagger-and-its-worth-the-wait/article_f5ab8f62-f4bb-5ee3-abf8-ffda1875631a.html |access-date=4 July 2022 |newspaper=[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]] |date=16 September 2021 |language=en |archive-date=5 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705191609/https://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/music/reviews/harry-styles-lights-up-enterprise-center-with-rock-star-swagger-and-its-worth-the-wait/article_f5ab8f62-f4bb-5ee3-abf8-ffda1875631a.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He plays acoustic guitar in addition to providing vocals.<ref>{{cite news |date=17 April 2018 |title=Harry Styles impresses the crowds at London's O2 Arena with funk and flair - review |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/harry-styles-review-o2-london-arena-tour-tickets-setlist-world-dates-2018-a8300911.html |access-date=4 July 2022 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |language=en |archive-date=17 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717021655/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/harry-styles-review-o2-london-arena-tour-tickets-setlist-world-dates-2018-a8300911.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Lead guitarist [[Mitch Rowland]] and drummer and vocalist [[Sarah Jones (drummer)|Sarah Jones]] have toured with Styles both during Harry Styles: Live on Tour and Love on Tour.<ref name="Rowland–Jones">{{cite web |date=15 March 2021 |title=Harry Styles' drummer Sarah Jones is pregnant with guitarist boyfriend Mitch Rowland. |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/harry-styles-sarah-jones-mitch-rowland-pregnant-drummer/ |access-date=21 May 2022 |website=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]] |archive-date=24 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220624231042/https://www.capitalfm.com/news/harry-styles-sarah-jones-mitch-rowland-pregnant-drummer/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Other members of his band have included the bassist/vocalist Elin Sandberg, pianist Niji Adeleye, percussionist and musical director [[Pauli Lovejoy]], multi-instrumentalist/vocalist Ny Oh, bassist Adam Prendergast, pianist Yaffra, keyboardist/vocalist Clare Uchima, and guitarist/keyboardist/vocalist Charlotte Clark.<ref name="Band">{{cite web |date=18 May 2022 |title=Who Are Harry Styles' Backing Band? Meet The Members |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/harry-styles/band-mitch-rowland-sarah-jones/ |access-date=21 May 2022 |website=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]] |archive-date=10 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211110172148/https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/harry-styles/band-mitch-rowland-sarah-jones/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Jade Yamazaki Stewart from the [[The Seattle Times|''Seattle Times'']] said of the band, "[Love on Tour] felt more like a 1970s rock festival than a 21st-century arena show from an international pop star."<ref>{{cite news |last=Stewart |first=Jade Yamazaki |date=8 November 2021 |title=Review: Harry Styles brings fans to emotional highs and lows at Tacoma Dome stop of Love on Tour |url=https://www.seattletimes.com/entertainment/music/review-harry-styles-brings-fans-to-emotional-highs-and-lows-at-tacoma-dome-stop-of-love-on-tour/ |access-date=4 July 2022 |newspaper=[[The Seattle Times]] |language=en-US |archive-date=5 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220705190913/https://www.seattletimes.com/entertainment/music/review-harry-styles-brings-fans-to-emotional-highs-and-lows-at-tacoma-dome-stop-of-love-on-tour/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Styles has been seen by critics to be an unusually energetic performer since at least 2015.<ref name=":13">{{Cite magazine |last=Sheffield |first=Rob |date=6 August 2015 |title=16 Reasons One Direction Are on Top of Stadium Rock |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-live-reviews/one-direction-stadium-tour-2015-51986/ |access-date=4 July 2022 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |language=en-US |archive-date=2 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220702173418/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-live-reviews/one-direction-stadium-tour-2015-51986/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In a 2015 ''Rolling Stone'' review of One Direction's concert at [[MetLife Stadium]], Rob Sheffield said, "It's like watching the footage of Secretariat running the Belmont Stakes in 1973 — he's 31 lengths ahead of the other horses, but he speeds up madly for the final stretch because he's so in love with being fast."<ref name=":13" /> Styles does not party or ingest substances after his shows because he tries to approach performing like an athlete in order to give fans the best show possible.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |date=18 May 2022 |title=Harry Styles Talks Showing His 'Bum Bum' on Film, Denies 'Daylight' Is About Taylor Swift on Howard Stern |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-talks-getting-naked-film-daylight-taylor-swift-olivia-wilde-love-song-howard-stern-1235072762/ |access-date=4 July 2022 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |language=en-US |archive-date=3 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220703004738/https://www.billboard.com/music/pop/harry-styles-talks-getting-naked-film-daylight-taylor-swift-olivia-wilde-love-song-howard-stern-1235072762/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Craig McLean described his onstage physicality for ''[[The Face (magazine)|The Face]]'' in 2022 as, "stomping, head-banging exuberance" that is "impossible to resist."<ref name=":14">{{cite magazine |last=McLean |first=Craig |date=25 May 2022 |title=The five best things that happened at Harry Styles' London show |url=https://theface.com/music/harry-styles-london-review-brixton-live-show-harrys-house-best-things-new-album |access-date=4 July 2022 |magazine=[[The Face (magazine)|The Face]] |language=en-gb |archive-date=28 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220628155354/https://theface.com/music/harry-styles-london-review-brixton-live-show-harrys-house-best-things-new-album |url-status=live }}</ref> His stage presence has been likened to that of Freddie Mercury and Mick Jagger,<ref name=":14" /><ref>{{cite magazine |last=D'Souza |first=Shaad |date=1 December 2017 |title=Harry Styles review: a frenzy of Jagger struts and pure happiness |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/dec/01/harry-styles-review-a-frenzy-of-jagger-struts-and-pure-happiness |access-date=1 December 2017 |magazine=[[The Guardian]] |language=en-gb |archive-date=1 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201014052/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/dec/01/harry-styles-review-a-frenzy-of-jagger-struts-and-pure-happiness |url-status=live }}</ref> while his charisma and playfulness have prompted comparisons to [[Rod Stewart]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Baltin |first=Steve |date=18 November 2021 |title=Harry Styles Shows Why He Is Music's Next Great Arena Rock Headliner At Dazzling L.A. Gig |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/stevebaltin/2021/11/18/harry-styles-shows-why-he-is-musics-next-great-arena-rock-headliner-at-dazzling-la-gig/?sh=191972ff56e5 |access-date=18 November 2021 |magazine=[[Forbes]] |language=en-gb |archive-date=27 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220727080607/https://www.forbes.com/sites/stevebaltin/2021/11/18/harry-styles-shows-why-he-is-musics-next-great-arena-rock-headliner-at-dazzling-la-gig/?sh=191972ff56e5 |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Cultural status==
{{Main|Cultural impact of Harry Styles}}

[[File:Harry Styles - Love On Tour @ Jeunesse Arena (52555729295) (cropped).jpg|thumb|291x291px|Styles on [[Love On Tour]] in 2022]]
Styles has been referred to as a [[pop icon]],<ref>{{cite news |date=9 December 2019 |title=New edition of Music Week out now |publisher=[[Music Week]] |url=https://www.musicweek.com/media/read/new-edition-of-music-week-out-now/078334 |url-status=live |access-date=9 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213185028/https://www.musicweek.com/media/read/new-edition-of-music-week-out-now/078334 |archive-date=13 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=17 July 2017 |title=Harry Styles interview: Dunkirk, power and politics |publisher=[[The Big Issue]] |url=https://www.bigissue.com/culture/film/harry-styles-talks-dunkirk-power-politics/ |url-status=live |access-date=17 July 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108101400/https://www.bigissue.com/culture/film/harry-styles-talks-dunkirk-power-politics/ |archive-date=8 January 2018}}</ref><ref name="MostWantedMan">{{cite magazine |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |date=22 August 2022 |title=How Harry Styles Became the World's Most Wanted Man |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-harrys-house-dont-worry-darling-my-policeman-cover-1397290/ |url-status=live |access-date=22 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220822115959/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-harrys-house-dont-worry-darling-my-policeman-cover-1397290/ |archive-date=22 August 2022}}</ref> a [[fashion icon]],<ref>{{cite news |date=3 December 2020 |title=How Harry Styles Became 2020's Biggest Fashion Icon |publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-harry-styles-became-2020s-biggest-style-icon-11606753389 |url-status=live |access-date=3 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220526235952/https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-harry-styles-became-2020s-biggest-style-icon-11606753389 |archive-date=26 May 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |date=1 February 2022 |title=21 times Harry Styles was a style icon |magazine=[[Vogue France]] |url=https://www.vogue.fr/vogue-hommes/fashion/diaporama/one-directions-harry-styles-best-looks/22900 |url-status=live |access-date=1 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220116140142/https://www.vogue.fr/vogue-hommes/fashion/diaporama/one-directions-harry-styles-best-looks/22900 |archive-date=16 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=6 September 2022 |title=Harry Styles Evolves From Heartthrob to Fashion Icon |publisher=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]] |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-09-06/harry-styles-evolves-from-heartthrob-to-fashion-icon |url-status=live |access-date=6 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220906172443/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-09-06/harry-styles-evolves-from-heartthrob-to-fashion-icon |archive-date=6 September 2022}}</ref> and a [[Cultural icon|global icon]].<ref>{{cite magazine |last= Piégay |first=Baptiste |date=4 December 2019 |title=Harry Styles is a Global Icon for the New Decade |magazine=[[L'Officiel USA]] |url=https://www.lofficielusa.com/gucci-beauty/harry-styles-fine-line-gucci-cover-story |url-status=live |access-date=14 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240623140004/https://www.lofficielusa.com/gucci-beauty/harry-styles-fine-line-gucci-cover-story |archive-date=23 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Farrell|first=Hannah|date=24 April 2024|title=Harry Styles' biggest career moments so far: From X Factor to global icon|url=https://hellorayo.co.uk/hits-radio/entertainment/music/harry-styles-career/|publisher=[[Bauer Media Audio UK#Rayo|Rayo]]|access-date=14 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=23 August 2023 |title=Olivia Wilde Says Harry Styles Left Crew 'In Tears' During ''Don't Worry Darling'' Filming |url=https://movieweb.com/olivia-wilde-says-harry-styles-left-crew-tears-during-dont-worry-darling-filming/ |access-date=14 July 2024 |publisher=[[MovieWeb]]}}</ref> He is considered to be among the most successful solo artists to have emerged from a band.<ref>{{cite news |date=20 May 2022 |title=From Beyoncé To Harry Styles, 10 Superstars Who Emerged From Bands |publisher=[[Grammy Awards]] |url=https://www.grammy.com/news/singers-from-bands-harry-styles-one-direction-solo-artists-beyonce-justin-timberlake-paul-mccartney |url-status=live |access-date=6 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220520202248/https://www.grammy.com/news/singers-from-bands-harry-styles-one-direction-solo-artists-beyonce-justin-timberlake-paul-mccartney |archive-date=20 May 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=26 July 2022 |title=Artists who left bands for successful solo careers |publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url=https://ew.com/music/artists-who-left-bands-for-successful-solo-careers/ |url-status=live |access-date=26 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220323202248/https://ew.com/music/artists-who-left-bands-for-successful-solo-careers/ |archive-date=23 March 2022}}</ref> Ben Beaumont-Thomas of ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that he is "a star who has negotiated one of the most difficult transitions in music – from boyband to solo artist – with more panache than even successful forebears such as [[Justin Timberlake]] and [[Robbie Williams]]."<ref>{{cite news |date=1 April 2022 |title=Harry Styles: As It Was review – a pop star in his own sunlit lane |work=[[The Guardian]] |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2022/apr/01/harry-styles-as-it-was-review-a-pop-star-in-his-own-sunlit-lane |url-status=live |access-date=1 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220401121624/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2022/apr/01/harry-styles-as-it-was-review-a-pop-star-in-his-own-sunlit-lane |archive-date=1 April 2022}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'' noted that with his third album, ''Harry's House'', Styles racked up a first-week vinyl sales count larger than anything any musician has managed before.<ref>{{cite news |last=McIntyre |first=Hugh |date=31 May 2022 |title=Harry Styles Is Doing Things No Musician Ever Has With His New Album |work=[[Forbes]] |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2022/05/31/harry-styles-is-doing-things-no-musician-has-in-history-with-his-new-album/?sh=12a79663d398 |access-date=31 May 2022 |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920163532/https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2022/05/31/harry-styles-is-doing-things-no-musician-has-in-history-with-his-new-album/?sh=12a79663d398 |url-status=live }}</ref>

He is one of the [[List of most-followed Twitter accounts|most-followed Twitter users]], with over 38 million followers as of 2022,<ref name="Twitter">{{cite news |last=Williamson |first=Harriet |title=Harry Styles has got it right about Twitter |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/harry-styles-twitter-olivia-wilde-abuse-b2151437.html |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=15 July 2024 |language=en |date=24 August 2022 |archive-date=28 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230428092515/https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/harry-styles-twitter-olivia-wilde-abuse-b2151437.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and has one of the most-followed [[Instagram]] accounts in the UK, with over 48 million followers as of 2024.<ref>{{cite news |last=Smith |first=Emily |title=Just 21 celebs Gypsy Rose Blanchard now has more followers than since leaving prison |url=https://thetab.com/uk/2024/01/15/just-21-celebs-gypsy-rose-blanchard-now-has-more-followers-than-since-leaving-prison-346057 |newspaper=[[The Tab]] |access-date=12 June 2024 |language=en |date=15 January 2024 |archive-date=12 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240612192701/https://thetab.com/uk/2024/01/15/just-21-celebs-gypsy-rose-blanchard-now-has-more-followers-than-since-leaving-prison-346057 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |last1= |first1= |title=Who Has The Most-Followers on Instagram-Top 10 |url=https://profiletree.com/who-has-the-most-followers-on-instagram-top-10/ |magazine=Profile Tree |access-date=23 April 2023 |language=en |date=14 April 2023 |archive-date=23 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423174343/https://profiletree.com/who-has-the-most-followers-on-instagram-top-10/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2022, his song "As It Was" was the most-streamed song of the year globally on [[Spotify]] and [[Deezer]], the second-most-streamed song globally on Apple Music, and the most-streamed song in the UK overall.<ref>{{cite news |last=Savage |first=Mark |title=Spotify Wrapped: Harry Styles had the most-streamed song of 2022 |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-63806914 |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=12 June 2024 |language=en |date=30 November 2022 |archive-date=17 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230917110538/https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-63806914 |url-status=live }}</ref> Styles was the second-most-searched musician on [[Google]] in 2022, after Taylor Swift.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Spinelli |first=Adrian |date=5 December 2022 |title=The Results Are In And Taylor Swift Is Atop The 10 Most Googled Artists Of 2022 |url=https://uproxx.com/pop/taylor-swift-most-googled-artist-2022/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230125190249/https://uproxx.com/pop/taylor-swift-most-googled-artist-2022/ |archive-date=25 January 2023 |access-date=12 June 2024 |website=[[Uproxx]]}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone UK]]'' named Styles the "new King of Pop" in 2022, following his groundbreaking year.<ref>{{cite web |last=Williams |first=Aaron |date=22 August 2022 |title=Michael Jackson Fans Fume After 'Rolling Stone' Calls Harry Styles 'The New King Of Pop' |website=[[Uproxx]] |url=https://uproxx.com/music/harry-styles-king-of-pop-michael-jackson-rolling-stone/ |access-date=14 July 2024 |archive-date=4 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220904061302/https://uproxx.com/music/harry-styles-king-of-pop-michael-jackson-rolling-stone/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="MostWantedMan" />

His fan base is known as "Harries."<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chilton |first1=Louis |title=Harry Styles' fan interactions aren't as heartwarming as you think – they're deeply unhealthy |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/harry-styles-olivia-wilde-dating-fan-proposal-b2152249.html |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |access-date=23 April 2023 |language=en |date=25 August 2022 |archive-date=23 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423175844/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/harry-styles-olivia-wilde-dating-fan-proposal-b2152249.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Due to his popularity, the singer has often fallen a victim of [[bottling (concert abuse)|bottling]],<ref>{{cite magazine |last1= |first1= |title=The long, strange history of people throwing stuff at Harry Styles |url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/harry-styles-fans-throwing-skittles |magazine=[[GQ]] |access-date=23 April 2023 |language=en |date=22 November 2022 |archive-date=5 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230705031044/https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/culture/article/harry-styles-fans-throwing-skittles |url-status=live }}</ref> frequently hitting him in the groin.<ref>{{cite web |date=27 February 2013 |title=A Brief History Of Harry Styles Getting Hit In The Balls With A Shoe |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/lyapalater/harry-styles-got-hit-in-the-balls-with-a-shoe |access-date=27 March 2015 |work=[[BuzzFeed]] |archive-date=1 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701234121/http://www.buzzfeed.com/lyapalater/harry-styles-got-hit-in-the-balls-with-a-shoe |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=27 February 2013 |title=Harry Styles Floored After Shoe Thrown By Fan |url=http://news.sky.com/story/1057767/harry-styles-floored-after-shoe-thrown-by-fan |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402170014/http://news.sky.com/story/1057767/harry-styles-floored-after-shoe-thrown-by-fan |archive-date=2 April 2015 |access-date=27 March 2015 |work=[[Sky News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Greenwood |first1=Carl |date=12 September 2015 |title=Wincing Harry Styles bottled in his special place by One Direction fans at concert |newspaper=[[Daily Mirror]] |publisher= |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/wincing-harry-styles-bottled-special-6430829 |access-date=20 September 2015 |archive-date=14 September 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150914233526/http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/wincing-harry-styles-bottled-special-6430829? |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=18 October 2022 |title=Watch Harry Styles Catch A Water Bottle To The Nuts |url=https://www.stereogum.com/2203158/watch-harry-styles-catch-a-water-bottle-to-the-nuts/news/ |website=[[Stereogum]] |access-date=23 April 2023 |archive-date=23 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423174342/https://www.stereogum.com/2203158/watch-harry-styles-catch-a-water-bottle-to-the-nuts/news/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Since One Direction's early years, a group of [[Shipping (fandom)|shipping]] [[Conspiracy theory|conspiracy theorist]] fans, often called "[[Larries]]," has been dedicated to proving that Styles and Louis Tomlinson, [[Name blending|name blended]] as "Larry Stylinson," are secretly a couple that has been [[closeted]] by a [[homophobia|homophobic]] music industry.<ref name="Vox2016">{{cite web |last=Romano |first=Aja |date=18 April 2016 |title=Larry Stylinson, the One Direction conspiracy theory that rules the internet, explained |url=https://www.vox.com/2016/4/18/11384118/larry-stylinson-one-direction-conspiracy-theory |access-date=11 June 2022 |website=[[Vox (website)|Vox]] |language=en |archive-date=20 April 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160420152107/https://www.vox.com/2016/4/18/11384118/larry-stylinson-one-direction-conspiracy-theory |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Queerbaiting and fandom" /><ref name="Everything I need I get from you">{{Cite book |last=Tiffany |first=Kaitlyn |title=Everything I need I get from you: how fangirls created the Internet as we know it |date=2022 |isbn=978-0-374-53918-4 |location=New York |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=381EEAAAQBAJ |oclc=1264273710 |publisher=[[Farrar, Straus and Giroux]] |access-date=21 June 2022 |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920171357/https://books.google.com/books?id=381EEAAAQBAJ |url-status=live }}</ref> Academics Clare Southerton and Hannah McCann connect the fan group to phenomena like [[Queering|queer reading]] and [[slash fiction]].<ref name="Queerbaiting and fandom">{{cite book |last1=Southerton |first1=Clare |last2=McCann |first2=Hannah |editor1-last=Brennan |editor1-first=Joseph |editor1-link=Joseph Brennan (author) |title=Queerbaiting and fandom: teasing fans through homoerotic possibilities |date=2019 |publisher=[[University of Iowa Press]] |location=Iowa City |isbn=9781609386726 |pages=161–163 |url=https://unsw-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/primo-explore/fulldisplay/unsworks_modsunsworks_66858/UNSWORKS |chapter=Queerbaiting and Real Person Slash: The Case of Larry Stylinson |access-date=3 June 2022 |archive-date=10 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220910112253/https://unsw-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/primo-explore/fulldisplay/unsworks_modsunsworks_66858/UNSWORKS |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Repetitions of Desire">{{cite journal |last1=McCann |first1=Hannah |last2=Southerton |first2=Clare |title=Repetitions of Desire: Queering the One Direction Fangirl |journal=[[Girlhood Studies]] |date=1 March 2019 |volume=12 |issue=1 |pages=49–65 |doi=10.3167/ghs.2019.120106 |s2cid=150794748 |url=https://www.proquest.com/docview/2273101426/5E77882B303F468EPQ |access-date=17 June 2022 |archive-date=20 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920172024/https://www.proquest.com/docview/2273101426/5E77882B303F468EPQ |url-status=live |hdl=1959.4/unsworks_62301 |hdl-access=free }}</ref> In 2016, the ship was labelled "one of the largest elements of the One Direction [[fandom]], which itself is one of the largest fandoms on the internet."<ref name="Vox2016" /> The theory, mainly proliferated on social media, has led to [[Cyberbullying|online bullying]] and harassment of Styles' and Tomlinson's friends, family, and girlfriends.<ref>{{cite web |last=Lucas |first=Jessica |title=Meet the TikTokers obsessed with Harry Styles' 'secret' love life |url=https://www.inputmag.com/culture/larries-larry-stylinson-tiktok-harry-styles-harrys-house-olivia-wilde |access-date=11 June 2022 |website=Input |language=en|date=10 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220528190938/https://www.inputmag.com/culture/larries-larry-stylinson-tiktok-harry-styles-harrys-house-olivia-wilde|archive-date=28 May 2022 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Vox2016" />

=== Legacy ===

Styles has inspired his fans to dress up for his concerts, leading ''[[Fashionista (website)|Fashionista]]'' to call the shows "his fans' [[Met Gala]]." Outfits often include sequins, pink cowboy hats, and feather boas<ref>{{cite news |last=Brannigan |first=Maura |title=Harry Styles Concerts Are His Fans' Met Gala |url=https://fashionista.com/2021/10/harry-styles-love-on-tour-outfit-ideas-2021 |access-date=1 July 2022 |website=[[Fashionista (website)|Fashionista]] |date=11 October 2021 |language=en |archive-date=29 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231029021431/https://fashionista.com/2021/10/harry-styles-love-on-tour-outfit-ideas-2021 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=8 July 2022 |title=How Harry Styles Fans Are Redefining Concert Fashion |publisher=[[Refinery29]] |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/harry-styles-love-on-tour-outfits |access-date=8 July 2022 |archive-date=8 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220708103739/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/harry-styles-love-on-tour-outfits |url-status=live }}</ref> and have been featured in ''Vogue'',<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Allaire |first=Christian |title=Harry Styles Threw the Best Halloween Party in New York |url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/harry-styles-harryween-halloween-concert |access-date=31 October 2021 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |date=31 October 2021 |language=en |archive-date=19 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211119080846/https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/harry-styles-harryween-halloween-concert |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'',<ref>{{cite web |last=La Ferla |first=Ruth |title=What Harry Styles Fans Wore for 'Harryween' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/11/01/style/harry-styles-halloween-costume.html |access-date=1 November 2021 |website=[[The New York Times]] |language=en |archive-date=2 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211102010903/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/11/01/style/harry-styles-halloween-costume.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and ''[[The New Yorker]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Rosner |first=Helen |title=Harry Styles Fans Put On a Show |url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/photo-booth/harry-styles-fans-put-on-a-show |access-date=14 September 2022 |magazine=[[The New Yorker]] |date=14 September 2022 |language=en |archive-date=14 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220914235029/https://www.newyorker.com/culture/photo-booth/harry-styles-fans-put-on-a-show |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2023, it was announced that [[Texas State University]] will be offering a course on Styles called "Harry Styles and the Cult of Celebrity: Identity, the Internet and European Pop Culture".<ref>{{cite news |date=19 July 2022 |title=Want to study Harry Styles? Consider this upcoming college course |publisher=[[CNN]] |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2022/07/19/entertainment/harry-styles-college-course-texas-cec/index.html |url-status=live |access-date=19 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220719165459/https://edition.cnn.com/2022/07/19/entertainment/harry-styles-college-course-texas-cec/index.html |archive-date=19 July 2022}}</ref>

Many musicians have expressed getting inspiration from Styles and their desire to work with him. Artists such as [[SZA]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Shutler |first=Ali |date=2022-12-17 |title=SZA's ''SOS'' could have featured Harry Styles, Billie Eilish and more |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/szas-sos-could-have-featured-harry-styles-billie-eilish-and-more-3368313 |access-date=2024-05-18 |magazine=[[NME]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> [[Miley Cyrus]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Devaney |first=Susan |date=2021-03-08 |title=Miley Cyrus Is Harry Styles's Number One Fan |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/miley-cyrus-harry-styles-instagram |access-date=2024-05-18 |magazine=[[British Vogue]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> [[Elton John]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Elton John is down to collaborate with Harry Styles: "That would be amazing" {{!}} ABC Audio Digital Syndication |url=https://digital.abcaudio.com/news/elton-john-down-collaborate-harry-styles-would-be-amazing |access-date=2024-05-18 |publisher=[[ABC Audio]]}}</ref> [[Shania Twain]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=James |first=Alastair |date=2023-02-03 |title=Shania Twain teases future collab with Harry Styles: 'I'd love to!' |url=https://www.attitude.co.uk/culture/shania-twain-teases-future-collab-with-harry-styles-424261/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |magazine=[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> [[Olivia Rodrigo]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-06-21 |title=5 artists that Olivia Rodrigo wants to collaborate with |url=https://www.musicmundial.com/en/2021/06/21/5-artists-that-olivia-rodrigo-wants-to-collaborate-with/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |language=en-US}}</ref> [[Chris Stapleton]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Dailey |first=Hannah |date=2024-05-17 |title=Chris Stapleton Reveals His Surprise Dua Lipa Duet at 2024 ACMs Came Together 'in the Last 2 Days' |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/chris-stapleton-dua-lipa-duet-2024-acm-awards-happened-2-days-1235686108/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |language=en-US}}</ref> [[Mark Ronson]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mark Ronson Would Like To Work With Harry Styles|url=https://www.antimusic.com/news/16/February/ts18Mark_Ronson_Would_Like_To_Work_With_Harry_Styles.shtml |access-date=2024-05-18 |website=AntiMusic}}</ref> [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=Halsey names Harry Styles as her dream collaboration |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/halsey-harry-styles-dream-collaboration/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |website=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]] |language=en}}</ref> [[Lorde]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Singh |first=Surej |date=2021-07-28 |title=Lorde reveals she wants to collaborate with Harry Styles |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/lorde-reveals-she-wants-to-collaborate-with-harry-styles-3004776 |access-date=2024-05-18 |magazine=[[NME]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> [[Matty Healy]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Smith |first=Amy |date=2019-01-03 |title="HMU if you wanna": Matty Healy uses Twitter to ask for a collaboration with Harry Styles |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/matty-healy-harry-styles-produce-new-album-the-1975-2426535 |access-date=2024-05-18 |magazine=[[NME]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> and [[Troye Sivan]] have all voiced their wishes to collaborate with Styles.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Bruce |first=Jasper |date=2020-12-10 |title=Listen to Troye Sivan's rework of 'Easy' featuring Kacey Musgraves and Mark Ronson |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/troye-sivan-reveals-release-date-for-mark-ronson-kacey-musgraves-collab-2835592 |access-date=2024-05-18 |magazine=[[NME]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> However, when asked about collaborating with other artists, Styles joked that he is an "antisocial musician."<ref>{{Cite web |title=Harry Styles Reveals He Felt 'Free' After Going Solo |url=https://kiisfm.iheart.com/content/2022-04-27-harry-styles-reveals-he-felt-free-after-going-solo/ |access-date=2024-05-18 |publisher=[[KIIS-FM]] |language=en}}</ref> Singer-songwriter [[Stevie Nicks]] likened his album ''Fine Line'' to [[Fleetwood Mac]]'s album ''[[Rumours (album)|Rumours]]'' (1977) and commented that she was inspired by him to write new music and poetry.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/stevie-nicks-harry-styles-coronavirus-letter-971517/|title=Stevie Nicks Calls Harry Styles' 'Fine Line' His 'Rumours' in COVID-19 PSA|magazine=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=23 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020|archive-date=23 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323171024/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/stevie-nicks-harry-styles-coronavirus-letter-971517/|url-status=live}}</ref>

Novels inspired by Styles include the ''[[After (Todd novel)|After]]'' series,<ref>{{cite web |last=Pham |first=Jason |date=12 April 2019 |title=How Anna Todd's Harry Styles Fanfiction Became a Bestselling Book—& Now a Movie |url=https://stylecaster.com/after-anna-todd-harry-styles-fanfiction/ |access-date=28 June 2022 |website=[[StyleCaster]] |language=en-US |archive-date=7 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107084431/https://stylecaster.com/after-anna-todd-harry-styles-fanfiction/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Grace and the Fever'',<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tiffany |first1=Kaitlyn |title=Grace and the Fever is a clear-eyed portrait of 'the girls of the internet' |url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/5/23/15676704/grace-and-the-fever-is-a-clear-eyed-portrait-of-the-girls-of-the-internet |website=[[The Verge]] |access-date=28 June 2022 |language=en |date=23 May 2017 |archive-date=27 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220627010401/https://www.theverge.com/2017/5/23/15676704/grace-and-the-fever-is-a-clear-eyed-portrait-of-the-girls-of-the-internet |url-status=live }}</ref> and ''The Idea of You''.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Ruiz |first1=Michelle |title=The Sleeper Hit of the Pandemic? A Three-Year-Old Romance Novel Inspired by Harry Styles |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/idea-of-you-book |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |access-date=28 June 2022 |date=28 December 2020 |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226161321/https://www.vogue.com/article/idea-of-you-book |url-status=live }}</ref> The ''After'' novels [[After (film series)|were turned into a film series]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kiang |first1=Jessica |title='After We Collided' Review: You Know, Maybe 'Twilight' Wasn't So Bad After All |url=https://variety.com/2020/film/reviews/after-we-collided-review-1234786022/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=6 December 2022 |date=1 October 2020 |archive-date=26 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226161448/https://variety.com/2020/film/reviews/after-we-collided-review-1234786022/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Anne Hathaway]] starred in the romantic comedy film ''[[The Idea of You]]'' (2024), an adaption of the novel.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Bucksbaum |first1=Sydney |title=Anne Hathaway to star in film adaptation of Harry Styles fan fiction The Idea of You |url=https://ew.com/movies/anne-hathaway-star-film-harry-styles-fan-fiction-the-idea-of-you/ |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=25 August 2022 |language=en |date=25 August 2022 |archive-date=2 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230202165124/https://ew.com/movies/anne-hathaway-star-film-harry-styles-fan-fiction-the-idea-of-you/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Children's books include ''Harry Styles: A Little Golden Book Biography''<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rovenstine |first1=Rebecca |title=Zendaya and Harry Styles Children's Books Are Available for Preorder |url=https://www.etonline.com/childrens-books-about-zendaya-and-harry-styles-are-available-for-preorder-now-and-theyre-just-6 |access-date=14 September 2024 |work=[[Entertainment Tonight]] |date=14 August 2024}}</ref> and ''Have You Heard of Harry Styles?''.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chan |first1=Tim |title=A New Harry Styles Children's Book Touts the Power of Positivity (and Personal Style) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lifestyle/shopping/have-you-heard-of-harry-styles-childrens-book-buy-online-1235830644/ |access-date=14 September 2024 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=20 February 2024}}</ref>

In June 2024, Styles' childhood village [[Holmes Chapel]] launched a 2.5-3 hour guided walking tour around the area.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=McNamee |first=Annie |date=2024-05-31 |title=You can now go on an official tour of Harry Styles' home village |url=https://www.timeout.com/uk/news/you-can-now-go-on-an-official-tour-of-harry-styles-home-village-053124 |access-date=2024-06-02 |magazine=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> The tour follows the bakery where Styles used to work, the Tremlow Viaduct featured in the One Direction documentary, ''[[One Direction: This Is Us]]'' (2013), where Styles signs his name, and other attractions.<ref name=":11">{{Cite news |last=Al-Othman |first=Hannah |date=2024-06-02 |title=This direction: Cheshire village launches Harry Styles tour for pop star's fans |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/article/2024/jun/02/this-direction-cheshire-village-launches-harry-styles-tour-for-pop-stars-fans |access-date=2024-06-02 |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The Holmes Chapel Partnership were forced to hire tour guides to cope with demand after 5,000 fans visited the village in 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Pennington |first=Josh |date=2024-06-01 |title="I wrote my dissertation on Harry Styles - now I run tours in his home village" |url=https://www.cheshire-live.co.uk/news/chester-cheshire-news/i-wrote-dissertation-harry-styles-29274978 |access-date=2024-06-02 |website=Cheshire Live |language=en}}</ref> There were over 150 applications for the role of a tour guide.<ref name=":11" /> [[Madame Tussauds]] wax museum has displayed a Styles wax figure since his time in One Direction, and as of 2023, Tussaud museums in several countries had a figure of him.<ref name="The Independent 18 July 2023">{{cite news |last1=Amber |first1=Raiken |title=Madame Tussauds unveils seven new wax figures of Harry Styles at different museums |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/madame-tussaunds-harry-styles-wax-figures-b2377545.html |access-date=4 March 2024 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=18 July 2023 |language=en}}</ref><ref name="Time Out London 29 June 2023">{{cite news |last1=Dubens |first1=Molly |title=A Harry Styles waxwork is coming to Madame Tussauds |url=https://www.timeout.com/london/news/a-harry-styles-waxwork-is-coming-to-madame-tussauds-062923 |access-date=4 March 2024 |work=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out London]] |date=29 June 2023}}</ref>

=== Fashion ===
{{Further|Blue Gucci dress of Harry Styles}}
Styles wore skinny jeans, sheer blouses, floral prints, flamboyant suits and ankle boots while in One Direction.<ref name="vogue">{{Cite news |last=Pike |first=Naomi |date=8 June 2017 |title=Harry Styles: Style Evolution |work=[[British Vogue]] |publisher=Condé Nast Britain |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/harry-styles-style-evolution |url-status=live |access-date=9 July 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710205032/http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/harry-styles-style-evolution |archive-date=10 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Key |first1=Christy |date=31 March 2018 |title=Harry Styles' Fashion Style Evolution: See 32 of the Pop Star's Best Looks |url=https://www.wmagazine.com/gallery/harry-styles-style-evolution/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920214158/https://www.wmagazine.com/gallery/harry-styles-style-evolution/ |archive-date=20 September 2020 |access-date=30 July 2020 |work=[[W (magazine)|W]]}}</ref> Nicole Saunders of ''Billboard'' noted that his fashion had "blossomed from a teen wearing purple [[Jack Wills]] hoodies to a carefully executed blend of '70s rock with a glamorous magpie feel" over the course of the group's five-year stint.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Saunders |first=Nicole |date=12 May 2017 |title=So Gucci: 8 of Harry Styles' Best Moments Wearing The Italian Brand |url=https://www.billboard.com/photos/7792087/so-gucci-8-of-harry-styles-best-moments-wearing-the-italian-brand |url-status=live |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707090201/http://www.billboard.com/photos/7792087/so-gucci-8-of-harry-styles-best-moments-wearing-the-italian-brand |archive-date=7 July 2017 |access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> Regarding Styles' time in One Direction, [[AllMusic]] writer Tim Sendra opined that his "charming persona and elastic vocals had him positioned as the [[Justin Timberlake|Timberlake]] of the group."<ref>{{cite web|last=Sendra|first=Tim|title=Harry Styles – Harry Styles – Songs, Reviews, Credits|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/harry-styles-mw0003041526|website=[[AllMusic]]|publisher=[[All Media Network]]|access-date=12 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170513041804/http://www.allmusic.com/album/harry-styles-mw0003041526|archive-date=13 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''{{'}}s Leah Greenblatt described him as "a dimpled, rakish prankster happy to wear the mantle of Class Clown."<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/music/2017/05/12/harry-styles-review/|title=Harry Styles pays tribute to his musical heroes on solo debut: EW review|last=Greenblatt|first=Leah|date=12 May 2017|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=12 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170512061435/http://ew.com/music/2017/05/12/harry-styles-review/|archive-date=12 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> During the band's 2014 ''Four'' era, Styles began collaborating with stylist [[Harry Lambert (stylist)|Harry Lambert]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=26 May 2022 |title=When Harry met Harry! The man who put Harry Styles in a dress |url=https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2022/may/26/when-harry-met-harry-the-man-who-put-harry-styles-in-a-dress |access-date=1 July 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |archive-date=10 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220710010920/https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2022/may/26/when-harry-met-harry-the-man-who-put-harry-styles-in-a-dress |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2016, he was featured in ''Another Man'' magazine,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anothermag.com/fashion-beauty/9114/the-making-of-another-man-with-harry-styles|title=The Making of Another Man With Harry Styles|last=Singer|first=Olivia|date=30 September 2016|website=[[Another Magazine|AnOther]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180919132207/http://www.anothermag.com/fashion-beauty/9114/the-making-of-another-man-with-harry-styles|archive-date=19 September 2018|url-status=live|access-date=19 September 2018}}</ref> after which Anne T. Donahue of ''[[The Guardian]]'' labelled him an "artthrob" who offers "something other than token shirtlessness" and telegraphs "an allegiance to the niche worlds of art and fashion rather than aiming for mainstream notoriety."<ref>{{cite web|last=Donahue|first=Anne T.|title=Harry Styles proves the heartthrob is dead: long live the artthrob|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/sep/27/harry-styles-one-direction-another-man-justin-beiber-heartthrob-image|website=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|access-date=16 October 2017|date=27 September 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170815184619/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2016/sep/27/harry-styles-one-direction-another-man-justin-beiber-heartthrob-image|archive-date=15 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''Billboard''{{'}}s Chris Payne opined that Styles' "vibe has always screamed rock star."<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7370490/harry-styles-solo-album-what-we-do-dont-want-hear-zayn-one-direction|title=Harry Styles' Solo Material: What We Do (And Don't) Want to Hear|last=Payne|first=Chris|date=25 March 2017|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=9 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170717003705/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7370490/harry-styles-solo-album-what-we-do-dont-want-hear-zayn-one-direction|archive-date=17 July 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

As a solo artist, Styles has opted for "candyfloss" custom pink suits, sequined tops, printed satin flares and a Gucci-heavy aesthetic.<ref name="vogue" /> ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''{{'}}s Erika Harwood stated that Styles went from "boy-bander" to "luxury suit connoisseur" in describing his change in style.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Harwood|first1=Erika|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2017/11/harry-styles-reveals-unlikely-fashion-inspiration|title=Harry Styles Reveals His Unlikely Fashion Inspiration|work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|url-access=limited|date=28 November 2017|access-date=13 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129084908/https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2017/11/harry-styles-reveals-unlikely-fashion-inspiration|archive-date=29 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> His style was noted as "flamboyant," "fashion-forward," and "fun."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tietjen |first1=Alexa |date=16 May 2017 |title=Harry Styles steps out in heels amid album release buzz |url=http://www.latimes.com/fashion/la-ig-wwd-harry-styles-heels-20170512-htmlstory.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171220225518/http://www.latimes.com/fashion/la-ig-wwd-harry-styles-heels-20170512-htmlstory.html |archive-date=20 December 2017 |access-date=13 September 2020 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref> Citing his use of the colour pink, Styles quoted English musician and [[The Clash]]'s bassist [[Paul Simonon]] in a ''Rolling Stone'' interview: "Pink is the only true rock & roll colour."<ref name="rolling stone" /> [[Ann Powers]] of NPR wrote that his fashion recalls the [[Spice Girls]]' "theatrical parade through pop's sartorial heritage" and that he "comforts with fashion's way of telling stories through artful accessories."<ref name="NPR HS" />
[[File:Dress worn by Styles on Vogue.jpg|thumb|upright|left|[[Blue Gucci dress of Harry Styles|Gucci dress worn by Styles]] on the cover of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' on display at the [[Victoria and Albert Museum|V&A Museum]]]]
Styles began wearing sweater vests, baggy high-waisted pants and pearl necklaces in 2019,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Eckardt |first1=Stephanie |date=18 December 2019 |title=We Need to Talk About Harry Styles's Pearl Necklace |url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/harry-styles-pearl-necklace/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201002005839/https://www.wmagazine.com/story/harry-styles-pearl-necklace/ |archive-date=2 October 2020 |access-date=13 September 2020 |work=[[W (magazine)|W]]}}</ref> which prompted Jacob Gallagher of ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' to call him the "popularizer of the manly pearl necklace."<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gallagher |first=Jacob |date=10 March 2020 |title=The Latest Must-Have Accessory for Men Is...a Pearl Necklace? |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-latest-must-have-accessory-for-men-is-a-pearl-necklace-11583868793 |url-status=live |url-access=subscription |access-date=30 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200619172614/https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-latest-must-have-accessory-for-men-is-a-pearl-necklace-11583868793 |archive-date=19 June 2020 |issn=0099-9660}}</ref> Tom Lamont of ''The Guardian'' noted that some of Styles' fashion choices have contributed to "an important political discussion about gendered fashion."<ref name="Lamont">{{cite web |last1=Lamont |first1=Tom |date=14 December 2019 |title=Harry Styles: 'I'm not just sprinkling in sexual ambiguity to be interesting' |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/14/harry-styles-sexual-ambiguity-dating-normals-rocking-a-dress |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214080236/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/dec/14/harry-styles-sexual-ambiguity-dating-normals-rocking-a-dress |archive-date=14 December 2019 |access-date=14 December 2019 |work=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref> In 2020, Styles became the first man to appear solo on the cover of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', for its December issue.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Heyward |first1=Giulia |last2=Ries |first2=Brian |date=13 November 2020 |title=Harry Styles becomes Vogue's first-ever solo male cover star |publisher=[[CNN]] |url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/harry-styles-vogue-cover-trnd/index.html |url-status=live |access-date=13 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113172706/https://www.cnn.com/style/article/harry-styles-vogue-cover-trnd/index.html/ |archive-date=13 November 2020}}</ref> Right-wing commentators criticised him for wearing [[Blue Gucci dress of Harry Styles|a blue Gucci dress]] on the cover;<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bianco |first1=Marcie |date=17 November 2020 |title=Candace Owens, Harry Styles' Vogue cover and the tyranny of the gender binary |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/think/opinion/candace-owens-harry-styles-vogue-cover-tyranny-gender-binary-ncna1247953 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204213516/https://www.nbcnews.com/think/opinion/candace-owens-harry-styles-vogue-cover-tyranny-gender-binary-ncna1247953 |archive-date=4 December 2020 |access-date=14 December 2020 |work=[[NBC News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Pitofsky |first1=Marina |date=2 December 2020 |title=Harry Styles hits back at criticism over wearing dress on Vogue cover |url=https://thehill.com/blogs/in-the-know/in-the-know/528394-harry-styles-hits-back-at-criticism-over-wearing-dress-on-vogue |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202195548/https://thehill.com/blogs/in-the-know/in-the-know/528394-harry-styles-hits-back-at-criticism-over-wearing-dress-on-vogue |archive-date=2 December 2020 |access-date=12 December 2020 |work=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]}}</ref> [[Candace Owens]] demanded that society must "Bring back manly men,"<ref>{{cite web |title=Candace Owens gets backlash from Harry Styles fans over 'bring back manly men' tweet |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/candace-owens-gets-backlash-harry-styles-fans-over-bring-back-n1247983 |access-date=1 July 2022 |work=[[NBC News]] |date=17 November 2020 |language=en |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701141643/https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/candace-owens-gets-backlash-harry-styles-fans-over-bring-back-n1247983 |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Ben Shapiro]] of ''[[The Daily Wire]]'' called the cover "a referendum on masculinity for men to don floofy dresses."<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Harry Styles Criticised for Wearing A Dress |url=https://www.vice.com/en/article/k7awnm/harry-styles-vogue-dress-ben-shapiro |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |date=17 November 2020 |language=en |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701143146/https://www.vice.com/en/article/k7awnm/harry-styles-vogue-dress-ben-shapiro |url-status=live }}</ref> Styles responded to the criticism by saying, "To not wear [something] because it's females' clothing, you shut out a whole world of great clothes" and "what's exciting about right now is you can wear what you like" as lines "are becoming more and more blurred."<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Halperin |first=Shirley |date=2 December 2020 |title=This Charming Man: Why We're Wild About Harry Styles |url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-fine-line-hitmaker-of-the-year-1234842744/ |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |language=en-US |archive-date=2 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202140100/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-fine-line-hitmaker-of-the-year-1234842744/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The decision to wear a dress, combined with his refusal to label his sexuality, have opened him up to accusations of [[queerbaiting]].<ref name=":10">{{cite magazine |last=Truman |first=Isabelle |title=Should Harry Styles Be Celebrated For Wearing A Dress? |url=https://graziamagazine.com/articles/harry-styles-wearing-dress-vogue-backlash/ |access-date=3 July 2022 |magazine=[[Grazia]] |language=en-US |archive-date=3 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220703232050/https://graziamagazine.com/articles/harry-styles-wearing-dress-vogue-backlash/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2022, the Gucci dress he wore on the cover of the magazine was incorporated into a [[Victoria and Albert Museum|V&A Museum]] exhibit called "Fashioning Masculinities: The Art of Menswear."<ref>{{Cite news |last=Rantala |first=Hanna |date=16 March 2022 |title=Menswear through the ages: V&A holds its first male fashion exhibition |language=en |work=[[Reuters]] |url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/menswear-through-ages-va-holds-its-first-male-fashion-exhibition-2022-03-16/ |access-date=1 July 2022 |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144711/https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/menswear-through-ages-va-holds-its-first-male-fashion-exhibition-2022-03-16/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Several of Styles' other outfits have been displayed in museums, including a blue velvet suit in the [[Rock and Roll Hall of Fame]], linen trousers at the [[Design Museum]], and a leather suit in the [[Grammy Museum at L.A. Live]].<ref>{{cite magazine |date=23 September 2020 |title=Harry Styles's Blue Gucci Suit Is Going Into a Museum |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/harry-styles-blue-gucci-suit-is-going-into-a-museum |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Teen Vogue]] |language=en-US |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144712/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/harry-styles-blue-gucci-suit-is-going-into-a-museum |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Grein |first=Paul |date=15 July 2021 |title=Outfits Worn at 2021 Grammys & 2020 Latin Grammys on Display at Grammy Museum |url=https://www.billboard.com/photos/2021-grammys-2020-latin-grammys-fashion-grammy-museum/ |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |language=en-US |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144711/https://www.billboard.com/photos/2021-grammys-2020-latin-grammys-fashion-grammy-museum/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=REBEL: 30 Years of London Fashion |url=https://designmuseum.org/exhibitions/rebel-30-years-of-london-fashion |access-date=2024-05-13 |publisher=[[Design Museum]] |language=en }}</ref> 
[[File:Harry Styles Cardigan at The Victoria and Albert Museum.jpg|thumb|[[JW Anderson]] cardigan worn by Styles on display at The [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] in London.]]
Styles frequently spotlights the work of small designers.<ref name="ls" /><ref>{{cite magazine |date=13 November 2020 |title=Harris Reed Is Harry Styles's Secret Fashion Weapon—And They Can Be Yours Too |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/harris-reed-harry-styles |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |language=en-US |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144711/https://www.vogue.com/article/harris-reed-harry-styles |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |date=29 October 2020 |title=Introducing S.S. Daley, the Brand Behind Harry Styles's "Golden" Look |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/ss-daley-fashion-designer-harry-styles-golden |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |language=en-US |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144711/https://www.vogue.com/article/ss-daley-fashion-designer-harry-styles-golden |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |date=13 November 2020 |title=From College to a Vogue Cover Story, Harry Styles and Bode Celebrate Senior Cords |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-bode-senior-cord |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |language=en-US |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144711/https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-bode-senior-cord |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |title=Meet Emily Bode, The Designer Loved By Harry Styles, Emma Corrin And Jay-Z |url=https://graziadaily.co.uk/fashion/news/emily-bode-designer/ |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Grazia]] |date=5 December 2021 |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144711/https://graziadaily.co.uk/fashion/news/emily-bode-designer/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":8">{{cite magazine |date=23 June 2022 |title=Meet Arturo Obegero—The Spanish Designer Dressing Harry Styles Put on His Second Show in Paris Today |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/spanish-designer-arturo-obegero-dressing-harry-styles |access-date=1 July 2022 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |language=en-US |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701144712/https://www.vogue.com/article/spanish-designer-arturo-obegero-dressing-harry-styles |url-status=live }}</ref> He has  been credited with increasing sales and attention for smaller brands such as [[Bode (fashion brand)|Bode]], Éliou, Egonlab, S.S. Daley, [[Daniel W. Fletcher]], Marco Ribeiro and Arturo Obegero.<ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Cary |first=Alice |date=2020-11-25 |title=Éliou Is The Independent Brand Behind Harry Styles's Playful Pearls |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/fashion/article/eliou-jewellery-harry-styles |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[British Vogue]] |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Chitrakorn |first=Kati |date=2022-09-27 |title=Why Harry Styles is putting his weight behind designer Marco Ribeiro |url=https://www.voguebusiness.com/beauty/harry-styles-beauty-brand-pleasing-marco-ribeiro-to-unveil-collab-at-paris-fashion-week |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[Vogue Business]] |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last2=van den Broeke |first1=Zak |last1=Maoui |first2=Teo |date=2020-12-02 |title=Daniel W Fletcher on Harry Styles: "I really owe a lot to Mr Styles" |url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/fashion/article/daniel-fletcher-harry-styles |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]] |language=en-GB }}</ref><ref name=":8" /><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Maoui |first=Zak |date=2023-02-06 |title=At the Grammys, Harry Styles supercharged the next big cult brand |url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/fashion/article/harry-styles-egonlab-grammys-2023 |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> During [[COVID-19 lockdowns|lockdown]], a [[JW Anderson]] cardigan that Styles wore in a 2020 rehearsal for ''[[Today (American TV program)|Today]]'' went viral on [[TikTok]] as Anderson provided the pattern for free online.<ref name=":2">{{cite news |author=Oscar Holland |title=The V&A museum has acquired the Harry Styles cardigan that sparked a TikTok craze |url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/harry-styles-cardigan-va-museum/index.html |access-date=1 July 2022 |publisher=[[CNN]] |language=en |archive-date=21 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230321125644/https://www.cnn.com/style/article/harry-styles-cardigan-va-museum/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> The V&A Museum acquired the cardigan for its permanent collection in November 2020, calling the viral craze a "cultural phenomenon that speaks to the power of creativity and social media in bringing people together in times of extreme adversity."<ref name=":2" />

Having won the British Style Award at the [[The Fashion Awards#2013|2013 Fashion Awards]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Denley |first1=Susan |date=3 December 2013 |title=Harry Styles of One Direction wins British Style Award |url=https://www.latimes.com/fashion/la-xpm-2013-dec-03-la-ar-harry-styles-british-style-award-20131202-story.html |url-access=limited |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203142921/http://articles.latimes.com/2013/dec/03/news/la-ar-harry-styles-british-style-award-20131202 |archive-date=3 December 2017 |access-date=13 September 2020 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref> Styles placed fourth on ''[[British GQ]]''{{'}}s 2018 list of 50 best-dressed men, in which fashion designer [[Michael Kors]] deemed him "the modern embodiment of British rocker style: edgy, flamboyant and worn with unapologetic swagger."<ref name="British GQ">{{cite magazine |date=2 January 2018 |title=GQ's 50 best-dressed men 2018 |url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/gallery/the-gq-best-dressed-men-2018 |url-status=live |magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]] |publisher=Condé Nast Britain |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103071554/http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/gallery/the-gq-best-dressed-men-2018 |archive-date=3 January 2018 |access-date=2 January 2018 }}</ref> In 2020, he was voted ''[[GQ]]''{{'}}s "Most Stylish Man of the Year."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/most-stylish-man-2020|title=Harry Styles Is the Most Stylish Man of the Year, as Voted By You|work=[[GQ]]|date=18 December 2020|access-date=18 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218175149/https://www.gq.com/story/most-stylish-man-2020|archive-date=18 December 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles was also ranked first and fifth on ''[[British Vogue]]''{{'}}s "The 50 Fittest Boys" list in 2016 and 2017, respectively,<ref>{{cite news |last=Pike |first=Naomi |date=17 August 2017 |title=The 50 Fittest Boys Of 2017 |work=[[British Vogue]] |publisher=Condé Nast Britain |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/2017-hot-boys |url-status=live |access-date=17 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818091328/http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/2017-hot-boys |archive-date=18 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Pike |first=Naomi |date=1 July 2016 |title=The 50 Fittest Boys Of 2016 |work=[[British Vogue]] |publisher=Condé Nast Britain |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/hot-guys-2016 |url-status=live |access-date=1 July 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160829113146/http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/hot-guys-2016 |archive-date=29 August 2016}}</ref> and was voted the "Sexiest Male in Pop" for three consecutive years between 2016 and 2018 in a poll by British radio network [[Capital London|Capital]].<ref>{{cite web |author1=Capital |date=12 August 2018 |title=Capital's Sexiest Male & Female In Pop 2018: The Winners |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/sexiest-male-female-2018-results/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818152257/https://www.capitalfm.com/news/sexiest-male-female-2018-results/ |archive-date=18 August 2018 |access-date=18 August 2018 |publisher=[[Capital London]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author1=Capital |date=6 August 2017 |title=Capital's Sexiest Male & Female In Pop Have Been Revealed! |publisher=[[Capital London]] |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/news/sexiest-male-female-pop-2017/ |url-status=live |access-date=6 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206150929/http://www.capitalfm.com/news/sexiest-male-female-pop-2017/ |archive-date=6 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=5 August 2016 |title=Capital's SEXIEST Male In Pop 2016: The Winners |publisher=[[Capital London]] |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/features/sexy-male-popstars-celebrities-2016/ |url-status=live |access-date=6 August 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180303020115/http://www.capitalfm.com/features/sexy-male-popstars-celebrities-2016/ |archive-date=3 March 2018}}</ref> In 2020, he was named the most influential man in fashion.<ref>{{cite magazine |date=17 November 2020 |title=Harry Styles is the most influential man in fashion in 2020 |magazine=[[Vogue France]] |url=https://www.vogue.fr/vogue-hommes-en/article/harry-styles-lyst-most-influential-man-fashion-2020 |access-date=17 November 2020 |archive-date=18 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118062818/https://www.vogue.fr/vogue-hommes-en/article/harry-styles-lyst-most-influential-man-fashion-2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''GQ'' named Styles the best-dressed musician in the world.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Maoui |first=Zak |date=2019-05-03 |title=It's official: Harry Styles is the best-dressed musician in the world |url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/gallery/harry-styles-best-fashion-moments |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> Styles was inducted as part of the Business of Fashion's Class of 2022, a definitive index of people shaping the global fashion industry.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Harry Styles {{!}} BoF 500 {{!}} The People Shaping the Global Fashion Industry |url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/community/people/harry-styles |access-date=2024-05-13 |website=[[Business of Fashion]] |date=17 November 2023 |language=en-GB}}</ref>

In 2022, Styles designed a joint capsule collection with Gucci's then-creative designer Alessandro Michele entitled "Ha Ha Ha" after their first initials and the way they traditionally signed off their messages to one another over the years.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2022-06-20 |title=Harry Styles And Alessandro Michele Have Collaborated On A Gucci Collection |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/news/article/harry-styles-gucci-collection |access-date=2024-05-13 |magazine=[[British Vogue]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> Unveiled at [[Milan Fashion Week]], the collection included tailored wool and velvet suits, tweed trench coats, tartan kilts, bowling shirts, and printed pyjamas.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2022-06-20 |title="This Collection Is a True Act of Love"—Alessandro Michele on His Gucci Ha Ha Ha Collab With Harry Styles |url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/gucci-ha-ha-ha-harry-styles-capsule |access-date=2024-05-13 |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |language=en-US}}</ref>

Styles has been credited for multiple trends and different waves of items' popularity within fashion. He has been attributed to the popularization of items such as pearl necklaces, [[Aloha shirt|Hawaiian shirts]], crochet garments, [[chelsea boot]]s, [[Boa (clothing accessory)|feather boas]], and wide leg trousers.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Marain |first=Alexandre |date=2020-07-17 |title=Could pearls be the biggest men's jewelry trend of 2020? |url=https://www.vogue.fr/vogue-hommes-en/article/mens-jewelry-trends-pearls-2020 |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[Vogue France]] |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Cary |first=Alice |date=2021-01-07 |title=8 Style Obsessions We Can Thank Harry Styles For |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/fashion/gallery/harry-styles-trends |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[British Vogue]] |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Gustashaw |first=Megan |date=2017-07-18 |title=Chelsea Boots Literally Get Harry Styles' Heart Racing |url=https://www.gq.com/story/harry-styles-loves-chelsea-boots-more-than-we-thought |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[GQ]] |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Harry Styles' Grammy outfits spark huge rise in sales of feather boas |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/features/harry-styles-grammys-outfit-feather-boa/ |access-date=2024-05-31 |publisher=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Quill |first=Heidi |date=2020-03-31 |title=Ten pieces from Harry Styles' wardrobe that you can (and should) add to your own |url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/fashion/article/how-to-dress-like-harry-styles |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> In 2023 Styles was credited alongside [[Beyoncé]] and [[Taylor Swift]] for the rise in elaborate concert dressing, emulating fan culture of the 60s.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-07-26 |title=Why fans dress up for Taylor Swift, Beyoncé and Harry Styles |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-66244480 |access-date=2024-05-31 |work=[[BBC News]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> After Styles wore [[Adidas Gazelle]]s as part of every concert outfit on Love On Tour, [[Adidas]] officially renamed the shoes on their web store to "Satellite Stompers" in honour of Styles reviving the shoe and his fans' nickname.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-07-31 |title=Adidas has actually renamed Gazelle trainers to 'Satellite stompers' in honour of Harry Styles |url=https://thetab.com/uk/2023/07/31/adidas-has-actually-renamed-gazelle-trainers-to-satellite-stompers-in-honour-of-harry-styles-319917 |access-date=2024-05-31 |newspaper=[[The Tab]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> In 2024, Styles invested in a minority stake in emerging British fashion label S.S. Daley.<ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Connor |first=Tamison |date=2024-01-11 |title=Harry Styles Invests in S.S. Daley |url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/news/luxury/harry-styles-invests-in-ss-daley/ |website=[[Business of Fashion]] |language=en |url-status=live |access-date=15 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240513105718/https://www.businessoffashion.com/news/luxury/harry-styles-invests-in-ss-daley/ |archive-date=13 May 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Styles splits his time between two homes in [[North London]], having previously lived above the [[Sunset Strip]] in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=David |first1=Mark |title=Harry Styles Takes Huge Hit on Sale of Sunset Strip Home |url=https://variety.com/2019/dirt/real-estalker/harry-styles-sunset-strip-one-direction-1203273049/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |access-date=27 November 2019 |date=19 July 2019 |archive-date=25 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225044905/https://variety.com/2019/dirt/real-estalker/harry-styles-sunset-strip-one-direction-1203273049/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He sold his Los Angeles residence, having become disillusioned with the city.<ref name=VarietyLovesHarry>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-fine-line-hitmaker-of-the-year-1234842744/|title=This Charming Man: Why We're Wild About Harry Styles|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=2 December 2020|last=Halperin|first=Shirley|access-date=15 December 2020|archive-date=14 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214214618/https://variety.com/2020/music/news/harry-styles-fine-line-hitmaker-of-the-year-1234842744/|url-status=live}}</ref> He also owns a loft apartment in [[Manhattan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.homesandproperty.co.uk/luxury/celebrity-homes/harry-styles-buys-second-north-london-house-88-million-property-is-a-stones-throw-from-one-direction-a131946.html|title=Harry Styles buys £8.8m semi near first north London property|date=11 July 2019|website=Homes and Property|access-date=14 May 2020|archive-date=16 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200416101050/https://www.homesandproperty.co.uk/luxury/celebrity-homes/harry-styles-buys-second-north-london-house-88-million-property-is-a-stones-throw-from-one-direction-a131946.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He lived in the attic of producer Ben Winston's home in [[Hampstead Heath]], London, for 20 months at the beginning of his career while he looked for his own house.<ref name="rolling stone" />

Styles believes in [[karma]], and when [[Chelsea Handler]] asked if he believes in God, he stated that he considered himself to be "[[more spiritual than religious]]" and that it is "naïve to say nothing exists and there's nothing above us or more powerful than us."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Handler |first1=Chelsea |author-link=Chelsea Handler|title=Harry Styles on LA Life, His Love Life and the After-Life |url=https://www.anothermanmag.com/life-culture/10172/harry-styles-on-la-life-his-love-life-and-the-after-life |website=[[Another Man]] |access-date=1 February 2018 |date=24 January 2020 |archive-date=4 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180204080847/http://www.anothermanmag.com/life-culture/10172/harry-styles-on-la-life-his-love-life-and-the-after-life |url-status=live }}</ref> 
In a 2020 interview with ''Vogue'', Styles shared that he practices [[pilates]] and meditates daily.<ref name=":12">{{Cite magazine|last=Bowles|first=Hamish|title=Playtime With Harry Styles|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-cover-december-2020|magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|date=13 November 2020|access-date=6 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301124833/https://www.vogue.com/article/harry-styles-cover-december-2020|archive-date=1 March 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> He also attends therapy regularly.<ref name="ls" />

He told ''Vogue'' in the same interview that he followed a [[Pescetarianism|pescatarian]] diet.<ref name=":12" /> In 2022, when fans started throwing chicken nuggets onstage during a concert and chanted that he should eat one, he told them, "I don't eat chicken, sorry. I don't eat meat," earning him [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]]'s 2022 Best Viral Moment for Animals Award.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-wins-peta-2022-best-viral-moment-for-animals-award-1235179516/|title=Nothing to Cluck About: Harry Styles Wins PETA's 2022 Best Viral Moment for Animals Award|last=Dailey|first=Hannah|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=1 December 2022|access-date=11 June 2024|archive-date=4 December 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221204190425/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-wins-peta-2022-best-viral-moment-for-animals-award-1235179516/|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles confirmed in 2017 that he has [[polythelia]], a condition where a person has more than two [[nipple]]s.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 July 2017 |title=Harry Styles Has Four Nipples, and That's More Common Than You Think |url=https://www.allure.com/story/harry-styles-confirms-he-has-four-nipples |access-date=17 January 2023 |website=Allure |language=en-US |archive-date=17 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230117005348/https://www.allure.com/story/harry-styles-confirms-he-has-four-nipples |url-status=live }}</ref>

In May 2019, Styles was named second on the [[Sunday Times Rich List|''Sunday Times'' Rich List]] of musicians in the UK under 30, with an estimated net worth of £58&nbsp;million, having previously featured third on the previous year's list with an estimated net worth of £50&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/who-is-the-richest-one-direction-member |title=How Did Harry Styles Become So Much Richer Than The Rest Of One Direction? |last=Pike |first=Naomi |work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |date=11 May 2019 |access-date=11 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190512033936/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/who-is-the-richest-one-direction-member |archive-date=12 May 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://businessinsider.com/richest-young-musicians-in-britain-2018-sunday-times-rich-list-2018-5/ |title=The 11 richest young musicians in Britain |last=Dodgson |first=Lindsay |work=[[Business Insider]] |date=10 May 2018 |access-date=11 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180510132609/http://www.businessinsider.com/richest-young-musicians-in-britain-2018-sunday-times-rich-list-2018-5 |archive-date=10 May 2018 }}</ref> He maintained his second-place position on the list in 2020 and 2021, with estimated net worths of £63&nbsp;million and £75&nbsp;million, respectively.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.itv.com/news/anglia/2020-05-13/ed-sheeran-tops-young-musicians-rich-list-for-second-year-running/|title=Ed Sheeran tops young musicians rich list for second year running|work=[[ITV (network)|ITV]]|date=13 May 2020|access-date=13 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200513142009/https://www.itv.com/news/anglia/2020-05-13/ed-sheeran-tops-young-musicians-rich-list-for-second-year-running/|archive-date=13 May 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/sir-paul-mccartney-tops-sunday-times-2021-music-rich-list-as-calvin-harris-and-ed-sheeran-vault-into-top-10__33205/|title=Sir Paul McCartney tops Sunday Times' 2021 Music Rich List as Calvin Harris and Ed Sheeran vault into Top 10|work=[[Official Charts Company|Official Charts]]|date=21 May 2021|access-date=23 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210521094606/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/sir-paul-mccartney-tops-sunday-times-2021-music-rich-list-as-calvin-harris-and-ed-sheeran-vault-into-top-10__33205/|archive-date=21 May 2021|url-status=live}}</ref> He topped the list in 2022, becoming the richest musician under 30 in the UK, with his net worth being estimated at £100&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/40-richest-musicians-uk-harry-styles-adele-sunday-times-rich-list-qfj8blmhf |title=The 40 richest musicians in the UK |last=Dean |first=Jonathan |work=[[The Sunday Times]] |date=20 May 2022 |access-date=20 May 2022 |archive-date=20 May 2022 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20220520063633/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/40-richest-musicians-uk-harry-styles-adele-sunday-times-rich-list-qfj8blmhf |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2023, Styles was estimated to be worth £150 million, placed this year jointly at 13th position in a new list headed "35 richest people under 35 in the UK."<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/35-under-35-sunday-times-rich-list-bmfxj9w9g | title=35 richest people under 35 in the UK | work=[[The Sunday Times]] | date=21 May 2023 | access-date=23 July 2023 | archive-date=23 July 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230723090825/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/35-under-35-sunday-times-rich-list-bmfxj9w9g | url-status=live }}</ref> ''The Times'' estimated Styles' wealth to be £175 million in 2024, placing 17th on the "40 under 40" list and the second richest young musician in the UK after [[Ed Sheeran]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Times |first=The Sunday |date=2024-05-17 |title=Harry Styles net worth — Sunday Times Rich List 2024 |newspaper=[[The Times]] |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/harry-styles-net-worth-sunday-times-rich-list-gcp6wlc2d |access-date=2024-05-18 |language=en |issn=0140-0460}}</ref>
