=== Tattoos ===
Styles is heavily tattooed, having got his first one at 18 years old; the most prominent of which is a large butterfly on his sternum.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fuentes |first=Tamara |date=2021-11-22 |title=A Complete Guide to (Almost) All of Harry Styles' Tattoos |url=https://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/g25381647/harry-styles-tattoos/ |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=Seventeen}}</ref> Styles' primary tattoo artist Liam Sparkes stated the butterfly on Styles' torso is "based on an old French prison tattoo inspired by the film ''[[Papillon (1973 film)|Papillon]]'' (1973)."<ref name=":9">{{Cite magazine |last=Johnston |first=Kathleen |date=2020-02-01 |title=The unknown story behind Harry Styles '17 Black' tattoo |url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/grooming/article/harry-styles-tattoos |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]] |language=en-GB}}</ref> He got tattooed on television as a dare on ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Lawson |first=Richard |date=2015-12-04 |title=Harry Styles Got a New Tattoo on Television Last Night |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/12/harry-styles-tattoo-late-late-show-james-corden |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |language=en-US}}</ref> His tattoos include the [[Green Bay Packers]] logo, [[swallow]]s, "[[New York City|NY]], [[Los Angeles|LA]], [[London|LDN]]," a padlock tattooed on him by Ed Sheeran, "never gonna dance again" (lyrics from the song "[[Careless Whisper]]" by [[George Michael]]), [[Brazil|Brasil!]], a naked mermaid, the cover art of the album ''The Dark Side of the Moon'' by Pink Floyd, his parents' birth years and various tattoos related to family members, and a tiny cross.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=2021-03-03 |title=Harry Styles Has Way More Tattoos Than You Realize |url=https://www.menshealth.com/entertainment/a35709879/harry-styles-tattoos/ |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[Men's Health]] |language=en-US}}</ref> Styles has "17 Black" below his left clavicle after losing money gambling in Australia on 17 black and shares matching work of the children's character [[Pingu]] with Ed Sheeran.<ref name=":9" /> He also shares a matching half a heart tattoo with Caleb Followill of [[Kings of Leon]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Britton |first=Luke Morgan |date=2016-10-14 |title=Kings Of Leon drummer has matching tattoo with Harry Styles |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/kings-of-leon-343-1555151 |access-date=2024-05-31 |magazine=[[NME]] |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Relationships===
From November 2011 to January 2012, 17-year-old Styles dated television presenter [[Caroline Flack]]; their relationship stirred controversy, as she was 14 years older than Styles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/style/celebrity/celebrity-news/caroline-flack-on-harry-styles-romance-it-was-a-laugh-until-i-started-being-called-paedophile-in-the-street-31599690.html|title=Caroline Flack on Harry Styles romance: 'It was a laugh, until I started being called paedophile in the street'|last=Drohan|first=Freya|date=11 October 2015|newspaper=[[Irish Independent]]|access-date=20 October 2017|archive-date=30 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190530032537/https://www.independent.ie/style/celebrity/celebrity-news/caroline-flack-on-harry-styles-romance-it-was-a-laugh-until-i-started-being-called-paedophile-in-the-street-31599690.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He briefly dated American singer-songwriter [[Taylor Swift]] later in 2012,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/what-to-listen-to/harry-styles-finally-opens-taylor-swift-relationships-hard/|title=Harry Styles finally opens up about Taylor Swift: 'Relationships are hard - but her songs are bloody good'|newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=18 April 2017|access-date=15 December 2019|archive-date=15 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215085559/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/what-to-listen-to/harry-styles-finally-opens-taylor-swift-relationships-hard/|url-status=live}}</ref> leading to fan and media speculation about them writing songs about each other after their breakup.<ref name="rolling stone" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Bricker |first=Tierney |date=28 October 2023 |title=All the Songs Taylor Swift and Harry Styles (Allegedly) Wrote About Their Romance |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1388826/all-the-songs-taylor-swift-and-harry-styles-allegedly-wrote-about-their-romance |access-date=12 August 2024 |website=[[E! News]]}}</ref> From 2013 to 2016, Styles dated model [[Kendall Jenner]] and later cited her as one of the muses of his debut album.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=21 November 2022 |last=Wurzburger |first=Andrea |title=Harry Styles and Kendall Jenner's Relationship: A Look Back |url=https://people.com/celebrity/harry-styles-kendall-jenner-dating-history/ |access-date=11 June 2024 |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |archive-date=3 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230603131321/https://people.com/celebrity/harry-styles-kendall-jenner-dating-history/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

From 2017 to 2018, Styles was in a relationship with French-American model [[Camille Rowe]], who inspired ''Fine Line''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/dating/harry-styles-camille-rowe-relationship-timeline|title=Harry Styles & Camille Rowe's Relationship Timeline Is Mysterious|last=Sullivan|first=Corinne|date=13 December 2019|work=[[Elite Daily]]|url-status=live|access-date=11 June 2024|archive-date=22 February 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240222062303/https://www.elitedaily.com/dating/harry-styles-camille-rowe-relationship-timeline}}</ref><ref name="Sheffield">{{cite magazine |last=Sheffield |first=Rob |author-link=Rob Sheffield |title=The Eternal Sunshine of Harry Styles |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-cover-interview-album-871568/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=11 June 2024 |date=26 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312192700/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-cover-interview-album-871568/ |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> From January 2021 to November 2022, Styles was in a relationship with actress and director [[Olivia Wilde]], whom he met on the set of ''Don't Worry Darling''.<ref>{{Cite magazine |date=6 May 2024 |last=Briese |first=Nicole |title=Harry Styles and Olivia Wilde's Relationship Timeline |url=https://people.com/music/harry-styles-olivia-wilde-relationship-timeline/ |access-date=11 June 2024 |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |archive-date=27 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240327155420/https://people.com/music/harry-styles-olivia-wilde-relationship-timeline/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Rolling Stone'' said in 2022, "If Styles is already held up to a high standard, his potential partners are held to an unreachable one for some of his fans."<ref name="How Harry Styles Became the World's Most Wanted Man">{{cite magazine |last1=Spanos |first1=Brittany |title=How Harry Styles Became the World's Most Wanted Man |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-harrys-house-dont-worry-darling-my-policeman-cover-1397290/ |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=6 September 2022 |date=22 August 2022 |archive-date=26 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220926175244/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/harry-styles-harrys-house-dont-worry-darling-my-policeman-cover-1397290/ |url-status=live }}</ref> From June 2023 to May 2024, Styles dated Canadian actress [[Taylor Russell]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Aizin |first=Rebecca |date=20 May 2024 |title=Harry Styles and Taylor Russell's Relationship Timeline |url=https://people.com/harry-styles-taylor-russell-relationship-timeline-7975617 |access-date=11 June 2024 |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |archive-date=10 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240610125905/https://people.com/harry-styles-taylor-russell-relationship-timeline-7975617 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Sexuality===
Styles has been repeatedly asked about his [[sexual orientation]] in interviews since he was 19 years old.<ref name="ls"/><ref name="Lamont" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":7">{{cite web |last=McNamara |first=Brittney |date=15 May 2017 |title=Harry Styles Says He's Never Labeled His Sexuality |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/harry-styles-does-not-label-sexuality |access-date=1 July 2022 |website=[[Teen Vogue]] |language=en-US |archive-date=1 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220701124504/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/harry-styles-does-not-label-sexuality |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Harry Styles: the boy is back |url=https://theface.com/music/harry-styles-feature-interview-music-stevie-nicks-elton-john-alessandro-michele-volume-4-issue-001 |access-date=1 July 2022 |website=The Face |date=5 September 2019 |language=en-gb |archive-date=9 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220709123825/https://theface.com/music/harry-styles-feature-interview-music-stevie-nicks-elton-john-alessandro-michele-volume-4-issue-001 |url-status=live }}</ref> When asked in a 2013 interview with ''British GQ'' whether he was bisexual, he replied, "Bisexual? Me? I don't think so. I'm pretty sure I'm not."<ref name=":1">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/one-direction-gq-covers-interview|title=This One Direction interview got us death threats|last=Heaf|first=Jonathan|magazine=[[GQ|British GQ]]|date=24 August 2015|access-date=15 December 2019|archive-date=20 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120121609/https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/article/one-direction-gq-covers-interview|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2017, when asked if he labelled his sexuality, he said, "No, I've never felt the need to really. I don't feel like it's something I've ever felt like I have to explain about myself."<ref name=":7" />

When ''The Guardian'' in 2019 questioned the authenticity of his flamboyant dressing style and his perceived sexual ambiguity, he stated:
{{blockquote|Am I sprinkling in nuggets of sexual ambiguity to try and be more interesting? No. ... In terms of how I wanna dress, and what the album sleeve's gonna be, I tend to make decisions in terms of collaborators I want to work with. I want things to look a certain way. Not because it makes me look gay, or it makes me look straight, or it makes me look bisexual, but because I think it looks cool. And more than that, I dunno, I just think sexuality's something that's fun. Honestly? I can't say I've given it any more thought than that.<ref name="Lamont"/>}}

In a 2022 interview with ''[[Better Homes and Gardens (magazine)|Better Homes and Gardens]]'', Styles stated that the expectation that he should publicly label his sexual orientation is "outdated." He said, "I've been really open with it with my friends, but that's my personal experience; it's mine," and "the whole point of where we should be heading, which is toward accepting everybody and being more open, is that it doesn't matter, and it's about not having to label everything, not having to clarify what boxes you're checking."<ref name=ls>{{cite web |date=26 April 2022 |first=Lou |last=Stoppard |title=Exclusive: Harry Styles Reveals the Meaning Behind His New Album, 'Harry's House' |url=https://www.bhg.com/better-homes-and-garden-magazine/harry-styles/ |access-date=28 April 2022 |website=[[Better Homes and Gardens (magazine)|Better Homes & Gardens]] |language=en |archive-date=19 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230419065518/https://www.bhg.com/better-homes-and-garden-magazine/harry-styles/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Philanthropy and advocacy==
[[File:Harry Styles - Xcel Energy Center - 9-22-2021 - 62 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Styles waving a progress pride flag in Little Rock, Arkansas, in November 2021]]
In 2013, Styles and fellow One Direction member [[Liam Payne]] became ambassadors for the cancer charity Trekstock, raising over US$800,000 through the online fundraising platform [[Prizeo]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://trekstock.com/our-story/patrons-ambassadors/|title=Patrons & Ambassadors| publisher= Trekstock| access-date=29 November 2014| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20141030012714/http://trekstock.com/our-story/patrons-ambassadors/ |archive-date= 30 October 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine| last= Lee| first= Ashley| url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5847924/taylor-swift-one-direction-top-list-of-most-charitable-stars|title=Taylor Swift, One Direction Top List of Most Charitable Stars| magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=26 December 2013|access-date=19 January 2014|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20131230013905/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/5847924/taylor-swift-one-direction-top-list-of-most-charitable-stars|archive-date=30 December 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> When the [[Westboro Baptist Church]] picketed a One Direction concert in 2013,<ref name=":5">{{cite web |last= Sieczkowski |first=Cavan |date=22 July 2013 |title=Westboro Baptist Church Pickets One Direction Concert; Harry Styles Responds |url= https://www.huffpost.com/entry/westboro-baptist-church-one-direction_n_3634663 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211230005131/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/westboro-baptist-church-one-direction_n_3634663 |archive-date=30 December 2021 |access-date=30 December 2021 |website=[[HuffPost]]}}</ref> Styles spoke up on Twitter, responding that he "believes in equal rights for everyone."<ref name=":5" /> In 2014, Styles joined LGBT rights charity [[Stonewall (charity)|Stonewall]]'s #FirstSnog campaign in celebration of their 25th anniversary<ref>{{cite news |last= Sharkey |first=Linda |date=10 June 2014 |title=Naomi Campbell, Harry Styles and Henry Holland take a selfie for Stonewall's #FirstSNOG Campaign |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/news/naomi-campbell-harry-styles-and-henry-holland-take-a-selfie-for-stonewall-s-firstsnog-campaign-9481292.html |url-status=live |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20211211200936/https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/news/naomi-campbell-harry-styles-and-henry-holland-take-a-selfie-for-stonewall-s-firstsnog-campaign-9481292.html |archive-date=11 December 2021 |access-date=11 December 2021 |website=[[The Independent]]}}</ref> and showed support for [[Michael Sam]], the first openly gay player drafted by an NFL team, by wearing his jersey onstage during One Direction's concert in St. Louis.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Peters |first=Mitchell |date=30 August 2014 |title=One Direction's Harry Styles Supports Gay NFL Player Michael Sam at St. Louis Concert |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/one-direction-harry-styles-wears-jersey-of-gay-nfl-player-michael-sam-st-louis-rams-6236517/ |url-status=live |magazine= Billboard |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20211211200936/https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/one-direction-harry-styles-wears-jersey-of-gay-nfl-player-michael-sam-st-louis-rams-6236517/ |archive-date=11 December 2021 |access-date=11 December 2021}}</ref> Styles regularly waves pride flags thrown onstage by fans at concerts,<ref>{{cite web |last=Villarreal |first=Yezmin |date=4 September 2015 |title=Harry Styles Wore a Gay Pride Flag as a Cape |url=http://www.pride.com/one-direction/2015/9/04/harry-styles-wore-rainbow-flag-cape-one-direction-concert |access-date=3 July 2022 |website=pride.com |language=en |archive-date=2 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220702031222/https://www.pride.com/one-direction/2015/9/04/harry-styles-wore-rainbow-flag-cape-one-direction-concert |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":6">{{cite web |last=Khan |first=Aamina |date=24 October 2017 |title=Harry Styles' Concerts are LGBTQ+ Safe Spaces |url=https://www.them.us/story/harry-styles-concerts-are-lgbtq-safe-spaces |access-date=3 July 2022 |website=them.us |language=en-US |archive-date=3 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220703232043/https://www.them.us/story/harry-styles-concerts-are-lgbtq-safe-spaces |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=McDaniel |first=Caitlynn |date=18 April 2022 |title=Watch Harry Styles Sing New Song "Boyfriends" |url=https://gayety.co/watch-harry-styles-sing-new-song-boyfriends |access-date=3 July 2022 |website=Gayety.co |language=en-US |archive-date=4 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220704124133/https://gayety.co/watch-harry-styles-sing-new-song-boyfriends |url-status=live }}</ref> and he assists fans with coming out publicly during sections of the show where he engages in banter with the audience.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last= Geraghty |first=Hollie |date=20 June 2022 |title=Harry Styles Helped a Fan Come Out at His London Show |url= https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-fan-come-out-london-show-1370889/ |access-date=3 July 2022 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Avery |first=Dan |date=4 November 2021 |title=Harry Styles helps fan come out to her mom at Milwaukee concert |url= https://www.nbcnews.com/nbc-out/out-pop-culture/harry-styles-helps-fan-come-mom-milwaukee-concert-rcna4578 |access-date=3 July 2022 |website= NBCNews.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Henderson |first=Taylor |date= 26 October 2021 |title=Watch Harry Styles Help This Fan Come Out on Stage |url=https://www.pride.com/celebrities/2021/10/26/watch-harry-styles-help-fan-come-out-stage |access-date= 3 July 2022 |website= pride.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Karlan |first=Sarah |date=17 July 2018 |title=Harry Styles Stopped Mid-Concert To Help A Fan Come Out To Her Mom |url= https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/skarlan/tina-shes-gay |access-date= 3 July 2022 |website= BuzzFeedNews.com |language=en}}</ref> LGBT fans have referred to Styles' concerts as "a safe space."<ref>{{cite web |last=Khan |first=Aamina |date=25 June 2018 |title=Harry Styles' Show Was The Best Queer Girl's Pride Celebration Ever |url= https://www.them.us/story/harry-styles-queer-pride |access-date=3 July 2022 |website=them.us |language=en-US}}</ref> Some of his lesbian and bisexual fans have called him a "[[Gay icon|lesbian icon]]."<ref name=":6" /><ref name="Perry">{{cite web |last= Perry |first=Grace |title=Why Are So Many Queer Women Obsessed With Harry Styles? |url= https://www.buzzfeed.com/graceeperry/why-are-so-many-queer-women-obsessed-with-harry-styles |access-date=3 July 2022 |website= BuzzFeed.com |date=26 November 2017 |language=en}}</ref> He received a ''[[Gay Times]]'' Honour for LGBTQ Advocate.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/harry-styles-is-the-recipient-of-the-gay-times-honours-for-lgbtq-advocate/| title=Harry Styles received a Gay Times Honour for LGBTQ Advocate| last= Corner| first= Lewis| date=8 November 2018|website=[[Gay Times]]|access-date=8 November 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200927115841/https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/harry-styles-is-the-recipient-of-the-gay-times-honours-for-lgbtq-advocate/|archive-date=27 September 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles has been nominated three times at the [[British LGBT Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-02-14 |title=British LGBT Awards 2023 Shortlist Revealed With Nods For Harry Styles, RuPaul, Alison Hammond And Joe Lycett |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/lgbt-awards-2023-nominations-full-list_uk_63eb943ce4b022eb3e328645 |access-date=2024-05-31 |website=HuffPost UK |language=en}}</ref> [[Los Angeles Times|The Los Angeles Times]] called Styles a "champion of the LGBT community" and that "Styles' ability to exist comfortably, and extremely publicly, in a fluid space along the gender spectrum is particularly resonant with young gender-nonconforming fans."<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gelt |first=Jessica |date=2022-10-29 |title=At Harry Styles concerts, young gender-nonconforming fans celebrate the freedom to be themselves |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/music/story/2022-10-29/harry-styles-gender-nonconforming-lgbtq-nonbinary-fans-kia-forum |access-date=2024-05-31 |newspaper=LA Times}}</ref>

In 2014, Styles endorsed [[Emma Watson]]'s [[HeForShe]] gender equality campaign.<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.mtv.co.uk/news/pyrke6/harry-styles-shows-his-support-for-emma-watsons-heforshe-campaign| title= Harry Styles Shows His Support For Emma Watson's #HeForShe Campaign| last= Bacon| first= Lucy|date=26 September 2014| website=[[MTV (UK and Ireland)|MTV.co.uk]]|access-date=8 August 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180808235308/http://www.mtv.co.uk/harry-styles/news/harry-styles-shows-his-support-for-emma-watsons-heforshe-campaign|archive-date=8 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2015, he sponsored water wells in India via Drop4Drop in support of [[Lifewater International|Life Water's]] [[World Water Day]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://drop4drop.org/projects/client/harry-styles/|title= Projects - HARRY STYLES| website=Drop4Drop.org |access-date=11 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811102534/http://drop4drop.org/projects/client/harry-styles/|archive-date=11 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The following year, he donated his hair to the UK charity Little Princess Trust, which supplies and funds wigs made of real hair to children who have hair loss as a result of illnesses.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/159309-harry-styles-donates-his-hair-to-charity-thats-the-best-reason-of-all-for-cutting|work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]|title=Harry Styles Donates His Hair To Charity & That's The Best Reason Of All For Cutting His Locks|first=Michelle|last=Mcgahan|date=7 May 2016|access-date=7 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170926190936/https://www.bustle.com/articles/159309-harry-styles-donates-his-hair-to-charity-thats-the-best-reason-of-all-for-cutting|archive-date=26 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> 
In May 2017, to celebrate the release of his debut album, he played intimate shows at [[The Garage, London|The Garage]] in London and at the [[Troubadour (West Hollywood, California)|Troubadour]] in Los Angeles, with all proceeds benefiting charities.<ref>{{cite magazine| url= https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7801116/harry-styles-one-direction-stevie-nicks-fleetwood-mac-los-angeles-troubadour|magazine= Billboard |title=Watch Harry Styles Duet With Stevie Nicks During Secret Show at L.A.'s Troubadour| first= Steven| last=Horowitz|date=20 May 2017| access-date=20 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170520230342/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7801116/harry-styles-one-direction-stevie-nicks-fleetwood-mac-los-angeles-troubadour|archive-date=20 May 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> That October, he performed at [[CBS Radio]]'s We Can Survive concert at the [[Hollywood Bowl]] for breast cancer awareness.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/pink-harry-styles-hollywood-bowl-we-can-survive-concert-1202596126/ |title=Pink, Harry Styles, Lorde Take on Cancer at We Can Survive Concert| last=Willman|first=Chris|date=22 October 2017| website= Variety.com |access-date=9 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705204157/https://variety.com/2017/music/news/pink-harry-styles-hollywood-bowl-we-can-survive-concert-1202596126/|archive-date=5 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles' first tour raised US$1.2 million in charity donations from ticket sales, [[Live Nation]]'s contributions, and [[GLSEN]]'s Pride campaign toward 62 charities around the world, while his second tour raised more than US$6.5 million for its charity partners Physicians for Reproductive Health, [[Black Voters Matter]] and [[Choose Love (organisation)|Choose Love]], as well as local efforts including aid for food-insecure families in need during the holidays. Both tours also promoted water conservation via recycling and reducing plastic water bottle usage.<ref name="Variety tour">{{cite news| url=https://variety.com/2018/biz/news/harry-styles-tour-tally-nearly-1-million-tickets-sold-1-2-million-in-charity-donations-exclusive-1202877832| title=Harry Styles Tour Tally: Nearly 1 Million Tickets Sold, $1.2 Million in Charity Donations| last=Aswad| first=Jem| work= Variety |date=19 July 2018|access-date=19 July 2018| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180720105926/https://variety.com/2018/biz/news/harry-styles-tour-tally-nearly-1-million-tickets-sold-1-2-million-in-charity-donations-exclusive-1202877832/|archive-date=20 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hstyles.co.uk/tpwk|title=Treat People With Kindness| publisher=Harry Styles Official website|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802012607/https://hstyles.co.uk/tpwk|archive-date=2 August 2018|url-status=live|access-date=9 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-love-on-tour-raises-millions-charity-1235381824/|title=Harry Styles' Love On Tour Raises More Than $6.5 Million for Charity|last=Dailey |first=Hannah |date=July 31, 2023 |magazine=billboard |access-date= May 14, 2024|quote=}}</ref> Styles also made an additional $100,000 joint donation with the [[United Center]] in [[Chicago]] to the creation of the arts and creative entrepreneurship incubator at the former St. Laurence Elementary School as a celebration of his six-night concert residency in Chicago.<ref>{{Cite web |title=MacArthur Investment Supports Rebuild Foundation's St. Laurence Arts Incubator |url=https://www.macfound.org/press/press-releases/macarthur-investment-supports-progress-for-rebuild-foundation%E2%80%99s-st-laurence-arts-incubator |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=www.macfound.org |language=en}}</ref>

In 2018, his online store sold T-shirts with the slogan "Treat People with Kindness" in a rainbow print for [[Pride Month]], with profits benefiting GLSEN.<ref>{{cite web| last=Singh| first= Olivia|title=9 times Harry Styles was a champion for the LGBTQIA+ community |url=https://www.thisisinsider.com/harry-styles-supported-lgtbqia-community-2018-7#when-he-released-pride-shirts-with-the-sales-going-to-glsen-1| work=[[Insider Inc.#Websites|Insider]]| access-date=9 August 2018|date=19 July 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180809090828/https://www.thisisinsider.com/harry-styles-supported-lgtbqia-community-2018-7#when-he-released-pride-shirts-with-the-sales-going-to-glsen-1|archive-date=9 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> That year, Styles also tweeted in support of the [[March for Our Lives]] petition,<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8224521/harry-styles-march-for-our-lives-signs-petition-gun-control |title=Harry Styles Signed March For Our Lives Petition & Says 'You Should Too'|magazine= Billboard| last=Maher| first=Natalie|date=2 March 2018| access-date=2 March 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180304083938/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8224521/harry-styles-march-for-our-lives-signs-petition-gun-control|archive-date=4 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and added "Black Lives Matter" and "End Gun Violence" stickers to his guitar.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Tornow| first=Sam| title=Harry Styles Adds 'Black Lives Matter Sticker' To His Guitar|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8463013/harry-styles-black-lives-matter-statement-guitar-photo|magazine= Billboard |access-date=16 August 2018|date=27 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180816064409/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8463013/harry-styles-black-lives-matter-statement-guitar-photo|archive-date=16 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles identifies as a [[Feminism|feminist]].<ref name=EternalSunshineHarry/> In December 2019, in response to an interview question about not using his influence more often to support specific causes, Styles stated: {{blockquote|Because of dilution. Because I'd prefer, when I say something, for people to think I mean it. To be honest, I'm still searching for that one thing, y'know. Something I can really stand up for, and get behind, and be like: This Is My Life Fight. There's a power to doing the one thing. You want your whole weight behind it.<ref name="Lamont"/>}}

On the impact of events such as [[Brexit]], the [[Black Lives Matter]] movement and [[First presidency of Donald Trump|Donald Trump's presidency]] on his song "[[Sign of the Times (Harry Styles song)|Sign of the Times]]," he said that "We're in a difficult time, and I think we've been in many difficult times before. But we happen to be in a time where things happening around the world are absolutely impossible to ignore. I think it would've been strange to not acknowledge what was going on at all."<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/11/arts/music/harry-styles-solo-album-interview.html|title=Harry Styles Opens Up, Slightly, About Going Solo With a Rock Edge|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=11 May 2017|access-date=14 November 2020|archive-date=8 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208070738/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/11/arts/music/harry-styles-solo-album-interview.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles leans to the political [[Left-wing politics|left]], and he visited the [[House of Lords]] in 2016 to attend a debate on Brexit following an invitation by [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] peer [[Robert Winston|Lord Winston]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Ashleigh Rainbird |date=22 February 2013 |title='I lean to the left': Harry Styles reveals his political direction is Labour |url= https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/harry-styles-labour-supporter-one-1723763 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211215032314/https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/harry-styles-labour-supporter-one-1723763 |archive-date=15 December 2021 |access-date=15 December 2021 |work=The Mirror}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/harry-styles-makes-surprise-visit-to-house-of-lords-to-attend-brexit-debate-a3289706.html| title=Harry Styles makes surprise visit to House of Lords to attend Brexit debate|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|date=6 July 2016|access-date=15 December 2021|archive-date=15 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211215032314/https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/harry-styles-makes-surprise-visit-to-house-of-lords-to-attend-brexit-debate-a3289706.html|url-status=live}}</ref> Regarding Brexit, he stated that "anything that brings people together is better than things that pull people apart" and stated that it symbolises "the opposite of the world [he] would like to be in."<ref name="rolling stone" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Murison |first=Krissi |title=Exclusive interview: Harry Styles on his new album and life after One Direction |newspaper=[[The Times]] |language=en |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/exclusive-interview-harry-styles-on-new-album-one-direction-nqvbjjvjw |access-date=28 June 2022 |issn=0140-0460}}</ref>

In light of the [[murder of George Floyd]] in May 2020, Styles showed support for Black Lives Matter, urging fans to share and donate in support, and pledged to donate to a bail fund for arrested Black Lives Matter activists.<ref>{{cite magazine| last=Bailey |first=Alyssa|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a32868396/harry-styles-mustache-beard-quarantine-photo/|title=Harry Styles Has Committed To A Mustache And Beard In Quarantine|magazine=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]| date=15 June 2020| access-date=12 October 2020| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201012130624/https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a32868396/harry-styles-mustache-beard-quarantine-photo/| archive-date=12 October 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| last=O'Connor|first=Roisin|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/harry-styles-black-lives-matter-donate-bail-protests-us-george-floyd-police-racism-a9542111.html|title=Harry Styles donates to arrested Black Lives Matter activists: 'Being not racist is not enough, we must be anti-racist'|date=1 June 2020|access-date=15 December 2021|newspaper= The Independent |archive-date=15 December 2021| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20211215033321/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/harry-styles-black-lives-matter-donate-bail-protests-us-george-floyd-police-racism-a9542111.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He attended a Los Angeles Black Lives Matter protest the following month.<ref>{{cite web| last= Bailey |first= Alyssa|date=3 June 2020| title= Harry Styles Joined a Los Angeles Black Lives Matter Protest |url= https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a32754617/harry-styles-los-angeles-black-lives-matter-protest-photo/|access-date=11 October 2020|website= Elle |archive-date=11 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201011213104/https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a32754617/harry-styles-los-angeles-black-lives-matter-protest-photo/|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite being a British citizen, Styles endorsed [[Joe Biden]] in the [[2020 United States presidential election]].<ref>{{cite news|last1= Kurtz| first1= Judy| url= https://thehill.com/blogs/in-the-know/in-the-know/523016-harry-styles-backs-biden-if-i-could-vote-in-america-id-vote|title=Harry Styles backs Biden: 'If I could vote in America, I'd vote with kindness'|newspaper=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]|date=27 October 2020|access-date=28 October 2020|archive-date=1 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101050619/https://thehill.com/blogs/in-the-know/in-the-know/523016-harry-styles-backs-biden-if-i-could-vote-in-america-id-vote|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles also endorsed Texas' gubernatorial race candidate [[Beto O'Rourke]] by inviting him to his shows in Austin, Texas.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Chan |first=Anna |date=2022-10-14 |title=Beto O'Rourke Is 'So Grateful' for Harry Styles' Endorsement: 'He's Well Aware of' the Issues |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/harry-styles-endorses-beto-o-rourke-texas-governor-hopeful-reacts-1235156160/ |access-date=2024-05-30 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref>

Styles is also an advocate for abortion rights. Speaking to [[Howard Stern]], Styles said the then potential overturning of [[Roe v. Wade]] was "scary" and "going backwards" and that "there should be backlash and uproar for these things."<ref>{{Cite web |last=Daly |first=Rhian |date=2022-05-19 |title=Harry Styles on overturning of Roe v. Wade: "It's quite scary to see how far backwards we're going" |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/harry-styles-overturning-roe-v-wade-3229689 |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=NME |language=en-GB}}</ref> When the ruling was overturned in June 2022, Styles posted on [[Twitter]]: "I'm absolutely devastated for the people of America today. Check on your friends. Look after each other. We're all in this together, and the fight is just beginning. A truly dark day for America."<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-06-25 |title=Harry Styles says the overturning of Roe v. Wade marks a 'dark day for America' |url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/harry-styles-abortion-roe-v-wade-overturn-153052817.html |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=Yahoo News |language=en-GB}}</ref> Styles referenced the ruling at his concert in Austin, Texas, telling the crowd that "No one can tell you what to do with your own body, it's yours."<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-09-29 |title=Harry Styles speaks on abortion rights during Austin residency |url=https://www.fox7austin.com/news/harry-styles-austin-texas-residency-abortion-rights |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=FOX 7 Austin |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 2 June 2022, Styles announced he was donating his appearance fee from Apple's [[AirPods]]' spatial audio campaign to the [[International Rescue Committee]], a global humanitarian aid organization that is responding to the more than six million refugees being forced to flee [[Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Garcia|first=Thania|title=Harry Styles Donates His Apple Commercial Paycheck to Refugee-Aid Organization| url=https://variety.com/2022/music/news/harry-styles-donates-apple-airpods-irc-donation-1235283592/|date=2 June 2022|access-date=2 June 2022|website=Variety}}</ref> Continuing the partnership, Styles also invited three Ukrainian refugees supported by the International Rescue Committee (IRC) to Love On Tour at his show at [[Warsaw]]'s PGE Narodowy Stadium in July 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |title=IRC supporter Harry Styles invites Ukrainian refugees in Poland to 'Love On Tour' concert in Warsaw {{!}} International Rescue Committee (IRC) |url=https://www.rescue.org/uk/press-release/irc-supporter-harry-styles-invites-ukrainian-refugees-poland-love-tour-concert-warsaw |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=www.rescue.org |language=en-gb}}</ref>  Styles also donated the fee for the use of his song ''Treat People with Kindness'' featured in [[Marks & Spencer|Marks and Spencer's]] 2022 Christmas advert to [[Centrepoint (charity)|Centrepoint]], a charity helping homeless young adults in the UK.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Harry Styles donates Christmas song fee to Centrepoint {{!}} Centrepoint |url=https://centrepoint.org.uk/news/harry-styles-donates-christmas-song-fee-centrepoint |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=centrepoint.org.uk |language=en}}</ref>

In 2022 and 2023, following the [[Uvalde school shooting|mass shooting at Robb Elementary School]] in Uvalde, Texas, Styles partnered with the nonprofit organization [[Everytown for Gun Safety|Everytown]] for Gun Safety for 44 shows across five cities in North America as part of his Love On Tour.<ref>{{cite web |title=Harry Styles Love on Tour x Everytown |url=https://everytownsupportfund.org/initiatives/cultural-and-entertainment-advocacy/music/ |website=Everytown Support Fund |access-date=15 May 2024}}</ref> Styles and [[Live Nation (events promoter)|Live Nation]] donated $1 million to the Everytown Support Fund, the education, research, and litigation arm of Everytown. Throughout the partnership, volunteers with Students Demand Action, one of Everytown's grassroots networks, tabled at shows to spread awareness about the gun safety movement and encourage fans to join efforts to end gun violence in America.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Janfaza |first1=Rachel |title=Harry Styles and Everytown Partnership Gets Young People Involved in Gun Violence Activism |url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/harry-styles-everytown-for-gun-safety |access-date=15 May 2024 |work=Teen Vogue |agency=Teen Vogue |publisher=Condé Nast |date=27 February 2023}}</ref> The partnership between Styles and Everytown earned industry recognition, winning a [[Pollstar|Pollstar Award]] for Brand Partnership/Live Campaign of the Year in 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Garcia |first=Thania |date=2023-02-23 |title=Dave Chappelle, Dave Grohl, Don Henley Drop in on 2023 Pollstar Awards, Where Harry Styles Wins Major Tour of the Year |url=https://variety.com/2023/music/news/harry-styles-dave-chappelle-2023-pollstar-awards-1235533062/ |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=Variety |language=en-US}}</ref>

Styles is a patron of the [[MusiCares]] non profit organization, and joined [[Fleetwood Mac]] for a performance of ''[[The Chain]]'' when the band were honored with the [[MusiCares Person of the Year]] award in 2018.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Spanos |first=Brittany |date=2018-01-27 |title=Harry Styles, Haim and Bill Clinton Honor Fleetwood Mac's Legacy |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-live-reviews/harry-styles-haim-and-bill-clinton-honor-fleetwood-macs-legacy-at-musicares-tribute-201131/ |access-date=2024-05-30 |magazine=Rolling Stone |language=en-US}}</ref> Styles donates items to the organization's annual charity relief auction, including multiple autographed [[Gibson Brands|Gibson]] and [[Gretsch]] electric guitars, and signed versions of his albums.<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Nazareno |first=Mia |date=2021-12-20 |title=BTS, Harry Styles & More Offering Rare Collectibles for MusiCares Auction |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/bts-harry-styles-collectibles-musicares-auction-2022-1235012993/ |access-date=2024-05-30 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Kaufman |first=Gil |date=2024-01-11 |title=Taylor Swift Guitar, Christine McVie Piano, Items From Harry Styles, Paul McCartney & More Up For 2024 MusiCares Auction |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/2024-musicares-auction-items-list-taylor-swift-harry-styles-1235580032/ |access-date=2024-05-30 |magazine=Billboard |language=en-US}}</ref>

During the COVID-19 lockdowns, Styles released t-shirts with the slogan 'Stay Home. Stay Safe. Protect Each Other,' on the front and 'This t-shirt fights COVID-19. Treat people with kindness' on the back with 100% of the profits going towards the [[COVID-19 Solidarity Response Fund]] by the [[World Health Organization]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=SPIN |date=2018-07-07 |title=Harry Styles Is Selling T-Shirts To Raise Money For The COVID-19 Solidarity Response Fund |url=https://www.spin1038.com/celeb/harry-styles-selling-t-shirts-raise-money-covid-19-solidarity-response-fund-996751 |access-date=2024-05-31 |website=SPIN1038 |language=en}}</ref> Styles also paid his core tour crew's salaries for the duration of the postponed dates until the end of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-03-25 |title=Harry Styles apparently paid his tour crew's salaries after postponing Love on Tour |url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/harry-styles-love-on-tour-crew-salary/ |access-date=2024-05-31 |website=Capital |language=en}}</ref>

===Treat People with Kindness===
"Treat People with Kindness," abbreviated to "TPWK," is a slogan used by Styles to promote his message of love, acceptance, and kindness to others.<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/harry-styles/tpwk-treat-people-with-kindness-album/ |title=What does Harry Styles's 'TPWK' stand for as his second album approaches?|website=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]] |access-date=30 March 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200329073216/https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/harry-styles/tpwk-treat-people-with-kindness-album/|url-status=live}}</ref> Styles began using the slogan during his debut concert tour in 2017 on a badge on his guitar and tour merchandise, including Pride T-shirts sold to raise funds for GLSEN.<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.dailytarheel.com/article/2017/10/review-harry-styles-preaches-kindness-at-d-c-show| title= Review: Harry Styles preaches kindness at D.C. show| website= [[The Daily Tar Heel]] |access-date=30 March 2020| archive-date=29 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200329114116/https://www.dailytarheel.com/article/2017/10/review-harry-styles-preaches-kindness-at-d-c-show|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.mtv.co.uk/news/b46wy8/harry-styles-new-tshirts-in-celebration-of-pride-are-all-we-wanna-wear-this-summer|title=Harry Styles' New T-Shirts In Celebration Of Pride Are All We Wanna Wear This Summer |publisher=[[MTV]]|access-date=30 March 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200329093042/http://www.mtv.co.uk/mtv-style-0/news/harry-styles-new-tshirts-in-celebration-of-pride-are-all-we-wanna-wear-this-summer|url-status= live}}</ref> In a December 2019 interview, he stated, "It was a pin I had on my guitar strap and we made T-shirts for it, then I saw a lot of T-shirts around. I'd be driving or something and see someone in one and I started feeling like, 'Oh this is a bit of a thing.'" The initiative gave Styles the idea to write a song titled after the slogan, which serves as the penultimate track on his second studio album, ''Fine Line''.<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/small-changes-make-a-big-difference-harry-styles-tells-the-story-of-treat-people-with-kindness/078397 |title='Small changes make a big difference': Harry Styles tells the story of Treat People With Kindness |website=[[Music Week]]|access-date= 30 March 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200329105756/https://www.musicweek.com/talent/read/small-changes-make-a-big-difference-harry-styles-tells-the-story-of-treat-people-with-kindness/078397| url-status=live}}</ref> The track was later released as a single with a subsequent music video featuring writer and actress [[Phoebe Waller-Bridge]] in January 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Marlowe |first=Gary |date=2024-01-15 |title=Treat People With Kindness: The story behind the song |url=https://gmarlowe.medium.com/treat-people-with-kindness-3a12815bedfe |access-date=2024-05-30 |website=[[Medium (website)|Medium]] |language=en}}</ref>

In October 2019, teaser posters including the phrase "Do you know who you are?" and the acronym "TPWK" were spotted in London, Tokyo, Los Angeles, New York, and Australia; fans were able to connect the posters to Styles and his new album release because of the reference to his "Treat People with Kindness" motto.<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/harry-styles/do-you-know-who-you-are-poster-hs2-music-1d/|title=Harry Styles is covering the world in teaser posters for new music 'Do You Know Who You Are'|website=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]] |access-date=30 March 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329131541/https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/harry-styles/do-you-know-who-you-are-poster-hs2-music-1d/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-10-09-buzz-for-harry-styles-new-album-begins-see-the-mysterious-poster/|title=Buzz For Harry Styles' New Album Begins: See The Mysterious Poster |date=9 October 2019 |agency=[[iHeartRadio]] |last=Brooks |first=Hayden |access-date=30 March 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329130552/https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-10-09-buzz-for-harry-styles-new-album-begins-see-the-mysterious-poster/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{cite magazine| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/harry-styles-new-album-one-direction-fan-world-mental-health-day-twitter-a9151416.html|title=Harry Styles sends fan touching mental health message as he hints at new album|date=10 October 2019|magazine=[[The Independent]]| access-date=30 March 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200329143153/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/harry-styles-new-album-one-direction-fan-world-mental-health-day-twitter-a9151416.html|url-status=live}}</ref> At the same time, to mark [[World Mental Health Day]], Styles launched a website bot called "Do You Know Who You Are?" that gives users positive randomised messages using words such as "bright," "determined," "loving," and "wonderful" and ending with "TPWK. LOVE, H."<ref name="auto"/><ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/voices/culture/article/2019/10/11/ill-wait-you-harry-styles-encouraging-words-fans| title='I'll wait for you': Harry Styles encouraging words for fans| publisher=[[Special Broadcasting Service]] |access-date=30 March 2020|archive-date=29 March 2020| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329140208/https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/voices/culture/article/2019/10/11/ill-wait-you-harry-styles-encouraging-words-fans|url-status=live}}</ref>

